{"_id":"00fhc3ohho3chf00","name":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-alicia-the-young-girl-in-love","ownerKey":"alicia-the-young-girl-in-love","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Alicia is Alissa's young lover who has infiltrated Wonder in an attempt to free her imprisoned partner. In addition to their romantic bond, Alicia is driven by guilt, convinced that Alissa was sent to Wonder due to the two girls' relationship. Alissa had even refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke of Norfolk's heir. Despite her courage and tenacity, Alicia soon became a prisoner of the deranged rooms of Wonder.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run away with her to live out our love in peace","contact":"<p>Alicia is Alissa's young lover who has infiltrated Wonder in an attempt to free her imprisoned partner. In addition to their romantic bond, Alicia is driven by guilt, convinced that Alissa was sent to Wonder due to the two girls' relationship. Alissa had even refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke of Norfolk's heir. Despite her courage and tenacity, Alicia soon became a prisoner of the deranged rooms of Wonder.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Alicia is Alissa's young lover who has infiltrated Wonder in an attempt to free her imprisoned partner. In addition to their romantic bond, Alicia is driven by guilt, convinced that Alissa was sent to Wonder due to the two girls' relationship. Alissa had even refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke of Norfolk's heir. Despite her courage and tenacity, Alicia soon became a prisoner of the deranged rooms of Wonder.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run away with her to live out our love in peace","contact":"<p>Alicia is Alissa's young lover who has infiltrated Wonder in an attempt to free her imprisoned partner. In addition to their romantic bond, Alicia is driven by guilt, convinced that Alissa was sent to Wonder due to the two girls' relationship. Alissa had even refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke of Norfolk's heir. Despite her courage and tenacity, Alicia soon became a prisoner of the deranged rooms of Wonder.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01rgjv5225vjgr10","name":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","ownerKey":"alicia-the-young-girl-in-love","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own</p>","positive":"I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"017k3i1qq1i3k710","name":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","ownerKey":"alicia-the-young-girl-in-love","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to my tenacity, I can overcome every obstacle</p>","positive":"Thanks to my tenacity, I can overcome every obstacle"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to my tenacity, I can overcome every obstacle</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Thanks to my tenacity, I can overcome every obstacle","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0086xc3aa3cx6800","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","ownerKey":"alicia-the-young-girl-in-love","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Alicia is Alissa's young lover who has infiltrated Wonder in an attempt to free her imprisoned partner. In addition to their romantic bond, Alicia is driven by guilt, convinced that Alissa was sent to Wonder due to the two girls' relationship. Alissa had even refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke of Norfolk's heir. Despite her courage and tenacity, Alicia soon became a prisoner of the deranged rooms of Wonder.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own<br>2. Thanks to my tenacity, I can overcome every obstacle</p><p>Agenda:<br>I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run away with her to live out our love in peace</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Alicia is Alissa's young lover who has infiltrated Wonder in an attempt to free her imprisoned partner. In addition to their romantic bond, Alicia is driven by guilt, convinced that Alissa was sent to Wonder due to the two girls' relationship. Alissa had even refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke of Norfolk's heir. Despite her courage and tenacity, Alicia soon became a prisoner of the deranged rooms of Wonder.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own<br>2. Thanks to my tenacity, I can overcome every obstacle</p><p>Agenda:<br>I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run away with her to live out our love in peace</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01hyqokyykoqyh10","name":"Alissa of Norfolk","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-tan.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Alissa of Norfolk","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-tan.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-alissa-of-norfolk","ownerKey":"alissa-of-norfolk","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alissa of Norfolk","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Alissa is the daughter of the Duke of Norfolk himself. Five months ago, she was taken to Wonder asylum due to her 'too rebellious and unseemly attitude for a young noblewoman.' The truth is that Alissa had refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with her lover Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke's heir. After the first month at Wonder, her letters to her family became more and more terrified and delusional, until they abruptly ceased. According to her words, Wonder is hell on earth where strange presences move in the dark rooms. When she proved incredibly resistant to Alice's 'cures,' the Director imprisoned her in the Hall of the Mind, invading her mind daily with nightmares to quell her rebellious spirit. Despite the physical toll, her love for Alicia has kept her mind strong and anchored to reality.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a future with Alicia","contact":"<p>Alissa is the daughter of the Duke of Norfolk himself. Five months ago, she was taken to Wonder asylum due to her 'too rebellious and unseemly attitude for a young noblewoman.' The truth is that Alissa had refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with her lover Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke's heir. After the first month at Wonder, her letters to her family became more and more terrified and delusional, until they abruptly ceased. According to her words, Wonder is hell on earth where strange presences move in the dark rooms. When she proved incredibly resistant to Alice's 'cures,' the Director imprisoned her in the Hall of the Mind, invading her mind daily with nightmares to quell her rebellious spirit. Despite the physical toll, her love for Alicia has kept her mind strong and anchored to reality.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Alissa is the daughter of the Duke of Norfolk himself. Five months ago, she was taken to Wonder asylum due to her 'too rebellious and unseemly attitude for a young noblewoman.' The truth is that Alissa had refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with her lover Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke's heir. After the first month at Wonder, her letters to her family became more and more terrified and delusional, until they abruptly ceased. According to her words, Wonder is hell on earth where strange presences move in the dark rooms. When she proved incredibly resistant to Alice's 'cures,' the Director imprisoned her in the Hall of the Mind, invading her mind daily with nightmares to quell her rebellious spirit. Despite the physical toll, her love for Alicia has kept her mind strong and anchored to reality.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a future with Alicia","contact":"<p>Alissa is the daughter of the Duke of Norfolk himself. Five months ago, she was taken to Wonder asylum due to her 'too rebellious and unseemly attitude for a young noblewoman.' The truth is that Alissa had refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with her lover Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke's heir. After the first month at Wonder, her letters to her family became more and more terrified and delusional, until they abruptly ceased. According to her words, Wonder is hell on earth where strange presences move in the dark rooms. When she proved incredibly resistant to Alice's 'cures,' the Director imprisoned her in the Hall of the Mind, invading her mind daily with nightmares to quell her rebellious spirit. Despite the physical toll, her love for Alicia has kept her mind strong and anchored to reality.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00j9nm2882mn9j00","name":"Alissa of Norfolk - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alissa of Norfolk","ownerKey":"alissa-of-norfolk","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alissa of Norfolk - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder</p>","positive":"I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Alissa of Norfolk","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01w0tnnaannt0w10","name":"Alissa of Norfolk - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alissa of Norfolk","ownerKey":"alissa-of-norfolk","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alissa of Norfolk - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>My mind is still strong</p>","positive":"My mind is still strong"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>My mind is still strong</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Alissa of Norfolk","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My mind is still strong","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01xci83ii38icx10","name":"Alissa of Norfolk - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alissa of Norfolk","ownerKey":"alissa-of-norfolk","itemKey":"descriptor2.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alissa of Norfolk - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>My love for Alicia kept me in the real world</p>","positive":"My love for Alicia kept me in the real world"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>My love for Alicia kept me in the real world</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.aldeano","owner":"Alissa of Norfolk","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My love for Alicia kept me in the real world","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01g5saszzsas5g10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alissa of Norfolk","ownerKey":"alissa-of-norfolk","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Alissa is the daughter of the Duke of Norfolk himself. Five months ago, she was taken to Wonder asylum due to her 'too rebellious and unseemly attitude for a young noblewoman.' The truth is that Alissa had refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with her lover Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke's heir. After the first month at Wonder, her letters to her family became more and more terrified and delusional, until they abruptly ceased. According to her words, Wonder is hell on earth where strange presences move in the dark rooms. When she proved incredibly resistant to Alice's 'cures,' the Director imprisoned her in the Hall of the Mind, invading her mind daily with nightmares to quell her rebellious spirit. Despite the physical toll, her love for Alicia has kept her mind strong and anchored to reality.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder<br>2. My mind is still strong<br>3. My love for Alicia kept me in the real world</p><p>Agenda:<br>Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a future with Alicia</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Alissa is the daughter of the Duke of Norfolk himself. Five months ago, she was taken to Wonder asylum due to her 'too rebellious and unseemly attitude for a young noblewoman.' The truth is that Alissa had refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with her lover Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke's heir. After the first month at Wonder, her letters to her family became more and more terrified and delusional, until they abruptly ceased. According to her words, Wonder is hell on earth where strange presences move in the dark rooms. When she proved incredibly resistant to Alice's 'cures,' the Director imprisoned her in the Hall of the Mind, invading her mind daily with nightmares to quell her rebellious spirit. Despite the physical toll, her love for Alicia has kept her mind strong and anchored to reality.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder<br>2. My mind is still strong<br>3. My love for Alicia kept me in the real world</p><p>Agenda:<br>Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a future with Alicia</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Alissa of Norfolk","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"010p9chpphc9p010","name":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-alizee-the-fugitive-nun","ownerKey":"alizee-the-fugitive-nun","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Key to resolving the spirit problem. Her Spiritualist Gift can remove Grudge Tokens from the underground pit. Will help if Hunters protect her and Lorenzo's secret.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don't need to fear the Church's punishment","contact":"<p>A young nun who abandoned her religious vows for love of Lorenzo. Possesses the natural ability to see and communicate with spirits, though this gift sometimes frightens her. Hiding in the Cemetery of the Innocents to avoid the Church's severe judgment. Watches the Hunters from behind tombstones, ready to intervene to help Lorenzo. Will try not to reveal her abilities unless cornered. Can sense that spirits are very agitated due to both a powerful hateful spirit (Yvonne) and the imminent passage of the comet Morituris.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Key to resolving the spirit problem. Her Spiritualist Gift can remove Grudge Tokens from the underground pit. Will help if Hunters protect her and Lorenzo's secret.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don't need to fear the Church's punishment","contact":"<p>A young nun who abandoned her religious vows for love of Lorenzo. Possesses the natural ability to see and communicate with spirits, though this gift sometimes frightens her. Hiding in the Cemetery of the Innocents to avoid the Church's severe judgment. Watches the Hunters from behind tombstones, ready to intervene to help Lorenzo. Will try not to reveal her abilities unless cornered. Can sense that spirits are very agitated due to both a powerful hateful spirit (Yvonne) and the imminent passage of the comet Morituris.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00rfe65ee56efr00","name":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","ownerKey":"alizee-the-fugitive-nun","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me.</p>","positive":"I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01hu42zmmz24uh10","name":"Spiritualist","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","ownerKey":"alizee-the-fugitive-nun","itemKey":"don1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Spiritualist","system":{"description":"<p>Alizée can see and communicate with spirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past twenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit energy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can obtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she has perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove a Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Alizée can see and communicate with spirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past twenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit energy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can obtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she has perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove a Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.aldeano","owner":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","category":"Villager Gift","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00jwd9x66x9dwj00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","ownerKey":"alizee-the-fugitive-nun","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A young nun who abandoned her religious vows for love of Lorenzo. Possesses the natural ability to see and communicate with spirits, though this gift sometimes frightens her. Hiding in the Cemetery of the Innocents to avoid the Church's severe judgment. Watches the Hunters from behind tombstones, ready to intervene to help Lorenzo. Will try not to reveal her abilities unless cornered. Can sense that spirits are very agitated due to both a powerful hateful spirit (Yvonne) and the imminent passage of the comet Morituris.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don't need to fear the Church's punishment</p><p>Gifts:<br>Spiritualist: Alizée can see and communicate with spirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past twenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit energy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can obtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she has perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove a Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.</p><p>Notes:<br>Key to resolving the spirit problem. Her Spiritualist Gift can remove Grudge Tokens from the underground pit. Will help if Hunters protect her and Lorenzo's secret.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A young nun who abandoned her religious vows for love of Lorenzo. Possesses the natural ability to see and communicate with spirits, though this gift sometimes frightens her. Hiding in the Cemetery of the Innocents to avoid the Church's severe judgment. Watches the Hunters from behind tombstones, ready to intervene to help Lorenzo. Will try not to reveal her abilities unless cornered. Can sense that spirits are very agitated due to both a powerful hateful spirit (Yvonne) and the imminent passage of the comet Morituris.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability sometimes scares me.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don't need to fear the Church's punishment</p><p>Gifts:<br>Spiritualist: Alizée can see and communicate with spirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past twenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit energy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can obtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she has perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove a Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.</p><p>Notes:<br>Key to resolving the spirit problem. Her Spiritualist Gift can remove Grudge Tokens from the underground pit. Will help if Hunters protect her and Lorenzo's secret.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Alizée - The Fugitive Nun","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00slo6h77h6ols00","name":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-amabile-burromo-innkeeper","ownerKey":"amabile-burromo-innkeeper","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Unscrupulous businessman. Will eventually discover Carlo's payment fraud. Can provide information about Carlo if properly motivated (bribed or threatened).</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"To make profitable deals, without worrying about scruples","contact":"<p>The greedy owner of Villa Balocchi, a sumptuous recently refurbished inn on the edge of Sinalunga. Amabile is in open competition with the historic town inn, the Gambero Rosso. He provides lodging for Carlo, letting the puppet sleep in a small back room. Carlo pays with stones temporarily turned into gold coins through his lies - Amabile has thrown them into his safe without noticing the trick yet. Cares only about profit and asks no questions about his guests.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Unscrupulous businessman. Will eventually discover Carlo's payment fraud. Can provide information about Carlo if properly motivated (bribed or threatened).</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"To make profitable deals, without worrying about scruples","contact":"<p>The greedy owner of Villa Balocchi, a sumptuous recently refurbished inn on the edge of Sinalunga. Amabile is in open competition with the historic town inn, the Gambero Rosso. He provides lodging for Carlo, letting the puppet sleep in a small back room. Carlo pays with stones temporarily turned into gold coins through his lies - Amabile has thrown them into his safe without noticing the trick yet. Cares only about profit and asks no questions about his guests.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"0000xqgvvgqx0000","name":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper","ownerKey":"amabile-burromo-innkeeper","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only.</p>","positive":"I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0094rpnoonpr4900","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper","ownerKey":"amabile-burromo-innkeeper","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>The greedy owner of Villa Balocchi, a sumptuous recently refurbished inn on the edge of Sinalunga. Amabile is in open competition with the historic town inn, the Gambero Rosso. He provides lodging for Carlo, letting the puppet sleep in a small back room. Carlo pays with stones temporarily turned into gold coins through his lies - Amabile has thrown them into his safe without noticing the trick yet. Cares only about profit and asks no questions about his guests.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only.</p><p>Agenda:<br>To make profitable deals, without worrying about scruples</p><p>Notes:<br>Unscrupulous businessman. Will eventually discover Carlo's payment fraud. Can provide information about Carlo if properly motivated (bribed or threatened).</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The greedy owner of Villa Balocchi, a sumptuous recently refurbished inn on the edge of Sinalunga. Amabile is in open competition with the historic town inn, the Gambero Rosso. He provides lodging for Carlo, letting the puppet sleep in a small back room. Carlo pays with stones temporarily turned into gold coins through his lies - Amabile has thrown them into his safe without noticing the trick yet. Cares only about profit and asks no questions about his guests.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only.</p><p>Agenda:<br>To make profitable deals, without worrying about scruples</p><p>Notes:<br>Unscrupulous businessman. Will eventually discover Carlo's payment fraud. Can provide information about Carlo if properly motivated (bribed or threatened).</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"name":"Andersen - The Former Commander","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-rivited-steel.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Andersen - The Former Commander","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-rivited-steel.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-andersen-the-former-commander","ownerKey":"andersen-the-former-commander","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries 1.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Andersen - The Former Commander","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Andersen is a skilled commander capable of coordinating defenses and enhancing allies with his orders. He genuinely wants to protect Satu and Erik, but his dark secret haunts him. He has a diary containing evidence of his crimes. If Erik is put in danger, Andersen will confess everything to save the child. The estate has ~20 servants but few can fight—defense relies on Andersen and Christian.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Defend my new family from the danger that Enar represents\nRedeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her understand that I am now a different man\nPrevent anyone from discovering what I have done","contact":"<p>Andersen is a former military commander who now lives on a luxurious estate near Sundsvall. Six years ago, he led a company of soldiers that included Enar. When Andersen discovered that Enar and the dancer Satu were in love, he became consumed with jealousy. Andersen abused his authority, raping Satu and then falsely accusing Enar of abandoning his post. As punishment, Enar was chained to rocks and left to drown in the sea. The injustice drove Enar to become an immortal monster seeking revenge. Unknown to Enar, Andersen fathered a son with Satu—Erik—whom Andersen now raises as his own. Andersen has tried to atone for his crimes by becoming a benefactor, but his past has caught up with him as Enar systematically hunts down and kills all members of the former company.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills</p>"}}}},"legacyNames":["Andersen - The Commander","Andersen - The Former Commander"]}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Captain Andersen is a former Carolean commander and war hero who led his company through the bloody Swedish-Russian war. Six years ago, driven by jealousy and strict religious discipline, he ordered the brutal punishment of Private Enar—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea—for deserting to be with Satu, a dancer Andersen himself secretly loved. After the execution, overcome with obsession, Andersen raped Satu, resulting in the birth of his son Erik. Now a wealthy retired officer living on his estate near Borgholm, Andersen is haunted by guilt. He has sought out Satu, freed her from poverty, and brought her and Erik to live with him, desperately trying to earn her forgiveness and build a family. But Enar has returned as an immortal monster bent on revenge, and Andersen must defend his newfound happiness while hiding the shameful truth of his past crimes from everyone, including his former soldiers.</p>"},"background":"<p>Captain Andersen is a former Carolean commander and war hero who led his company through the bloody Swedish-Russian war. Six years ago, driven by jealousy and strict religious discipline, he ordered the brutal punishment of Private Enar—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea—for deserting to be with Satu, a dancer Andersen himself secretly loved. After the execution, overcome with obsession, Andersen raped Satu, resulting in the birth of his son Erik. Now a wealthy retired officer living on his estate near Borgholm, Andersen is haunted by guilt. He has sought out Satu, freed her from poverty, and brought her and Erik to live with him, desperately trying to earn her forgiveness and build a family. But Enar has returned as an immortal monster bent on revenge, and Andersen must defend his newfound happiness while hiding the shameful truth of his past crimes from everyone, including his former soldiers.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"medium","impulse":"Defend my new family from the danger that Enar represents","oppositionLevel":5},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Defend my new family from the danger that Enar represents\nRedeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her understand that I am now a different man\nPrevent anyone from discovering what I have done","contact":"<p>Captain Andersen is a former Carolean commander and war hero who led his company through the bloody Swedish-Russian war. Six years ago, driven by jealousy and strict religious discipline, he ordered the brutal punishment of Private Enar—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea—for deserting to be with Satu, a dancer Andersen himself secretly loved. After the execution, overcome with obsession, Andersen raped Satu, resulting in the birth of his son Erik. Now a wealthy retired officer living on his estate near Borgholm, Andersen is haunted by guilt. He has sought out Satu, freed her from poverty, and brought her and Erik to live with him, desperately trying to earn her forgiveness and build a family. But Enar has returned as an immortal monster bent on revenge, and Andersen must defend his newfound happiness while hiding the shameful truth of his past crimes from everyone, including his former soldiers.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"r2WW5RD2hibbYgmS","name":"Andersen - The Former Commander - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","ownerKey":"andersen-the-former-commander","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.andersen-the-former-commander","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.andersen-the-former-commander","sourceBackup":"Adversaries 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills</p>","notes":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.andersen-the-former-commander","owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"CNZIjYjKcvnBJTpM","name":"Andersen - The Former Commander - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","ownerKey":"andersen-the-former-commander","itemKey":"descriptor2.andersen-the-former-commander","contentKey":"descriptor2.andersen-the-former-commander","sourceBackup":"Adversaries 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a capable fighter trained in Carolean military tactics</p>","notes":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.andersen-the-former-commander","owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a capable fighter trained in Carolean military tactics","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"XVuvoFOxBvLvijh2","name":"Andersen - The Former Commander - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","ownerKey":"andersen-the-former-commander","itemKey":"descriptor3.andersen-the-former-commander","contentKey":"descriptor3.andersen-the-former-commander","sourceBackup":"Adversaries 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I carry the weight of terrible sins from my past</p>","notes":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.andersen-the-former-commander","owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I carry the weight of terrible sins from my past","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"Opq0GYINXSnA4CMG","name":"Andersen - The Former Commander - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","ownerKey":"andersen-the-former-commander","itemKey":"descriptor4.andersen-the-former-commander","contentKey":"descriptor4.andersen-the-former-commander","sourceBackup":"Adversaries 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I will do anything to protect my new family</p>","notes":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.andersen-the-former-commander","owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I will do anything to protect my new family","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"D5GypWF75E8RmxAY","name":"Commander","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","ownerKey":"andersen-the-former-commander","itemKey":"don1.andersen-the-former-commander","contentKey":"don1.andersen-the-former-commander","sourceBackup":"Adversaries 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Andersen is skilled at giving orders and managing a battle. **Tactical Orders:** Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen can issue an order to an ally. The ally receives 1 Additional Success when executing that order (+1 to Opposition Level in the case of an NPC). **Coordinated Defense:** Allies fighting alongside Andersen within 30 feet can use his tactical advice to improve their positioning and timing.</p>","notes":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.andersen-the-former-commander","owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"successes":0,"trigger":"","exhausted":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"NaYDtVSthgvr96oV","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","ownerKey":"andersen-the-former-commander","sourceBackup":"Adversaries 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Defend my new family from the danger that Enar represents</p><p>Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her understand that I am now a different man</p><p>Prevent anyone from discovering what I have done</p>","notes":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"ENJk3Hew0YUkJz9E","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","ownerKey":"andersen-the-former-commander","sourceBackup":"Adversaries 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Andersen is a complex antagonist/ally who committed horrible crimes (ordering Enar's execution, raping Satu) but genuinely seeks redemption. He loves Erik deeply and has changed, but his past sins are inescapable. Voice: Commanding but with undertones of regret. If Erik is endangered, Andersen will confess everything to save him. If the Hunters learn the truth, he may become suicidal or attempt to sacrifice himself. Works well with Christian (his most loyal soldier). Has over 20 servants on his estate but only he and Christian are skilled fighters.</p>","notes":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Andersen - The Former Commander","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Adversaries 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"00csnarggransc00","folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","sort":0}
{"_id":"01pgi2ryyr2igp10","name":"Angry Little Girl","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/child-girl-grey.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Angry Little Girl","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/child-girl-grey.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-angry-little-girl","ownerKey":"angry-little-girl","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Angry Little Girl","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>A ten-year-old girl, the sole survivor of a massacre at a ruined castle on a hill. The men and women who once lived within its walls apparently killed each other in the madness brought by the curse. Traumatized and angry, she hides with a knife and will attack anyone who approaches, driven by fear and survival instinct.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find a safe place to stay or a group of people ready to accept and protect me","contact":"<p>A ten-year-old girl, the sole survivor of a massacre at a ruined castle on a hill. The men and women who once lived within its walls apparently killed each other in the madness brought by the curse. Traumatized and angry, she hides with a knife and will attack anyone who approaches, driven by fear and survival instinct.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I survived the adults' madness</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>A ten-year-old girl, the sole survivor of a massacre at a ruined castle on a hill. The men and women who once lived within its walls apparently killed each other in the madness brought by the curse. Traumatized and angry, she hides with a knife and will attack anyone who approaches, driven by fear and survival instinct.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find a safe place to stay or a group of people ready to accept and protect me","contact":"<p>A ten-year-old girl, the sole survivor of a massacre at a ruined castle on a hill. The men and women who once lived within its walls apparently killed each other in the madness brought by the curse. Traumatized and angry, she hides with a knife and will attack anyone who approaches, driven by fear and survival instinct.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I survived the adults' madness</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"005ixr9cc9rxi500","name":"Angry Little Girl - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Angry Little Girl","ownerKey":"angry-little-girl","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Angry Little Girl - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I survived the adults' madness</p>","positive":"I survived the adults' madness"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I survived the adults' madness</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Angry Little Girl","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I survived the adults' madness","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00yvlwqeeqwlvy00","name":"Angry Little Girl - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Angry Little Girl","ownerKey":"angry-little-girl","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Angry Little Girl - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Now I struggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this cruel world</p>","positive":"Now I struggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this cruel world"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Now I struggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this cruel world</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Angry Little Girl","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Now I struggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this cruel world","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00wy4mxbbxm4yw00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Angry Little Girl","ownerKey":"angry-little-girl","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A ten-year-old girl, the sole survivor of a massacre at a ruined castle on a hill. The men and women who once lived within its walls apparently killed each other in the madness brought by the curse. Traumatized and angry, she hides with a knife and will attack anyone who approaches, driven by fear and survival instinct.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I survived the adults' madness<br>2. Now I struggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this cruel world</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find a safe place to stay or a group of people ready to accept and protect me</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A ten-year-old girl, the sole survivor of a massacre at a ruined castle on a hill. The men and women who once lived within its walls apparently killed each other in the madness brought by the curse. Traumatized and angry, she hides with a knife and will attack anyone who approaches, driven by fear and survival instinct.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I survived the adults' madness<br>2. Now I struggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this cruel world</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find a safe place to stay or a group of people ready to accept and protect me</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Angry Little Girl","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00kkla7vv7alkk00","name":"Anne the Little Chatterer","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Anne the Little Chatterer","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-anne-the-little-chatterer","ownerKey":"anne-the-little-chatterer","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Anne the Little Chatterer","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Spy on the townsfolk for Lady Elizaveta in exchange for gifts.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Spy on the townsfolk for Lady Elizaveta in exchange for gifts.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01u97d9119d79u10","name":"Anne the Little Chatterer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anne the Little Chatterer","ownerKey":"anne-the-little-chatterer","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Anne the Little Chatterer - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.</p>","positive":"Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Anne the Little Chatterer","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"019pyknggnkyp910","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anne the Little Chatterer","ownerKey":"anne-the-little-chatterer","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Spy on the townsfolk for Lady Elizaveta in exchange for gifts.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Spy on the townsfolk for Lady Elizaveta in exchange for gifts.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Anne the Little Chatterer","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00g4sgwggwgs4g00","name":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-antonio-ciliegia-gullible-alchemist","ownerKey":"antonio-ciliegia-gullible-alchemist","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>His apprentice Nino is currently tied up in the Secret Laboratory. Antonio's workshop was the original scene of the experiments before they fled to Villa Cilesterino.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to alchemy","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>His apprentice Nino is currently tied up in the Secret Laboratory. Antonio's workshop was the original scene of the experiments before they fled to Villa Cilesterino.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to alchemy","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00p3c40pp04c3p00","name":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","ownerKey":"antonio-ciliegia-gullible-alchemist","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am an old alchemist who has never discovered anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck is never on my side.</p>","positive":"I am an old alchemist who has never discovered anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck is never on my side."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old alchemist who has never discovered anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck is never on my side.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am an old alchemist who has never discovered anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck is never on my side.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01e6depvvped6e10","name":"Unlucky Alchemist","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","ownerKey":"antonio-ciliegia-gullible-alchemist","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Unlucky Alchemist","system":{"description":"<p>Antonio can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides in his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or 6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound due to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the surrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 Wound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets suffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target is knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the ground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 Wound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that quickly solidifies in the air. The target will be paralyzed until the compound is removed. The Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Antonio can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides in his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or 6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound due to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the surrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 Wound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets suffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target is knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the ground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 Wound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that quickly solidifies in the air. The target will be paralyzed until the compound is removed. The Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00uuqk3ss3kquu00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","ownerKey":"antonio-ciliegia-gullible-alchemist","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Known as Mastro 'Cherry' Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. An old alchemist who partnered with Geppetto to discover the secret of eternal life. Works on a magic oak tree and has been kidnapping people in Sinalunga to flay them for their skin. Now hiding in Villa Cilesterino with Azzurra's spirit.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am an old alchemist who has never discovered anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck is never on my side.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to alchemy</p><p>Gifts:<br>Unlucky Alchemist: Antonio can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides in his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or 6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound due to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the surrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 Wound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets suffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target is knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the ground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 Wound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that quickly solidifies in the air. The target will be paralyzed until the compound is removed. The Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p><p>Notes:<br>His apprentice Nino is currently tied up in the Secret Laboratory. Antonio's workshop was the original scene of the experiments before they fled to Villa Cilesterino.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Known as Mastro 'Cherry' Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. An old alchemist who partnered with Geppetto to discover the secret of eternal life. Works on a magic oak tree and has been kidnapping people in Sinalunga to flay them for their skin. Now hiding in Villa Cilesterino with Azzurra's spirit.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am an old alchemist who has never discovered anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck is never on my side.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to alchemy</p><p>Gifts:<br>Unlucky Alchemist: Antonio can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides in his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or 6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound due to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the surrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 Wound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets suffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target is knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the ground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 Wound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that quickly solidifies in the air. The target will be paralyzed until the compound is removed. The Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p><p>Notes:<br>His apprentice Nino is currently tied up in the Secret Laboratory. Antonio's workshop was the original scene of the experiments before they fled to Villa Cilesterino.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00it3vaiiav3ti00","name":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-bull-horned-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/helm-bull-horned-orange.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-arthur-browne-the-big-brother","ownerKey":"arthur-browne-the-big-brother","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Arthur Browne worked for years to make Whitehaven a quiet town where every resident could have a home and a job. When Bardolf Greed bought the town's favor, he seized property and leveled houses to build factories, throwing the three Browne brothers out on the street. Arthur was forced to work in the mines, where a collapse left him trapped by falling rubble and left for dead. The collapse was caused by the awakening of The God Under the Mine. Alive and trapped underground, Arthur found the God's head and after days of agony fed on divine flesh, discovering it confers incredible powers. Consumed with grief and wild hope, his brother Frank dug a tunnel to create communication. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed, leading the Pig Heads gang from beneath the city.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything I built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / Transforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig Heads","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Arthur Browne worked for years to make Whitehaven a quiet town where every resident could have a home and a job. When Bardolf Greed bought the town's favor, he seized property and leveled houses to build factories, throwing the three Browne brothers out on the street. Arthur was forced to work in the mines, where a collapse left him trapped by falling rubble and left for dead. The collapse was caused by the awakening of The God Under the Mine. Alive and trapped underground, Arthur found the God's head and after days of agony fed on divine flesh, discovering it confers incredible powers. Consumed with grief and wild hope, his brother Frank dug a tunnel to create communication. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed, leading the Pig Heads gang from beneath the city.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything I built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / Transforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig Heads","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00god1i44i1dog00","name":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","ownerKey":"arthur-browne-the-big-brother","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as the mastermind of the gang</p>","positive":"I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as the mastermind of the gang"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as the mastermind of the gang</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as the mastermind of the gang","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00dzg540045gzd00","name":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","ownerKey":"arthur-browne-the-big-brother","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Living in my natural prison has taught me how to see even in total darkness</p>","positive":"Living in my natural prison has taught me how to see even in total darkness"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Living in my natural prison has taught me how to see even in total darkness</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Living in my natural prison has taught me how to see even in total darkness","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00gypnk55knpyg00","name":"The Flesh of The God Under the Mine","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","ownerKey":"arthur-browne-the-big-brother","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Flesh of The God Under the Mine","system":{"description":"<p>Arthur can tear pieces of flesh from the God's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Arthur can tear pieces of flesh from the God's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01j27nt55tn72j10","name":"Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","ownerKey":"arthur-browne-the-big-brother","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Gang Leader","system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01i5gjkqqkjg5i10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","ownerKey":"arthur-browne-the-big-brother","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Arthur Browne worked for years to make Whitehaven a quiet town where every resident could have a home and a job. When Bardolf Greed bought the town's favor, he seized property and leveled houses to build factories, throwing the three Browne brothers out on the street. Arthur was forced to work in the mines, where a collapse left him trapped by falling rubble and left for dead. The collapse was caused by the awakening of The God Under the Mine. Alive and trapped underground, Arthur found the God's head and after days of agony fed on divine flesh, discovering it confers incredible powers. Consumed with grief and wild hope, his brother Frank dug a tunnel to create communication. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed, leading the Pig Heads gang from beneath the city.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as the mastermind of the gang<br>2. Living in my natural prison has taught me how to see even in total darkness</p><p>Agenda:<br>Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything I built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / Transforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig Heads</p><p>Gifts:<br>The Flesh of The God Under the Mine: Arthur can tear pieces of flesh from the God's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.<br>Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Arthur Browne worked for years to make Whitehaven a quiet town where every resident could have a home and a job. When Bardolf Greed bought the town's favor, he seized property and leveled houses to build factories, throwing the three Browne brothers out on the street. Arthur was forced to work in the mines, where a collapse left him trapped by falling rubble and left for dead. The collapse was caused by the awakening of The God Under the Mine. Alive and trapped underground, Arthur found the God's head and after days of agony fed on divine flesh, discovering it confers incredible powers. Consumed with grief and wild hope, his brother Frank dug a tunnel to create communication. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed, leading the Pig Heads gang from beneath the city.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as the mastermind of the gang<br>2. Living in my natural prison has taught me how to see even in total darkness</p><p>Agenda:<br>Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything I built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / Transforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig Heads</p><p>Gifts:<br>The Flesh of The God Under the Mine: Arthur can tear pieces of flesh from the God's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.<br>Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00yctabiibatcy00","name":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-noble-grey.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/commoner-noble-grey.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-bardolf-greed-the-wealthy-industrialist","ownerKey":"bardolf-greed-the-wealthy-industrialist","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>A wealthy industrialist in his seventies who made his fortune through shrewd deals and trade. Reaching the ripe old age of seventy without an heir, Bardolf decided to dedicate his life to money. He moved to Whitehaven, an unremarkable town whose only resource was rich mines beneath the city. Within years, he transformed it into an industrial city by trapping all inhabitants into employment with starvation wages. He seized property, leveled houses to build factories and dormitories, and forced the Browne brothers (who cared for the community) out on the street. His greed and exploitation led to a mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine, and now a gang called the Pig Heads wages war against him. His face is plump with thick lupine sideburns, shrewd eyes peek over small round glasses, and he never feels safe despite his personal guards.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Own every business and aspect of trade in Whitehaven, so that the whole city is under my total control","contact":"<p>A wealthy industrialist in his seventies who made his fortune through shrewd deals and trade. Reaching the ripe old age of seventy without an heir, Bardolf decided to dedicate his life to money. He moved to Whitehaven, an unremarkable town whose only resource was rich mines beneath the city. Within years, he transformed it into an industrial city by trapping all inhabitants into employment with starvation wages. He seized property, leveled houses to build factories and dormitories, and forced the Browne brothers (who cared for the community) out on the street. His greed and exploitation led to a mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine, and now a gang called the Pig Heads wages war against him. His face is plump with thick lupine sideburns, shrewd eyes peek over small round glasses, and he never feels safe despite his personal guards.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>A wealthy industrialist in his seventies who made his fortune through shrewd deals and trade. Reaching the ripe old age of seventy without an heir, Bardolf decided to dedicate his life to money. He moved to Whitehaven, an unremarkable town whose only resource was rich mines beneath the city. Within years, he transformed it into an industrial city by trapping all inhabitants into employment with starvation wages. He seized property, leveled houses to build factories and dormitories, and forced the Browne brothers (who cared for the community) out on the street. His greed and exploitation led to a mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine, and now a gang called the Pig Heads wages war against him. His face is plump with thick lupine sideburns, shrewd eyes peek over small round glasses, and he never feels safe despite his personal guards.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Own every business and aspect of trade in Whitehaven, so that the whole city is under my total control","contact":"<p>A wealthy industrialist in his seventies who made his fortune through shrewd deals and trade. Reaching the ripe old age of seventy without an heir, Bardolf decided to dedicate his life to money. He moved to Whitehaven, an unremarkable town whose only resource was rich mines beneath the city. Within years, he transformed it into an industrial city by trapping all inhabitants into employment with starvation wages. He seized property, leveled houses to build factories and dormitories, and forced the Browne brothers (who cared for the community) out on the street. His greed and exploitation led to a mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine, and now a gang called the Pig Heads wages war against him. His face is plump with thick lupine sideburns, shrewd eyes peek over small round glasses, and he never feels safe despite his personal guards.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01st6x4jj4x6ts10","name":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","ownerKey":"bardolf-greed-the-wealthy-industrialist","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me</p>","positive":"I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01py5leppel5yp10","name":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","ownerKey":"bardolf-greed-the-wealthy-industrialist","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>My body is old, but my mind remains infallible</p>","positive":"My body is old, but my mind remains infallible"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>My body is old, but my mind remains infallible</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My body is old, but my mind remains infallible","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00pks4kmmk4skp00","name":"Smell the Deal","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","ownerKey":"bardolf-greed-the-wealthy-industrialist","itemKey":"don1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Smell the Deal","system":{"description":"<p>Bardolf is a master of negotiation and reading others. After talking to a subject, Bardolf can obtain one of the following pieces of information: 1. Discover a secret regarding the person he is speaking with; 2. Obtain an object or piece of information valuable to the other party in the negotiation, and which he can use as leverage. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to prevent Bardolf from using this Gift on them.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Bardolf is a master of negotiation and reading others. After talking to a subject, Bardolf can obtain one of the following pieces of information: 1. Discover a secret regarding the person he is speaking with; 2. Obtain an object or piece of information valuable to the other party in the negotiation, and which he can use as leverage. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to prevent Bardolf from using this Gift on them.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.aldeano","owner":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","category":"Villager Gift","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00s4o9affa9o4s00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","ownerKey":"bardolf-greed-the-wealthy-industrialist","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A wealthy industrialist in his seventies who made his fortune through shrewd deals and trade. Reaching the ripe old age of seventy without an heir, Bardolf decided to dedicate his life to money. He moved to Whitehaven, an unremarkable town whose only resource was rich mines beneath the city. Within years, he transformed it into an industrial city by trapping all inhabitants into employment with starvation wages. He seized property, leveled houses to build factories and dormitories, and forced the Browne brothers (who cared for the community) out on the street. His greed and exploitation led to a mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine, and now a gang called the Pig Heads wages war against him. His face is plump with thick lupine sideburns, shrewd eyes peek over small round glasses, and he never feels safe despite his personal guards.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me<br>2. My body is old, but my mind remains infallible</p><p>Agenda:<br>Own every business and aspect of trade in Whitehaven, so that the whole city is under my total control</p><p>Gifts:<br>Smell the Deal: Bardolf is a master of negotiation and reading others. After talking to a subject, Bardolf can obtain one of the following pieces of information: 1. Discover a secret regarding the person he is speaking with; 2. Obtain an object or piece of information valuable to the other party in the negotiation, and which he can use as leverage. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to prevent Bardolf from using this Gift on them.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A wealthy industrialist in his seventies who made his fortune through shrewd deals and trade. Reaching the ripe old age of seventy without an heir, Bardolf decided to dedicate his life to money. He moved to Whitehaven, an unremarkable town whose only resource was rich mines beneath the city. Within years, he transformed it into an industrial city by trapping all inhabitants into employment with starvation wages. He seized property, leveled houses to build factories and dormitories, and forced the Browne brothers (who cared for the community) out on the street. His greed and exploitation led to a mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine, and now a gang called the Pig Heads wages war against him. His face is plump with thick lupine sideburns, shrewd eyes peek over small round glasses, and he never feels safe despite his personal guards.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me<br>2. My body is old, but my mind remains infallible</p><p>Agenda:<br>Own every business and aspect of trade in Whitehaven, so that the whole city is under my total control</p><p>Gifts:<br>Smell the Deal: Bardolf is a master of negotiation and reading others. After talking to a subject, Bardolf can obtain one of the following pieces of information: 1. Discover a secret regarding the person he is speaking with; 2. Obtain an object or piece of information valuable to the other party in the negotiation, and which he can use as leverage. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to prevent Bardolf from using this Gift on them.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01poiocppcoiop10","name":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-black-wolves-of-greskars-pack","ownerKey":"black-wolves-of-greskars-pack","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":""},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Follow without hesitation every order from the pack’s alpha.","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Follow without hesitation every order from the pack’s alpha.","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01nnd4d66d4dnn10","name":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","ownerKey":"black-wolves-of-greskars-pack","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are fierce black wolves, we hate humans and obey only our pack leader.</p>","positive":"We are fierce black wolves, we hate humans and obey only our pack leader."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are fierce black wolves, we hate humans and obey only our pack leader.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are fierce black wolves, we hate humans and obey only our pack leader.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"013ec58mm85ce310","name":"The Power of the Pack","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","ownerKey":"black-wolves-of-greskars-pack","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Power of the Pack","system":{"description":"<p>Any action taken while being engaged by two or more Wolves receives 1 Penalty.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Any action taken while being engaged by two or more Wolves receives 1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00ue989vv989eu00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","ownerKey":"black-wolves-of-greskars-pack","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are fierce black wolves, we hate humans and obey only our pack leader.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Follow without hesitation every order from the pack’s alpha.</p><p>Gifts:<br>The Power of the Pack: Any action taken while being engaged by two or more Wolves receives 1 Penalty.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are fierce black wolves, we hate humans and obey only our pack leader.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Follow without hesitation every order from the pack’s alpha.</p><p>Gifts:<br>The Power of the Pack: Any action taken while being engaged by two or more Wolves receives 1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Black Wolves of Greskar's Pack","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00n5er3gg3re5n00","name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/dog-hunting-褐色-tan.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/mammals/dog-hunting-褐色-tan.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-canine-tigers-deceptive-guardians","ownerKey":"canine-tigers-deceptive-guardians","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":"<p>Canine Tigers are excellent tactical complications. Place them in combat zones where they might get caught in crossfire. When unwounded, they're OL 3 and friendly-seeming. Once wounded, they become OL 7 berserkers. Henkle uses them strategically—he knows they'll transform and create chaos. Smart Hunters might avoid wounding them or use them tactically by deliberately wounding one near enemies. A wounded Canine Tiger attacking a wish-warped villager might even break the wish's hold temporarily.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Fácil 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":"<p>Canine Tigers are excellent tactical complications. Place them in combat zones where they might get caught in crossfire. When unwounded, they're OL 3 and friendly-seeming. Once wounded, they become OL 7 berserkers. Henkle uses them strategically—he knows they'll transform and create chaos. Smart Hunters might avoid wounding them or use them tactically by deliberately wounding one near enemies. A wounded Canine Tiger attacking a wish-warped villager might even break the wish's hold temporarily.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"items":[{"_id":"00psvgjbbjgvsp00","name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","ownerKey":"canine-tigers-deceptive-guardians","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We appear as large friendly dogs</p>","positive":"We appear as large friendly dogs"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We appear as large friendly dogs</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We appear as large friendly dogs","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0117l953359l7110","name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","ownerKey":"canine-tigers-deceptive-guardians","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>But we were created by the wishing well to be guardians</p>","positive":"But we were created by the wishing well to be guardians"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>But we were created by the wishing well to be guardians</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"But we were created by the wishing well to be guardians","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01tmjosjjsojmt10","name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","ownerKey":"canine-tigers-deceptive-guardians","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>We are docile until wounded</p>","positive":"We are docile until wounded"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are docile until wounded</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are docile until wounded","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00wa03vvvv30aw00","name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","ownerKey":"canine-tigers-deceptive-guardians","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>Then we become fierce as tigers</p>","positive":"Then we become fierce as tigers"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Then we become fierce as tigers</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Then we become fierce as tigers","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"017mfjorrojfm710","name":"Fierce as Tiger","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","ownerKey":"canine-tigers-deceptive-guardians","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Fierce as Tiger","system":{"description":"<p>Canine Tigers appear docile and even friendly at first. But when a Canine Tiger suffers its first Wound: **Transformation:** Its Opposition Level immediately increases from 3 to 7. **Berserker Rage:** It enters a rage and attacks the nearest living thing (ally or enemy) without discrimination. **Unstoppable:** It cannot be reasoned with, calmed, or controlled in any way. **Relentless:** It fights until destroyed or until all nearby creatures flee beyond its reach. Storytellers should use Canine Tigers as complications—they may seem harmless until someone accidentally wounds one during another combat.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Canine Tigers appear docile and even friendly at first. But when a Canine Tiger suffers its first Wound: **Transformation:** Its Opposition Level immediately increases from 3 to 7. **Berserker Rage:** It enters a rage and attacks the nearest living thing (ally or enemy) without discrimination. **Unstoppable:** It cannot be reasoned with, calmed, or controlled in any way. **Relentless:** It fights until destroyed or until all nearby creatures flee beyond its reach. Storytellers should use Canine Tigers as complications—they may seem harmless until someone accidentally wounds one during another combat.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00kbtvz88zvtbk00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","ownerKey":"canine-tigers-deceptive-guardians","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. We appear as large friendly dogs<br>2. But we were created by the wishing well to be guardians<br>3. We are docile until wounded<br>4. Then we become fierce as tigers</p><p>Gifts:<br>Fierce as Tiger: Canine Tigers appear docile and even friendly at first. But when a Canine Tiger suffers its first Wound: **Transformation:** Its Opposition Level immediately increases from 3 to 7. **Berserker Rage:** It enters a rage and attacks the nearest living thing (ally or enemy) without discrimination. **Unstoppable:** It cannot be reasoned with, calmed, or controlled in any way. **Relentless:** It fights until destroyed or until all nearby creatures flee beyond its reach. Storytellers should use Canine Tigers as complications—they may seem harmless until someone accidentally wounds one during another combat.</p><p>Notes:<br>Canine Tigers are excellent tactical complications. Place them in combat zones where they might get caught in crossfire. When unwounded, they're OL 3 and friendly-seeming. Once wounded, they become OL 7 berserkers. Henkle uses them strategically—he knows they'll transform and create chaos. Smart Hunters might avoid wounding them or use them tactically by deliberately wounding one near enemies. A wounded Canine Tiger attacking a wish-warped villager might even break the wish's hold temporarily.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. We appear as large friendly dogs<br>2. But we were created by the wishing well to be guardians<br>3. We are docile until wounded<br>4. Then we become fierce as tigers</p><p>Gifts:<br>Fierce as Tiger: Canine Tigers appear docile and even friendly at first. But when a Canine Tiger suffers its first Wound: **Transformation:** Its Opposition Level immediately increases from 3 to 7. **Berserker Rage:** It enters a rage and attacks the nearest living thing (ally or enemy) without discrimination. **Unstoppable:** It cannot be reasoned with, calmed, or controlled in any way. **Relentless:** It fights until destroyed or until all nearby creatures flee beyond its reach. Storytellers should use Canine Tigers as complications—they may seem harmless until someone accidentally wounds one during another combat.</p><p>Notes:<br>Canine Tigers are excellent tactical complications. Place them in combat zones where they might get caught in crossfire. When unwounded, they're OL 3 and friendly-seeming. Once wounded, they become OL 7 berserkers. Henkle uses them strategically—he knows they'll transform and create chaos. Smart Hunters might avoid wounding them or use them tactically by deliberately wounding one near enemies. A wounded Canine Tiger attacking a wish-warped villager might even break the wish's hold temporarily.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Canine Tigers - Deceptive Guardians","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00e8iqo22oqi8e00","name":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-carlo-the-living-puppet","ownerKey":"carlo-the-living-puppet","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Carlo unwittingly created the horror in Sinalunga but is not evil - he's terrified of being caught by Geppetto and Antonio. Can be redeemed if Hunters gain his trust. Azzurra's spirit wants to use his fairy magic to return to life.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Living a carefree life without responsibility\nI don't want to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but I'm always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Carlo unwittingly created the horror in Sinalunga but is not evil - he's terrified of being caught by Geppetto and Antonio. Can be redeemed if Hunters gain his trust. Azzurra's spirit wants to use his fairy magic to return to life.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Living a carefree life without responsibility\nI don't want to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but I'm always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"008ickqrrqkci800","name":"Carlo - The Living Puppet - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","ownerKey":"carlo-the-living-puppet","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Carlo - The Living Puppet - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The lies I tell become reality for a short time.</p>","positive":"I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The lies I tell become reality for a short time."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The lies I tell become reality for a short time.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The lies I tell become reality for a short time.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00rb9vrrrrv9br00","name":"Lies","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","ownerKey":"carlo-the-living-puppet","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lies","system":{"description":"<p>Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life by creating a Descriptor that allows him to perform incredible feats. All lies must be centered on him. For example: I can walk through walls or I am invisible to the human eye. The effects of the lies' power are literal. For this reason, Carlo would not be able to go through a closed door and he would be seen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 Scene or until a new lie is told.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life by creating a Descriptor that allows him to perform incredible feats. All lies must be centered on him. For example: I can walk through walls or I am invisible to the human eye. The effects of the lies' power are literal. For this reason, Carlo would not be able to go through a closed door and he would be seen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 Scene or until a new lie is told.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00f8p1u22u1p8f00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","ownerKey":"carlo-the-living-puppet","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A wooden puppet animated by fairy magic from an enchanted oak tree. By nature, Carlo cannot speak even a single word of truth. His lies convinced Geppetto and Antonio that they needed to flay people alive for their experiments. Horrified by what he caused, Carlo escaped to Sinalunga where he disguises himself as a real child every morning using his powers. Attends school and has befriended Lucino. Wears old elegant shoes given to him by Geppetto. Currently hiding at Villa Balocchi, paying the innkeeper with stones temporarily transformed into gold coins.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The lies I tell become reality for a short time.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Living a carefree life without responsibility<br>I don't want to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but I'm always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me</p><p>Gifts:<br>Lies: Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life by creating a Descriptor that allows him to perform incredible feats. All lies must be centered on him. For example: I can walk through walls or I am invisible to the human eye. The effects of the lies' power are literal. For this reason, Carlo would not be able to go through a closed door and he would be seen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 Scene or until a new lie is told.</p><p>Notes:<br>Carlo unwittingly created the horror in Sinalunga but is not evil - he's terrified of being caught by Geppetto and Antonio. Can be redeemed if Hunters gain his trust. Azzurra's spirit wants to use his fairy magic to return to life.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A wooden puppet animated by fairy magic from an enchanted oak tree. By nature, Carlo cannot speak even a single word of truth. His lies convinced Geppetto and Antonio that they needed to flay people alive for their experiments. Horrified by what he caused, Carlo escaped to Sinalunga where he disguises himself as a real child every morning using his powers. Attends school and has befriended Lucino. Wears old elegant shoes given to him by Geppetto. Currently hiding at Villa Balocchi, paying the innkeeper with stones temporarily transformed into gold coins.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The lies I tell become reality for a short time.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Living a carefree life without responsibility<br>I don't want to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but I'm always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me</p><p>Gifts:<br>Lies: Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life by creating a Descriptor that allows him to perform incredible feats. All lies must be centered on him. For example: I can walk through walls or I am invisible to the human eye. The effects of the lies' power are literal. For this reason, Carlo would not be able to go through a closed door and he would be seen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 Scene or until a new lie is told.</p><p>Notes:<br>Carlo unwittingly created the horror in Sinalunga but is not evil - he's terrified of being caught by Geppetto and Antonio. Can be redeemed if Hunters gain his trust. Azzurra's spirit wants to use his fairy magic to return to life.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"0188lhr99rhl8810","name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/invertebrates/worm-slug-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/invertebrates/worm-slug-green.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-caterpillar-of-the-wonderful-lands","ownerKey":"caterpillar-of-the-wonderful-lands","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":"<p>These horrifying creatures inhabit the Caterpillars' Greenhouse, one of the three Cure Rooms in Wonder. Massive carnivorous caterpillars over two meters long, they hunt patients who wander into their domain, feeding on fresh meat and using corpses to lay their eggs. The dense yellow fog and alien plants of the greenhouse provide perfect cover for their hunting.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":"<p>These horrifying creatures inhabit the Caterpillars' Greenhouse, one of the three Cure Rooms in Wonder. Massive carnivorous caterpillars over two meters long, they hunt patients who wander into their domain, feeding on fresh meat and using corpses to lay their eggs. The dense yellow fog and alien plants of the greenhouse provide perfect cover for their hunting.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01sxmyjzzjymxs10","name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","ownerKey":"caterpillar-of-the-wonderful-lands","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two meters long</p>","positive":"I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two meters long"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two meters long</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two meters long","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01j3s61hh16s3j10","name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","ownerKey":"caterpillar-of-the-wonderful-lands","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the carcasses of creatures I've devoured</p>","positive":"I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the carcasses of creatures I've devoured"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the carcasses of creatures I've devoured</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the carcasses of creatures I've devoured","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00af6vm66mv6fa00","name":"Hunter Caterpillar","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","ownerKey":"caterpillar-of-the-wonderful-lands","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hunter Caterpillar","system":{"description":"<p>When a Caterpillar moves, any human-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. Whoever is in the Caterpillar's way must perform a Defense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The Caterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people prone on the ground.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>When a Caterpillar moves, any human-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. Whoever is in the Caterpillar's way must perform a Defense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The Caterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people prone on the ground.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01d725bttb527d10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","ownerKey":"caterpillar-of-the-wonderful-lands","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>These horrifying creatures inhabit the Caterpillars' Greenhouse, one of the three Cure Rooms in Wonder. Massive carnivorous caterpillars over two meters long, they hunt patients who wander into their domain, feeding on fresh meat and using corpses to lay their eggs. The dense yellow fog and alien plants of the greenhouse provide perfect cover for their hunting.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two meters long<br>2. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the carcasses of creatures I've devoured</p><p>Gifts:<br>Hunter Caterpillar: When a Caterpillar moves, any human-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. Whoever is in the Caterpillar's way must perform a Defense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The Caterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people prone on the ground.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>These horrifying creatures inhabit the Caterpillars' Greenhouse, one of the three Cure Rooms in Wonder. Massive carnivorous caterpillars over two meters long, they hunt patients who wander into their domain, feeding on fresh meat and using corpses to lay their eggs. The dense yellow fog and alien plants of the greenhouse provide perfect cover for their hunting.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two meters long<br>2. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the carcasses of creatures I've devoured</p><p>Gifts:<br>Hunter Caterpillar: When a Caterpillar moves, any human-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. Whoever is in the Caterpillar's way must perform a Defense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The Caterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people prone on the ground.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00q6nvvttvvn6q00","name":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/cat-hunched-glowing-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/mammals/cat-hunched-glowing-red.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-cheshire-the-faithful-lynx","ownerKey":"cheshire-the-faithful-lynx","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura principal","notes":"<p>Alice Liddell controls this large, trained lynx through her power. By moving through the narrow conduits of the asylum, Cheshire acts as the eyes of her mistress, watching over Wonder and reporting any disturbances.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main Creature","notes":"<p>Alice Liddell controls this large, trained lynx through her power. By moving through the narrow conduits of the asylum, Cheshire acts as the eyes of her mistress, watching over Wonder and reporting any disturbances.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00j2mut99tum2j00","name":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","ownerKey":"cheshire-the-faithful-lynx","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a snappy and aggressive lynx</p>","positive":"I am a snappy and aggressive lynx"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a snappy and aggressive lynx</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a snappy and aggressive lynx","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ta4jqvvqj4at00","name":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","ownerKey":"cheshire-the-faithful-lynx","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I roam the halls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress</p>","positive":"I roam the halls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I roam the halls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I roam the halls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"019qftgssgtfq910","name":"Elusive","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","ownerKey":"cheshire-the-faithful-lynx","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Elusive","system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, Cheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, and move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always move without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to attack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the constant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This Gift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, Cheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, and move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always move without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to attack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the constant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This Gift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00rb80v11v08br00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","ownerKey":"cheshire-the-faithful-lynx","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Alice Liddell controls this large, trained lynx through her power. By moving through the narrow conduits of the asylum, Cheshire acts as the eyes of her mistress, watching over Wonder and reporting any disturbances.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a snappy and aggressive lynx<br>2. I roam the halls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress</p><p>Gifts:<br>Elusive: Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, Cheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, and move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always move without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to attack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the constant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This Gift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Alice Liddell controls this large, trained lynx through her power. By moving through the narrow conduits of the asylum, Cheshire acts as the eyes of her mistress, watching over Wonder and reporting any disturbances.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a snappy and aggressive lynx<br>2. I roam the halls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress</p><p>Gifts:<br>Elusive: Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, Cheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, and move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always move without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to attack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the constant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This Gift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Cheshire - The Faithful Lynx","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"006mzqw88wqzm600","name":"Christian the Relentless","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Christian the Relentless","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-christian-the-relentless","ownerKey":"christian-the-relentless","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Christian the Relentless","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Gift: Immune to behavior effects when carrying out orders, +1 OL when eliminating obstacles</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Help Andersen, eliminate Enar","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Former soldier, cold determination</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Gift: Immune to behavior effects when carrying out orders, +1 OL when eliminating obstacles</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Help Andersen, eliminate Enar","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Former soldier, cold determination</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01xuil3uu3liux10","name":"Christian the Relentless - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Christian the Relentless","ownerKey":"christian-the-relentless","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Christian the Relentless - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>Former soldier, cold determination</p>","positive":"Former soldier, cold determination"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Former soldier, cold determination</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Christian the Relentless","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Former soldier, cold determination","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01q3ygxhhxgy3q10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Christian the Relentless","ownerKey":"christian-the-relentless","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. Former soldier, cold determination</p><p>Agenda:<br>Help Andersen, eliminate Enar</p><p>Notes:<br>Gift: Immune to behavior effects when carrying out orders, +1 OL when eliminating obstacles</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. Former soldier, cold determination</p><p>Agenda:<br>Help Andersen, eliminate Enar</p><p>Notes:<br>Gift: Immune to behavior effects when carrying out orders, +1 OL when eliminating obstacles</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Christian the Relentless","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01x6b6dyyd6b6x10","name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-scream-tan.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-scream-tan.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-clarence-browne-the-younger-brother","ownerKey":"clarence-browne-the-younger-brother","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>The youngest of the three Browne brothers. When Bardolf Greed threw them out on the street and forced them to accept jobs as miners or starve, Clarence soon quit, choosing the life of a slacker over labor in the mines. After the mine collapse that injured Frank and trapped Arthur, Clarence became part of the Pig Heads revolution but maintains his lazy lifestyle. He lives in a rickety rundown house with a thatched roof in the abandoned apple orchard that the Browne family once gifted to the city. Clarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take them off guard. When the mutation from eating the God's flesh begins to take effect on miners, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. He has a special relationship with Emma, his childhood friend, who he has always promised to take away from Whitehaven, though she knows he will never abandon his brothers. From hanging around the city, Clarence knows Whitehaven like the back of his hand.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on the Pig Head's cause in my spare time","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>The youngest of the three Browne brothers. When Bardolf Greed threw them out on the street and forced them to accept jobs as miners or starve, Clarence soon quit, choosing the life of a slacker over labor in the mines. After the mine collapse that injured Frank and trapped Arthur, Clarence became part of the Pig Heads revolution but maintains his lazy lifestyle. He lives in a rickety rundown house with a thatched roof in the abandoned apple orchard that the Browne family once gifted to the city. Clarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take them off guard. When the mutation from eating the God's flesh begins to take effect on miners, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. He has a special relationship with Emma, his childhood friend, who he has always promised to take away from Whitehaven, though she knows he will never abandon his brothers. From hanging around the city, Clarence knows Whitehaven like the back of his hand.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on the Pig Head's cause in my spare time","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01l9selooles9l10","name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","ownerKey":"clarence-browne-the-younger-brother","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am the youngest of the Pig Heads</p>","positive":"I am the youngest of the Pig Heads"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the youngest of the Pig Heads</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am the youngest of the Pig Heads","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01vpdmmoommdpv10","name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","ownerKey":"clarence-browne-the-younger-brother","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Despite believing in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on it</p>","positive":"Despite believing in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on it"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Despite believing in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on it</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Despite believing in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on it","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"000ft4jssj4tf000","name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","ownerKey":"clarence-browne-the-younger-brother","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back of my hand</p>","positive":"From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back of my hand"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back of my hand</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back of my hand","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00o0b50bb05b0o00","name":"Slacker","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","ownerKey":"clarence-browne-the-younger-brother","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Slacker","system":{"description":"<p>Clarence is a master of the art of disappearing when things get tough. In the presence of even a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it is his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able to stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the orchard, passing the entire following Scene there.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Clarence is a master of the art of disappearing when things get tough. In the presence of even a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it is his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able to stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the orchard, passing the entire following Scene there.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00qk260dd062kq00","name":"Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","ownerKey":"clarence-browne-the-younger-brother","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Gang Leader","system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00fpc0c66c0cpf00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","ownerKey":"clarence-browne-the-younger-brother","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>The youngest of the three Browne brothers. When Bardolf Greed threw them out on the street and forced them to accept jobs as miners or starve, Clarence soon quit, choosing the life of a slacker over labor in the mines. After the mine collapse that injured Frank and trapped Arthur, Clarence became part of the Pig Heads revolution but maintains his lazy lifestyle. He lives in a rickety rundown house with a thatched roof in the abandoned apple orchard that the Browne family once gifted to the city. Clarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take them off guard. When the mutation from eating the God's flesh begins to take effect on miners, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. He has a special relationship with Emma, his childhood friend, who he has always promised to take away from Whitehaven, though she knows he will never abandon his brothers. From hanging around the city, Clarence knows Whitehaven like the back of his hand.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the youngest of the Pig Heads<br>2. Despite believing in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on it<br>3. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back of my hand</p><p>Agenda:<br>Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on the Pig Head's cause in my spare time</p><p>Gifts:<br>Slacker: Clarence is a master of the art of disappearing when things get tough. In the presence of even a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it is his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able to stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the orchard, passing the entire following Scene there.<br>Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The youngest of the three Browne brothers. When Bardolf Greed threw them out on the street and forced them to accept jobs as miners or starve, Clarence soon quit, choosing the life of a slacker over labor in the mines. After the mine collapse that injured Frank and trapped Arthur, Clarence became part of the Pig Heads revolution but maintains his lazy lifestyle. He lives in a rickety rundown house with a thatched roof in the abandoned apple orchard that the Browne family once gifted to the city. Clarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take them off guard. When the mutation from eating the God's flesh begins to take effect on miners, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. He has a special relationship with Emma, his childhood friend, who he has always promised to take away from Whitehaven, though she knows he will never abandon his brothers. From hanging around the city, Clarence knows Whitehaven like the back of his hand.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the youngest of the Pig Heads<br>2. Despite believing in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on it<br>3. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back of my hand</p><p>Agenda:<br>Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on the Pig Head's cause in my spare time</p><p>Gifts:<br>Slacker: Clarence is a master of the art of disappearing when things get tough. In the presence of even a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it is his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able to stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the orchard, passing the entire following Scene there.<br>Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00h162occo261h00","name":"Corinne the Housekeeper","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Corinne the Housekeeper","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-corinne-the-housekeeper","ownerKey":"corinne-the-housekeeper","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Corinne the Housekeeper","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Spread rumors and collect gossip, especially when she’s given something in return.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I know all rumors in the village, partly because I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love receiving gifts.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Spread rumors and collect gossip, especially when she’s given something in return.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I know all rumors in the village, partly because I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love receiving gifts.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01pubh3663hbup10","name":"Corinne the Housekeeper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Corinne the Housekeeper","ownerKey":"corinne-the-housekeeper","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Corinne the Housekeeper - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I know all rumors in the village, partly because I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love receiving gifts.</p>","positive":"I know all rumors in the village, partly because I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love receiving gifts."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I know all rumors in the village, partly because I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love receiving gifts.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Corinne the Housekeeper","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I know all rumors in the village, partly because I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love receiving gifts.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"013fts6pp6stf310","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Corinne the Housekeeper","ownerKey":"corinne-the-housekeeper","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I know all rumors in the village, partly because I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love receiving gifts.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Spread rumors and collect gossip, especially when she’s given something in return.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I know all rumors in the village, partly because I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love receiving gifts.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Spread rumors and collect gossip, especially when she’s given something in return.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Corinne the Housekeeper","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"name":"Dead Pirates","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/death/skull-horned-worn-white-blue.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Dead Pirates","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/magic/death/skull-horned-worn-white-blue.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-dead-pirates","ownerKey":"dead-pirates","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dead Pirates","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Gift: Walking Dead (act after final wound), Hook's crew from shipwreck</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Revenge on living","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Lost souls seeking revenge, swollen rotten flesh</p>"}}}},"legacyNames":["Dead Pirates - Hook's Crew","Dead Pirates"]}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"Creature","notes":"<p>A dozen pirates died in the caves beneath the cliff after their ship was wrecked on the rocks. Their souls, unable to find peace, now haunt the tunnel network leading to the Sea Fairy's central pool. These walking corpses are heaps of swollen, rotten flesh that move slowly but relentlessly. They recognize James the Swordsman if he is present—he killed their captain in a duel, which led to their ship's destruction—and will prioritize tasting his flesh first. The Dead Pirates are driven purely by hatred for the living and hunger for vengeance. They shamble through the dark tunnels, their putrescent bodies dripping seawater and decay. Even when dismembered, their body parts continue to move and attack. They are a dangerous obstacle for anyone seeking the Sea Fairy, and their numbers (about a dozen) make them a significant threat despite their individual weakness.</p>"},"background":"<p>A dozen pirates died in the caves beneath the cliff after their ship was wrecked on the rocks. Their souls, unable to find peace, now haunt the tunnel network leading to the Sea Fairy's central pool. These walking corpses are heaps of swollen, rotten flesh that move slowly but relentlessly. They recognize James the Swordsman if he is present—he killed their captain in a duel, which led to their ship's destruction—and will prioritize tasting his flesh first. The Dead Pirates are driven purely by hatred for the living and hunger for vengeance. They shamble through the dark tunnels, their putrescent bodies dripping seawater and decay. Even when dismembered, their body parts continue to move and attack. They are a dangerous obstacle for anyone seeking the Sea Fairy, and their numbers (about a dozen) make them a significant threat despite their individual weakness.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"easy","impulse":"Taste the flesh of the living to satisfy our eternal hunger","oppositionLevel":3},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Taste the flesh of the living to satisfy our eternal hunger\nTake revenge on James the Swordsman for killing our captain and causing our deaths\nPrevent anyone from reaching the Sea Fairy's sanctuary","contact":"<p>A dozen pirates died in the caves beneath the cliff after their ship was wrecked on the rocks. Their souls, unable to find peace, now haunt the tunnel network leading to the Sea Fairy's central pool. These walking corpses are heaps of swollen, rotten flesh that move slowly but relentlessly. They recognize James the Swordsman if he is present—he killed their captain in a duel, which led to their ship's destruction—and will prioritize tasting his flesh first. The Dead Pirates are driven purely by hatred for the living and hunger for vengeance. They shamble through the dark tunnels, their putrescent bodies dripping seawater and decay. Even when dismembered, their body parts continue to move and attack. They are a dangerous obstacle for anyone seeking the Sea Fairy, and their numbers (about a dozen) make them a significant threat despite their individual weakness.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a lost soul who only wishes for revenge on those who are still alive</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"WgftZ1RgoYTopEFh","name":"Dead Pirates - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","ownerKey":"dead-pirates","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.dead-pirates","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.dead-pirates","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a lost soul who only wishes for revenge on those who are still alive</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.dead-pirates","owner":"Dead Pirates","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a lost soul who only wishes for revenge on those who are still alive","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"oT4vuDcJhoUp0asJ","name":"Dead Pirates - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","ownerKey":"dead-pirates","itemKey":"descriptor2.dead-pirates","contentKey":"descriptor2.dead-pirates","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>My body is a heap of swollen and rotten flesh that moves slowly</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.dead-pirates","owner":"Dead Pirates","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My body is a heap of swollen and rotten flesh that moves slowly","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"69sTOHLkcVf8suYt","name":"Dead Pirates - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","ownerKey":"dead-pirates","itemKey":"descriptor3.dead-pirates","contentKey":"descriptor3.dead-pirates","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am part of Hook's crew, doomed to haunt these caves forever</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.dead-pirates","owner":"Dead Pirates","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am part of Hook's crew, doomed to haunt these caves forever","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"7mGnQaTBvV1Xy3Bz","name":"Dead Pirates - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","ownerKey":"dead-pirates","itemKey":"descriptor4.dead-pirates","contentKey":"descriptor4.dead-pirates","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Even dismembered, my body parts continue to attack</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.dead-pirates","owner":"Dead Pirates","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Even dismembered, my body parts continue to attack","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"3uE2oaY4mzBBT9MG","name":"Walking Dead","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","ownerKey":"dead-pirates","itemKey":"don1.dead-pirates","contentKey":"don1.dead-pirates","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Dead Pirate's body is rotten and putrescent, but it does not stop even if dismembered. **Final Action:** After suffering his only Wound, a Dead Pirate can still take his action before being eliminated, if he has not already acted in the current Exchange. This allows for a final desperate attack or grab. **Pack Tactics:** If a Dead Pirate acts against an outnumbered enemy (more pirates than defenders in melee range), his Opposition Level is increased by +1. **Relentless Advance:** Dead Pirates ignore fear, pain, and morale effects. They never retreat or surrender. **Slow Movement:** Dead Pirates move at half speed but can attack normally once in range.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.dead-pirates","owner":"Dead Pirates","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"successes":0,"trigger":"","exhausted":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"MCvLeqZYmQJA6yZ7","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","ownerKey":"dead-pirates","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Taste the flesh of the living to satisfy our eternal hunger</p><p>Take revenge on James the Swordsman for killing our captain and causing our deaths</p><p>Prevent anyone from reaching the Sea Fairy's sanctuary</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Dead Pirates","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"lYR42MXajI1z3P2i","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dead Pirates","ownerKey":"dead-pirates","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Encounter occurs on a 5-6 when rolling for Cliff threats. Approximately 12 Dead Pirates in total—use multiple in combat. Voice: Gurgling moans, water-logged groans. Special interaction: If James the Swordsman is present, they focus on him first, shouting 'You killed our captain! It's your fault we wrecked!' through rotted mouths. Slow but dangerous in numbers. Tunnels are narrow, which works to their advantage (limits how many Hunters can fight at once). Bodies drip seawater and smell of rot and brine. Dismembered limbs continue to crawl and attack. Can grab and pull victims underwater in flooded tunnel sections. No strategy beyond mindless revenge.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Dead Pirates","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"01bx08z00z80xb10","folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","sort":0}
{"_id":"00olemc22cmelo00","name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-didier-the-grumpy-old-man","ownerKey":"didier-the-grumpy-old-man","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Criticize the current leadership and stir up resentment in the village.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who even married a foreigner!</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Criticize the current leadership and stir up resentment in the village.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who even married a foreigner!</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"000szm2qq2mzs000","name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","ownerKey":"didier-the-grumpy-old-man","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who even married a foreigner!</p>","positive":"I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who even married a foreigner!"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who even married a foreigner!</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who even married a foreigner!","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"002wrvtnntvrw200","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","ownerKey":"didier-the-grumpy-old-man","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who even married a foreigner!</p><p>Agenda:<br>Criticize the current leadership and stir up resentment in the village.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who even married a foreigner!</p><p>Agenda:<br>Criticize the current leadership and stir up resentment in the village.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00sj9bp44pb9js00","name":"Dose - The Tin Man","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Dose - The Tin Man","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-dose-the-tin-man","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose - The Tin Man","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Muffled and echoing through his helmet<br>- Mannerisms: Stiff, mechanical movements; constantly adjusts his armor<br>- Pathos: Desperately wants to feel something, anything</p><p>WEAKNESS: The small door over his heart is his only vulnerability. Targeting it requires skill (1 Increment from Outcome) but negates his armor immunity for the rest of the Scene.</p><p>KEY MOMENT: If the Hunters show Dose compassion, he's deeply moved and may refuse to fight them later. His humanity is the key to his redemption.</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he falls in love and his heart returns—metaphorically regaining his lost humanity.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Protect my companions\nFind a cure so I can feel again\nPrevent myself from becoming a monster","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Muffled and echoing through his helmet<br>- Mannerisms: Stiff, mechanical movements; constantly adjusts his armor<br>- Pathos: Desperately wants to feel something, anything</p><p>WEAKNESS: The small door over his heart is his only vulnerability. Targeting it requires skill (1 Increment from Outcome) but negates his armor immunity for the rest of the Scene.</p><p>KEY MOMENT: If the Hunters show Dose compassion, he's deeply moved and may refuse to fight them later. His humanity is the key to his redemption.</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he falls in love and his heart returns—metaphorically regaining his lost humanity.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect my companions\nFind a cure so I can feel again\nPrevent myself from becoming a monster","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00jw5ufppfu5wj00","name":"Dose - The Tin Man - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose - The Tin Man - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leprosy and other diseases</p>","positive":"I suffer from leprosy and other diseases"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leprosy and other diseases</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I suffer from leprosy and other diseases","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"014cuqhhhhquc410","name":"Dose - The Tin Man - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose - The Tin Man - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>To protect others from contagion, I sealed myself in metal armor</p>","positive":"To protect others from contagion, I sealed myself in metal armor"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>To protect others from contagion, I sealed myself in metal armor</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"To protect others from contagion, I sealed myself in metal armor","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00hke2qbbq2ekh00","name":"Dose - The Tin Man - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose - The Tin Man - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>I cannot feel anything through the metal, and I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity piece by piece</p>","positive":"I cannot feel anything through the metal, and I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity piece by piece"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I cannot feel anything through the metal, and I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity piece by piece</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I cannot feel anything through the metal, and I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity piece by piece","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"009b9wleelw9b900","name":"Of Steel","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Of Steel","system":{"description":"<p>Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks unless: 1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door (requires 1 Increment from their Outcome), or 2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature. When the heart door is opened or targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks unless: 1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door (requires 1 Increment from their Outcome), or 2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature. When the heart door is opened or targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00sbjz2442zjbs00","name":"Giant","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Giant","system":{"description":"<p>Dose has 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose has 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00oldmoiiomdlo00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Dose was a patient from early 1900s America who suffered from leprosy and other contagious diseases. To protect others from infection, he sealed himself in crude metal armor bolted and strapped to his body. The armor prevents him from feeling anything—no touch, no warmth, no pain. Over time, Dose has begun to fear he's becoming hollow inside, losing his humanity piece by piece like rust eating away at metal. He was thrown back in time by Dr. Henkle's malfunctioning Compass Rose along with OZena and the others. He follows OZena hoping to find a cure that will allow him to feel again. He helps kidnap Klaus in the swamp to test the Hunters' character.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from leprosy and other diseases<br>2. To protect others from contagion, I sealed myself in metal armor<br>3. I cannot feel anything through the metal, and I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity piece by piece</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect my companions<br>Find a cure so I can feel again<br>Prevent myself from becoming a monster</p><p>Gifts:<br>Of Steel: Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks unless: 1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door (requires 1 Increment from their Outcome), or 2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature. When the heart door is opened or targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene.<br>Giant: Dose has 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant.</p><p>Notes:<br>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Muffled and echoing through his helmet<br>- Mannerisms: Stiff, mechanical movements; constantly adjusts his armor<br>- Pathos: Desperately wants to feel something, anything</p><p>WEAKNESS: The small door over his heart is his only vulnerability. Targeting it requires skill (1 Increment from Outcome) but negates his armor immunity for the rest of the Scene.</p><p>KEY MOMENT: If the Hunters show Dose compassion, he's deeply moved and may refuse to fight them later. His humanity is the key to his redemption.</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he falls in love and his heart returns—metaphorically regaining his lost humanity.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose was a patient from early 1900s America who suffered from leprosy and other contagious diseases. To protect others from infection, he sealed himself in crude metal armor bolted and strapped to his body. The armor prevents him from feeling anything—no touch, no warmth, no pain. Over time, Dose has begun to fear he's becoming hollow inside, losing his humanity piece by piece like rust eating away at metal. He was thrown back in time by Dr. Henkle's malfunctioning Compass Rose along with OZena and the others. He follows OZena hoping to find a cure that will allow him to feel again. He helps kidnap Klaus in the swamp to test the Hunters' character.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from leprosy and other diseases<br>2. To protect others from contagion, I sealed myself in metal armor<br>3. I cannot feel anything through the metal, and I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity piece by piece</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect my companions<br>Find a cure so I can feel again<br>Prevent myself from becoming a monster</p><p>Gifts:<br>Of Steel: Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks unless: 1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door (requires 1 Increment from their Outcome), or 2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature. When the heart door is opened or targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene.<br>Giant: Dose has 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant.</p><p>Notes:<br>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Muffled and echoing through his helmet<br>- Mannerisms: Stiff, mechanical movements; constantly adjusts his armor<br>- Pathos: Desperately wants to feel something, anything</p><p>WEAKNESS: The small door over his heart is his only vulnerability. Targeting it requires skill (1 Increment from Outcome) but negates his armor immunity for the rest of the Scene.</p><p>KEY MOMENT: If the Hunters show Dose compassion, he's deeply moved and may refuse to fight them later. His humanity is the key to his redemption.</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he falls in love and his heart returns—metaphorically regaining his lost humanity.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Dose - The Tin Man","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"name":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-banded-steel.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-banded-steel.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Dose's transformation is ongoing and visible—patches of flesh on his arms, chest, face. He speaks constantly about his beloved. If his beloved is present, he's extremely protective. If the Hunters threaten her, he fights to the death. If they protect her or promise to help them stay together, he becomes an ally. He weeps openly when discussing Dorothea's fate. Voice: Emotional, no longer monotone. Mannerisms: Touches the flesh patches, protective gestures. His ending is the happiest—fully human, in love, choosing to stay.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Protect my beloved at all costs\nFind a way to stay in this time with the one I love\nBecome fully human again through love's power","oppositionLevel":5}}}},"legacyNames":["Dose the Tin Man - The Giant in Love","Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man"]}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Dose suffers from leprosy and other contagious diseases. In early 1900s America, to protect others from infection, he made the agonizing decision to seal himself inside crude metal armor—plates bolted and strapped onto his body, covering him completely except for a small door over his heart. The armor protected others but isolated him completely. He could no longer feel anything through the metal—no warmth, no gentle touch, no human contact. Over time, he began to fear he was becoming hollow inside, losing his humanity piece by piece, transforming into nothing but empty metal. When the Compass Rose threw him to 1780, Dose found himself in a world where his appearance—a walking metal man—terrified villagers who thought him a demon or golem. He follows Dorothea because she accepts him despite his armor, and because protecting her gives meaning to his hollowness. His voice is muffled and echoing through his helmet. His movements are stiff and mechanical. He constantly adjusts his armor, a nervous habit from years of maintaining the seal. Dose desperately wants to feel something—anything—again. In Part Three, if he survives, Dose experiences the most dramatic transformation: he falls in love with a villager of Smaragd. The power of that love begins to physically transform him. Where his beloved touches his armor, it falls away and living flesh grows in its place. Dose the Giant in Love still retains metal armor over most of his body (providing immunity to physical attacks), but patches of exposed flesh show on his arms, chest, and face. The area around his heart—his most vulnerable spot—is now unprotected flesh, covered only by the small door. When fighting to protect his beloved, Dose can act twice in one Exchange, love giving him superhuman determination. His movements become more fluid, more human. He speaks constantly about his beloved, showing emotion rather than mechanical detachment.</p>"},"background":"<p>Dose suffers from leprosy and other contagious diseases. In early 1900s America, to protect others from infection, he made the agonizing decision to seal himself inside crude metal armor—plates bolted and strapped onto his body, covering him completely except for a small door over his heart. The armor protected others but isolated him completely. He could no longer feel anything through the metal—no warmth, no gentle touch, no human contact. Over time, he began to fear he was becoming hollow inside, losing his humanity piece by piece, transforming into nothing but empty metal. When the Compass Rose threw him to 1780, Dose found himself in a world where his appearance—a walking metal man—terrified villagers who thought him a demon or golem. He follows Dorothea because she accepts him despite his armor, and because protecting her gives meaning to his hollowness. His voice is muffled and echoing through his helmet. His movements are stiff and mechanical. He constantly adjusts his armor, a nervous habit from years of maintaining the seal. Dose desperately wants to feel something—anything—again. In Part Three, if he survives, Dose experiences the most dramatic transformation: he falls in love with a villager of Smaragd. The power of that love begins to physically transform him. Where his beloved touches his armor, it falls away and living flesh grows in its place. Dose the Giant in Love still retains metal armor over most of his body (providing immunity to physical attacks), but patches of exposed flesh show on his arms, chest, and face. The area around his heart—his most vulnerable spot—is now unprotected flesh, covered only by the small door. When fighting to protect his beloved, Dose can act twice in one Exchange, love giving him superhuman determination. His movements become more fluid, more human. He speaks constantly about his beloved, showing emotion rather than mechanical detachment.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"medium","impulse":"Protect my companions who accept me despite my armor","oppositionLevel":5},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Protect my companions who accept me despite my armor\nFind a cure so I can feel again and be truly human\nPrevent myself from becoming completely hollow—a monster without humanity\nIn Part Three: Protect my beloved at any cost and embrace my returning humanity","contact":"<p>Dose suffers from leprosy and other contagious diseases. In early 1900s America, to protect others from infection, he made the agonizing decision to seal himself inside crude metal armor—plates bolted and strapped onto his body, covering him completely except for a small door over his heart. The armor protected others but isolated him completely. He could no longer feel anything through the metal—no warmth, no gentle touch, no human contact. Over time, he began to fear he was becoming hollow inside, losing his humanity piece by piece, transforming into nothing but empty metal. When the Compass Rose threw him to 1780, Dose found himself in a world where his appearance—a walking metal man—terrified villagers who thought him a demon or golem. He follows Dorothea because she accepts him despite his armor, and because protecting her gives meaning to his hollowness. His voice is muffled and echoing through his helmet. His movements are stiff and mechanical. He constantly adjusts his armor, a nervous habit from years of maintaining the seal. Dose desperately wants to feel something—anything—again. In Part Three, if he survives, Dose experiences the most dramatic transformation: he falls in love with a villager of Smaragd. The power of that love begins to physically transform him. Where his beloved touches his armor, it falls away and living flesh grows in its place. Dose the Giant in Love still retains metal armor over most of his body (providing immunity to physical attacks), but patches of exposed flesh show on his arms, chest, and face. The area around his heart—his most vulnerable spot—is now unprotected flesh, covered only by the small door. When fighting to protect his beloved, Dose can act twice in one Exchange, love giving him superhuman determination. His movements become more fluid, more human. He speaks constantly about his beloved, showing emotion rather than mechanical detachment.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I suffer from leprosy encased in metal armor to protect others from contagion</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"TdonavxVh9ne8hBv","name":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leprosy encased in metal armor to protect others from contagion</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I suffer from leprosy encased in metal armor to protect others from contagion","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"SrvrSt7QuX617VRc","name":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","itemKey":"descriptor2.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","contentKey":"descriptor2.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I cannot feel anything through the metal and fear I'm becoming hollow inside</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I cannot feel anything through the metal and fear I'm becoming hollow inside","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"QT4pKSfmDegUT0fG","name":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","itemKey":"descriptor3.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","contentKey":"descriptor3.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I desperately want to feel human connection again but armor keeps me isolated</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I desperately want to feel human connection again but armor keeps me isolated","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"kuDCNu8quBWobVFy","name":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","itemKey":"descriptor4.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","contentKey":"descriptor4.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>By Part Three: I've fallen in love and my armor is being replaced by living flesh where love touches</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"By Part Three: I've fallen in love and my armor is being replaced by living flesh where love touches","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"lnJmIlxzjCaYvgiK","name":"Of Steel (Parts One and Two)","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","itemKey":"don1.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","contentKey":"don1.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to ALL physical attacks (swords, arrows, blunt force, etc.) unless: An attacker specifically targets the heart door, which requires spending 1 Increment from their Outcome to aim precisely, OR the attack is magical or supernatural in nature (fire, lightning, curses, etc.). When the heart door is opened or successfully targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene, as the impact disrupts the armor's integrity. His armor makes him nearly invincible to mundane weapons but creates a critical vulnerability.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"successes":0,"trigger":"","exhausted":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"NsBoNIxYb3C7WA8g","name":"Giant","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","itemKey":"don2.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","contentKey":"don2.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose has 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant (giving him 3 Wounds total plus 1 extra Wound for 4 total). His massive armored form and enhanced endurance make him extraordinarily difficult to bring down.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"successes":0,"trigger":"","exhausted":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"QoEYYy4DWVbgdeIZ","name":"Of Steel and Love (Part Three Transformation)","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","itemKey":"don3.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","contentKey":"don3.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>**ONLY IN PART THREE:** Dose's armor is slowly being replaced by living flesh wherever his beloved touches him. **Partial Immunity:** Dose still has metal armor covering most of his body, providing immunity to physical attacks except where flesh is exposed (face, arms, chest patches). **Vulnerable Heart:** The area around his heart is now unprotected flesh covered only by the small door. Attacking this spot requires 1 Increment but completely bypasses his armor immunity. **Love's Strength:** When fighting to protect his beloved, Dose can act twice in one Exchange instead of once, empowered by desperate love and the return of human emotion.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don3.dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"successes":0,"trigger":"","exhausted":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"BtPGHCHVo0LbdcEa","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Protect my companions who accept me despite my armor</p><p>Find a cure so I can feel again and be truly human</p><p>Prevent myself from becoming completely hollow—a monster without humanity</p><p>In Part Three: Protect my beloved at any cost and embrace my returning humanity</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"YDsHtA0xVsO07YOI","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","ownerKey":"dose-the-giant-in-love-the-transformed-tin-man","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose is the Tin Man seeking a heart—but discovers he had one all along when he finds love. Roleplaying notes: Voice muffled and echoing through helmet, speaks about wanting to feel things; movements stiff and mechanical in Parts One/Two, becomes more fluid in Part Three; constantly adjusts armor (nervous habit); in Part Three shows patches of exposed flesh and speaks constantly about beloved with emotion and wonder. Key transformation moment: when beloved first touches his face and armor falls away revealing human skin, Dose weeps for first time in years—can finally feel tears. If Hunters show him compassion (acknowledging his sacrifice to protect others through isolation), he's deeply moved and may refuse to fight them later. If treated as just a monster or obstacle, he fights mechanically without emotion. His tragedy: he voluntarily imprisoned himself in armor out of selfless desire to protect others from disease, but that protection cost him his humanity. His redemption: love literally brings his humanity back, flesh replacing metal where love touches. Ultimate fate: if he survives and is redeemed, he chooses to stay in 1780 with his beloved, watching the last pieces of armor fall away as he becomes fully human again. If killed, his final words are about wishing he could have felt one more time. The small heart door can be recovered as tragic memento—symbol of his vulnerability and humanity.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"00tjb8i55i8bjt00","folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","sort":0}
{"_id":"011rnxyddyxnr110","name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-metal-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-metal-orange.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-dose-the-tin-man-original-version","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man-original-version","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>This is Dose's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Giant in Love in Part Three). Nearly invulnerable to physical attacks except heart door (needs Increment). Magic bypasses armor. Desperately wants to feel something. If shown compassion, deeply moved and may refuse to fight later. Guards Klaus in swamp alongside Hirnloser. Character arc: Hollow metal man → Finds love, armor replaced by flesh. Voice: Muffled, echoing through helmet. Mannerisms: Stiff movements, constantly adjusts armor, clanking sounds. 4 Wounds total due to Giant gift.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Protect my companions from harm\nFind a cure so I can feel again\nPrevent myself from becoming a monster\nGet home where maybe modern medicine can help me","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>This is Dose's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Giant in Love in Part Three). Nearly invulnerable to physical attacks except heart door (needs Increment). Magic bypasses armor. Desperately wants to feel something. If shown compassion, deeply moved and may refuse to fight later. Guards Klaus in swamp alongside Hirnloser. Character arc: Hollow metal man → Finds love, armor replaced by flesh. Voice: Muffled, echoing through helmet. Mannerisms: Stiff movements, constantly adjusts armor, clanking sounds. 4 Wounds total due to Giant gift.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect my companions from harm\nFind a cure so I can feel again\nPrevent myself from becoming a monster\nGet home where maybe modern medicine can help me","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"016quld33dluq610","name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leprosy and sealed myself in metal armor</p>","positive":"I suffer from leprosy and sealed myself in metal armor"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leprosy and sealed myself in metal armor</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I suffer from leprosy and sealed myself in metal armor","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"006d48atta84d600","name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>To protect others from contagion</p>","positive":"To protect others from contagion"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>To protect others from contagion</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"To protect others from contagion","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00scolo99olocs00","name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>I cannot feel anything through the metal</p>","positive":"I cannot feel anything through the metal"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I cannot feel anything through the metal</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I cannot feel anything through the metal","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01cp1a0xx0a1pc10","name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity</p>","positive":"I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00uc0zyrryz0cu00","name":"Of Steel","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man-original-version","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Of Steel","system":{"description":"<p>Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks (swords, arrows, blunt weapons) unless: (1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door, which requires 1 Increment from their Outcome to aim precisely, or (2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature, which bypasses the physical armor. When the heart door is opened or successfully targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene as his vulnerability is exposed.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks (swords, arrows, blunt weapons) unless: (1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door, which requires 1 Increment from their Outcome to aim precisely, or (2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature, which bypasses the physical armor. When the heart door is opened or successfully targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene as his vulnerability is exposed.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00xx5w5bb5w5xx00","name":"Giant","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man-original-version","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Giant","system":{"description":"<p>Dose's massive armored form grants him 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant (4 total instead of 3 for Main NPC).</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose's massive armored form grants him 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant (4 total instead of 3 for Main NPC).</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01gejh9vv9hjeg10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","ownerKey":"dose-the-tin-man-original-version","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from leprosy and sealed myself in metal armor<br>2. To protect others from contagion<br>3. I cannot feel anything through the metal<br>4. I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect my companions from harm<br>Find a cure so I can feel again<br>Prevent myself from becoming a monster<br>Get home where maybe modern medicine can help me</p><p>Gifts:<br>Of Steel: Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks (swords, arrows, blunt weapons) unless: (1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door, which requires 1 Increment from their Outcome to aim precisely, or (2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature, which bypasses the physical armor. When the heart door is opened or successfully targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene as his vulnerability is exposed.<br>Giant: Dose's massive armored form grants him 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant (4 total instead of 3 for Main NPC).</p><p>Notes:<br>This is Dose's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Giant in Love in Part Three). Nearly invulnerable to physical attacks except heart door (needs Increment). Magic bypasses armor. Desperately wants to feel something. If shown compassion, deeply moved and may refuse to fight later. Guards Klaus in swamp alongside Hirnloser. Character arc: Hollow metal man → Finds love, armor replaced by flesh. Voice: Muffled, echoing through helmet. Mannerisms: Stiff movements, constantly adjusts armor, clanking sounds. 4 Wounds total due to Giant gift.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from leprosy and sealed myself in metal armor<br>2. To protect others from contagion<br>3. I cannot feel anything through the metal<br>4. I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect my companions from harm<br>Find a cure so I can feel again<br>Prevent myself from becoming a monster<br>Get home where maybe modern medicine can help me</p><p>Gifts:<br>Of Steel: Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks (swords, arrows, blunt weapons) unless: (1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door, which requires 1 Increment from their Outcome to aim precisely, or (2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature, which bypasses the physical armor. When the heart door is opened or successfully targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene as his vulnerability is exposed.<br>Giant: Dose's massive armored form grants him 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant (4 total instead of 3 for Main NPC).</p><p>Notes:<br>This is Dose's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Giant in Love in Part Three). Nearly invulnerable to physical attacks except heart door (needs Increment). Magic bypasses armor. Desperately wants to feel something. If shown compassion, deeply moved and may refuse to fight later. Guards Klaus in swamp alongside Hirnloser. Character arc: Hollow metal man → Finds love, armor replaced by flesh. Voice: Muffled, echoing through helmet. Mannerisms: Stiff movements, constantly adjusts armor, clanking sounds. 4 Wounds total due to Giant gift.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00a95yr33ry59a00","name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","type":"villager","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-ochre.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-ochre.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-edward-the-miners-chief","ownerKey":"edward-the-miners-chief","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>The chief of the miners at Whitehaven's coal mine, an honest and dutiful man who ensures the mine works at full capacity under watchful control. Edward is a long-time friend of Arthur Browne and mourns his death in the mine collapse. Everyone in the mine follows his orders without question. He hates foreigners who want to poke their noses into his work, protecting the mine's operations for Bardolf Greed. Out of respect for their friendship and grief, Edward allows Frank Browne into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur supposedly died. What Edward doesn't know is that Arthur is still alive beneath the mine, and Frank uses these visits to bring supplies and communicate with his brother through the hidden well leading to the cave where The God Under the Mine's head emerges from the rock.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>The chief of the miners at Whitehaven's coal mine, an honest and dutiful man who ensures the mine works at full capacity under watchful control. Edward is a long-time friend of Arthur Browne and mourns his death in the mine collapse. Everyone in the mine follows his orders without question. He hates foreigners who want to poke their noses into his work, protecting the mine's operations for Bardolf Greed. Out of respect for their friendship and grief, Edward allows Frank Browne into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur supposedly died. What Edward doesn't know is that Arthur is still alive beneath the mine, and Frank uses these visits to bring supplies and communicate with his brother through the hidden well leading to the cave where The God Under the Mine's head emerges from the rock.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>The chief of the miners at Whitehaven's coal mine, an honest and dutiful man who ensures the mine works at full capacity under watchful control. Edward is a long-time friend of Arthur Browne and mourns his death in the mine collapse. Everyone in the mine follows his orders without question. He hates foreigners who want to poke their noses into his work, protecting the mine's operations for Bardolf Greed. Out of respect for their friendship and grief, Edward allows Frank Browne into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur supposedly died. What Edward doesn't know is that Arthur is still alive beneath the mine, and Frank uses these visits to bring supplies and communicate with his brother through the hidden well leading to the cave where The God Under the Mine's head emerges from the rock.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>The chief of the miners at Whitehaven's coal mine, an honest and dutiful man who ensures the mine works at full capacity under watchful control. Edward is a long-time friend of Arthur Browne and mourns his death in the mine collapse. Everyone in the mine follows his orders without question. He hates foreigners who want to poke their noses into his work, protecting the mine's operations for Bardolf Greed. Out of respect for their friendship and grief, Edward allows Frank Browne into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur supposedly died. What Edward doesn't know is that Arthur is still alive beneath the mine, and Frank uses these visits to bring supplies and communicate with his brother through the hidden well leading to the cave where The God Under the Mine's head emerges from the rock.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"014s5rirrir5s410","name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","ownerKey":"edward-the-miners-chief","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death</p>","positive":"I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01z0ynbrrbny0z10","name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","ownerKey":"edward-the-miners-chief","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Everyone in the mine does what I say</p>","positive":"Everyone in the mine does what I say"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Everyone in the mine does what I say</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Everyone in the mine does what I say","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"019p5fcllcf5p910","name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","ownerKey":"edward-the-miners-chief","itemKey":"descriptor2.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>I hate foreigners who want to poke their nose into my work</p>","positive":"I hate foreigners who want to poke their nose into my work"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I hate foreigners who want to poke their nose into my work</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.aldeano","owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I hate foreigners who want to poke their nose into my work","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"018i9s0ff0s9i810","name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","ownerKey":"edward-the-miners-chief","itemKey":"descriptor3.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I allow Frank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died</p>","positive":"I allow Frank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I allow Frank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.aldeano","owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I allow Frank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01jdkhlsslhkdj10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","ownerKey":"edward-the-miners-chief","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>The chief of the miners at Whitehaven's coal mine, an honest and dutiful man who ensures the mine works at full capacity under watchful control. Edward is a long-time friend of Arthur Browne and mourns his death in the mine collapse. Everyone in the mine follows his orders without question. He hates foreigners who want to poke their noses into his work, protecting the mine's operations for Bardolf Greed. Out of respect for their friendship and grief, Edward allows Frank Browne into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur supposedly died. What Edward doesn't know is that Arthur is still alive beneath the mine, and Frank uses these visits to bring supplies and communicate with his brother through the hidden well leading to the cave where The God Under the Mine's head emerges from the rock.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death<br>2. Everyone in the mine does what I say<br>3. I hate foreigners who want to poke their nose into my work<br>4. I allow Frank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The chief of the miners at Whitehaven's coal mine, an honest and dutiful man who ensures the mine works at full capacity under watchful control. Edward is a long-time friend of Arthur Browne and mourns his death in the mine collapse. Everyone in the mine follows his orders without question. He hates foreigners who want to poke their noses into his work, protecting the mine's operations for Bardolf Greed. Out of respect for their friendship and grief, Edward allows Frank Browne into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur supposedly died. What Edward doesn't know is that Arthur is still alive beneath the mine, and Frank uses these visits to bring supplies and communicate with his brother through the hidden well leading to the cave where The God Under the Mine's head emerges from the rock.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death<br>2. Everyone in the mine does what I say<br>3. I hate foreigners who want to poke their nose into my work<br>4. I allow Frank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01pp04mwwm40pp10","name":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/female.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/female.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-elizaveta-the-cruel-bride","ownerKey":"elizaveta-the-cruel-bride","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>She is the mother of Iskra and the central antagonist behind the girl's tragic backstory.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have earned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter Iskra.","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>She is the mother of Iskra and the central antagonist behind the girl's tragic backstory.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":3,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have earned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter Iskra.","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01pgkqdttdqkgp10","name":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride","ownerKey":"elizaveta-the-cruel-bride","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever is needed to get what I want.</p>","positive":"I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever is needed to get what I want."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever is needed to get what I want.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever is needed to get what I want.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00fouv5ww5vuof00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride","ownerKey":"elizaveta-the-cruel-bride","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Elizaveta enjoys a life of comfort and prestige, secured through calculated manipulation and cold ambition. She is determined to protect her position, even if it means sacrificing her own daughter to keep secrets buried.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever is needed to get what I want.</p><p>Agenda:<br>To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have earned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter Iskra.</p><p>Notes:<br>She is the mother of Iskra and the central antagonist behind the girl's tragic backstory.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Elizaveta enjoys a life of comfort and prestige, secured through calculated manipulation and cold ambition. She is determined to protect her position, even if it means sacrificing her own daughter to keep secrets buried.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever is needed to get what I want.</p><p>Agenda:<br>To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have earned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter Iskra.</p><p>Notes:<br>She is the mother of Iskra and the central antagonist behind the girl's tragic backstory.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01p11tellet11p10","name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-pink.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-pink.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-emma-the-childhood-friend","ownerKey":"emma-the-childhood-friend","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>A childhood friend of Clarence Browne with whom she has a special relationship. Clarence has always promised that he will take her away from Whitehaven, but Emma knows deep down that he will never abandon his brothers. She understands that Clarence has a big secret - she suspects his involvement with the Pig Heads - but he tries to protect her by keeping her in the dark about the revolution. Emma offers her services in the city and is curious to talk to foreigners, possibly seeking news or hoping for a way out of the industrial town that has become a battleground between Bardolf Greed and the Browne brothers.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>A childhood friend of Clarence Browne with whom she has a special relationship. Clarence has always promised that he will take her away from Whitehaven, but Emma knows deep down that he will never abandon his brothers. She understands that Clarence has a big secret - she suspects his involvement with the Pig Heads - but he tries to protect her by keeping her in the dark about the revolution. Emma offers her services in the city and is curious to talk to foreigners, possibly seeking news or hoping for a way out of the industrial town that has become a battleground between Bardolf Greed and the Browne brothers.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a childhood friend of Clarence</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>A childhood friend of Clarence Browne with whom she has a special relationship. Clarence has always promised that he will take her away from Whitehaven, but Emma knows deep down that he will never abandon his brothers. She understands that Clarence has a big secret - she suspects his involvement with the Pig Heads - but he tries to protect her by keeping her in the dark about the revolution. Emma offers her services in the city and is curious to talk to foreigners, possibly seeking news or hoping for a way out of the industrial town that has become a battleground between Bardolf Greed and the Browne brothers.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>A childhood friend of Clarence Browne with whom she has a special relationship. Clarence has always promised that he will take her away from Whitehaven, but Emma knows deep down that he will never abandon his brothers. She understands that Clarence has a big secret - she suspects his involvement with the Pig Heads - but he tries to protect her by keeping her in the dark about the revolution. Emma offers her services in the city and is curious to talk to foreigners, possibly seeking news or hoping for a way out of the industrial town that has become a battleground between Bardolf Greed and the Browne brothers.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a childhood friend of Clarence</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01ebeymssmyebe10","name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","ownerKey":"emma-the-childhood-friend","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a childhood friend of Clarence</p>","positive":"I am a childhood friend of Clarence"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a childhood friend of Clarence</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a childhood friend of Clarence","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0084qcnggncq4800","name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","ownerKey":"emma-the-childhood-friend","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I have a special relationship with him</p>","positive":"I have a special relationship with him"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I have a special relationship with him</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I have a special relationship with him","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00mh21ywwy12hm00","name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags"