ptor 5","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","ownerKey":"emma-the-childhood-friend","itemKey":"descriptor4.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend - Descriptor 5","system":{"description":"<p>I understand that he has a big secret, but he tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark</p>","positive":"I understand that he has a big secret, but he tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I understand that he has a big secret, but he tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.aldeano","owner":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I understand that he has a big secret, but he tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00faby2ii2ybaf00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","ownerKey":"emma-the-childhood-friend","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A childhood friend of Clarence Browne with whom she has a special relationship. Clarence has always promised that he will take her away from Whitehaven, but Emma knows deep down that he will never abandon his brothers. She understands that Clarence has a big secret - she suspects his involvement with the Pig Heads - but he tries to protect her by keeping her in the dark about the revolution. Emma offers her services in the city and is curious to talk to foreigners, possibly seeking news or hoping for a way out of the industrial town that has become a battleground between Bardolf Greed and the Browne brothers.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a childhood friend of Clarence<br>2. I have a special relationship with him<br>3. He has always promised that he will take me away from this place<br>4. But I know that he will never abandon his brothers<br>5. I understand that he has a big secret, but he tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A childhood friend of Clarence Browne with whom she has a special relationship. Clarence has always promised that he will take her away from Whitehaven, but Emma knows deep down that he will never abandon his brothers. She understands that Clarence has a big secret - she suspects his involvement with the Pig Heads - but he tries to protect her by keeping her in the dark about the revolution. Emma offers her services in the city and is curious to talk to foreigners, possibly seeking news or hoping for a way out of the industrial town that has become a battleground between Bardolf Greed and the Browne brothers.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a childhood friend of Clarence<br>2. I have a special relationship with him<br>3. He has always promised that he will take me away from this place<br>4. But I know that he will never abandon his brothers<br>5. I understand that he has a big secret, but he tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"name":"Erik","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/child-sleeping.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Erik","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/child-sleeping.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-erik","ownerKey":"erik","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Erik","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Son of Andersen and Satu, unknowingly key to conflict</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Understand who Andersen is","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Lively child who can never sit still</p>"}}}},"legacyNames":["Erik - The Innocent","Erik"]}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"NPC","notes":"<p>Erik is a lively, curious six-year-old boy who can never sit still. He is the son of Satu and Captain Andersen, conceived through rape six years ago, though Erik knows nothing of his dark origins. For most of his life, Erik lived in poverty with his mother, working alongside her in difficult conditions. Then, months ago, a wealthy man—Andersen—appeared and took them both to live in a beautiful mansion on a grand estate. Erik doesn't fully understand who Andersen is or why he brought them here. He senses there is a complicated relationship between the man and his mother, but no one will explain it to him. Erik is fascinated by the Hunters and will approach them with endless questions, not fully grasping the danger surrounding the estate. He is an innocent caught in the middle of adult sins and vengeance. Erik collects shells and on Day 2, he will recognize the shells that fall from Enar's body as matching those found at the cliff where the Sea Fairy lives—this becomes a crucial clue. If Erik is put in danger, both Satu and Andersen will put their lives at risk to protect him. If Enar discovers that Erik is Andersen's son, the child becomes his new primary target, as killing him is the perfect way to make Andersen feel the pain he inflicted.</p>"},"background":"<p>Erik is a lively, curious six-year-old boy who can never sit still. He is the son of Satu and Captain Andersen, conceived through rape six years ago, though Erik knows nothing of his dark origins. For most of his life, Erik lived in poverty with his mother, working alongside her in difficult conditions. Then, months ago, a wealthy man—Andersen—appeared and took them both to live in a beautiful mansion on a grand estate. Erik doesn't fully understand who Andersen is or why he brought them here. He senses there is a complicated relationship between the man and his mother, but no one will explain it to him. Erik is fascinated by the Hunters and will approach them with endless questions, not fully grasping the danger surrounding the estate. He is an innocent caught in the middle of adult sins and vengeance. Erik collects shells and on Day 2, he will recognize the shells that fall from Enar's body as matching those found at the cliff where the Sea Fairy lives—this becomes a crucial clue. If Erik is put in danger, both Satu and Andersen will put their lives at risk to protect him. If Enar discovers that Erik is Andersen's son, the child becomes his new primary target, as killing him is the perfect way to make Andersen feel the pain he inflicted.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"easy","impulse":"Understand who Andersen really is, and why he took my mom and me out of the misery we lived in","oppositionLevel":3},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Understand who Andersen really is, and why he took my mom and me out of the misery we lived in\nExplore the estate and meet the interesting visitors (the Hunters)\nMake my mother smile again like she used to","contact":"<p>Erik is a lively, curious six-year-old boy who can never sit still. He is the son of Satu and Captain Andersen, conceived through rape six years ago, though Erik knows nothing of his dark origins. For most of his life, Erik lived in poverty with his mother, working alongside her in difficult conditions. Then, months ago, a wealthy man—Andersen—appeared and took them both to live in a beautiful mansion on a grand estate. Erik doesn't fully understand who Andersen is or why he brought them here. He senses there is a complicated relationship between the man and his mother, but no one will explain it to him. Erik is fascinated by the Hunters and will approach them with endless questions, not fully grasping the danger surrounding the estate. He is an innocent caught in the middle of adult sins and vengeance. Erik collects shells and on Day 2, he will recognize the shells that fall from Enar's body as matching those found at the cliff where the Sea Fairy lives—this becomes a crucial clue. If Erik is put in danger, both Satu and Andersen will put their lives at risk to protect him. If Enar discovers that Erik is Andersen's son, the child becomes his new primary target, as killing him is the perfect way to make Andersen feel the pain he inflicted.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a lively child who can never sit still</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"RQSYnHCZpRryvl2f","name":"Erik - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Erik","ownerKey":"erik","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.erik","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.erik","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a lively child who can never sit still</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.erik","owner":"Erik","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a lively child who can never sit still","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"U3DgqeTC2Bw2xSkx","name":"Erik - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Erik","ownerKey":"erik","itemKey":"descriptor2.erik","contentKey":"descriptor2.erik","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am curious about everything and everyone</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.erik","owner":"Erik","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am curious about everything and everyone","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"r4imFM29m1izWNdi","name":"Erik - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Erik","ownerKey":"erik","itemKey":"descriptor3.erik","contentKey":"descriptor3.erik","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I collect shells and know the stories about the Sea Fairy</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.erik","owner":"Erik","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I collect shells and know the stories about the Sea Fairy","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"n1b0TO6sxecF1yEY","name":"Erik - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Erik","ownerKey":"erik","itemKey":"descriptor4.erik","contentKey":"descriptor4.erik","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I don't understand why my mother is so sad</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.erik","owner":"Erik","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I don't understand why my mother is so sad","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"1F9Sg2K4QAxce7wW","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Erik","ownerKey":"erik","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Understand who Andersen really is, and why he took my mom and me out of the misery we lived in</p><p>Explore the estate and meet the interesting visitors (the Hunters)</p><p>Make my mother smile again like she used to</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Erik","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"COPfQi7HOpusLael","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Erik","ownerKey":"erik","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Erik is the emotional center of the scenario—his innocence contrasts with the darkness around him. Voice: High-pitched, excited, full of questions. Randomly encountered on estate (roll 3-4 on d6). Provides crucial Day 2 clue by recognizing Enar's shells as matching those from the cliff caves. If endangered, both parents will confess everything to save him. If Enar learns he's Andersen's son (through overheard conversation or confession), Erik becomes primary target. Doesn't understand the tension in the house. Loves exploring, collecting things, asking questions. Represents the innocent future both Satu and Andersen are fighting to protect. His existence is proof of Andersen's crime but also his path to redemption. Can become tragic victim if Hunters fail to protect him.</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Erik","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"0161foceecof1610","folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","sort":0}
{"_id":"015470b22b074510","name":"Father Adrien","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Father Adrien","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-father-adrien","ownerKey":"father-adrien","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Father Adrien","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>The main antagonist whose crime started everything. Will call the Hunters to investigate, hoping they stop Yvonne before she reaches him. If confronted, will collapse in tears and reveal his recurring nightmares. Knows about the comet Morituris and fears the New Year.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling and then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new world","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>The main antagonist whose crime started everything. Will call the Hunters to investigate, hoping they stop Yvonne before she reaches him. If confronted, will collapse in tears and reveal his recurring nightmares. Knows about the comet Morituris and fears the New Year.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling and then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new world","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"000fvdoiiodvf000","name":"Father Adrien - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Father Adrien","ownerKey":"father-adrien","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Father Adrien - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a young priest who chose to take holy vows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and distillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.</p>","positive":"I am a young priest who chose to take holy vows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and distillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young priest who chose to take holy vows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and distillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Father Adrien","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a young priest who chose to take holy vows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and distillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01fgnrcaacrngf10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Father Adrien","ownerKey":"father-adrien","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A young priest at the church of Saint Pierre in Paris who appears tired and worried, with swollen eyes from lack of sleep. Adrien distills absinthe in his church cellars and smuggles it through the catacombs. He murdered little Yvonne when she discovered his illegal laboratory - he strangled her unconscious, set her on fire, and threw her remains in the catacombs. Now haunted by nightmares of Yvonne's death and visions of Paris burning. Yvonne's spirit is systematically killing all those who witnessed her death but stayed silent, saving Adrien for last. A heavy trap door connects the cellars to the catacombs where he passes absinthe to his henchmen (the Ravens).</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a young priest who chose to take holy vows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and distillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling and then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new world</p><p>Notes:<br>The main antagonist whose crime started everything. Will call the Hunters to investigate, hoping they stop Yvonne before she reaches him. If confronted, will collapse in tears and reveal his recurring nightmares. Knows about the comet Morituris and fears the New Year.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A young priest at the church of Saint Pierre in Paris who appears tired and worried, with swollen eyes from lack of sleep. Adrien distills absinthe in his church cellars and smuggles it through the catacombs. He murdered little Yvonne when she discovered his illegal laboratory - he strangled her unconscious, set her on fire, and threw her remains in the catacombs. Now haunted by nightmares of Yvonne's death and visions of Paris burning. Yvonne's spirit is systematically killing all those who witnessed her death but stayed silent, saving Adrien for last. A heavy trap door connects the cellars to the catacombs where he passes absinthe to his henchmen (the Ravens).</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a young priest who chose to take holy vows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and distillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling and then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new world</p><p>Notes:<br>The main antagonist whose crime started everything. Will call the Hunters to investigate, hoping they stop Yvonne before she reaches him. If confronted, will collapse in tears and reveal his recurring nightmares. Knows about the comet Morituris and fears the New Year.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Father Adrien","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01elyfsjjsfyle10","name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/hand/gauntlet-tooled-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/hand/gauntlet-tooled-purple.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-frank-browne-the-middle-brother","ownerKey":"frank-browne-the-middle-brother","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>The middle Browne brother who lost an arm and a leg during the mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine and left Arthur trapped. Consuming with grief and driven by wild hope that Arthur wasn't dead, Frank dug a long vertical tunnel, eventually managing to create a communication channel with his brother. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed. Frank has managed to get hired as a butcher at the big meat factory in the city and secretly mixes the flesh of the God with common meat, infecting the unsuspecting miners who eat it. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. Frank replaced his missing arm with a home-made mechanical pincer with multiple functions. He takes care of their elderly mother Martha but tells her nothing of their plans.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and find a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the day of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine with beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to add to the ranks of the gang","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>The middle Browne brother who lost an arm and a leg during the mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine and left Arthur trapped. Consuming with grief and driven by wild hope that Arthur wasn't dead, Frank dug a long vertical tunnel, eventually managing to create a communication channel with his brother. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed. Frank has managed to get hired as a butcher at the big meat factory in the city and secretly mixes the flesh of the God with common meat, infecting the unsuspecting miners who eat it. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. Frank replaced his missing arm with a home-made mechanical pincer with multiple functions. He takes care of their elderly mother Martha but tells her nothing of their plans.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and find a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the day of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine with beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to add to the ranks of the gang","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00frg85cc58grf00","name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","ownerKey":"frank-browne-the-middle-brother","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act as the strongarm of the gang</p>","positive":"I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act as the strongarm of the gang"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act as the strongarm of the gang</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act as the strongarm of the gang","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00c3gjdqqdjg3c00","name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","ownerKey":"frank-browne-the-middle-brother","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I have control over all cultists</p>","positive":"I have control over all cultists"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I have control over all cultists</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I have control over all cultists","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00vzinymmynizv00","name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","ownerKey":"frank-browne-the-middle-brother","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>The power of The God Under the Mine has given me strength and endurance equal to that of five men</p>","positive":"The power of The God Under the Mine has given me strength and endurance equal to that of five men"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The power of The God Under the Mine has given me strength and endurance equal to that of five men</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"The power of The God Under the Mine has given me strength and endurance equal to that of five men","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"019afqrpprqfa910","name":"The Pincer","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","ownerKey":"frank-browne-the-middle-brother","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Pincer","system":{"description":"<p>Frank replaced his left arm with a home-made mechanical arm with many functions. During a Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: 1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; 2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise or lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other subjects with him.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Frank replaced his left arm with a home-made mechanical arm with many functions. During a Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: 1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; 2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise or lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other subjects with him.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01gc9jv44vj9cg10","name":"Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","ownerKey":"frank-browne-the-middle-brother","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Gang Leader","system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01you3b99b3uoy10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","ownerKey":"frank-browne-the-middle-brother","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>The middle Browne brother who lost an arm and a leg during the mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine and left Arthur trapped. Consuming with grief and driven by wild hope that Arthur wasn't dead, Frank dug a long vertical tunnel, eventually managing to create a communication channel with his brother. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed. Frank has managed to get hired as a butcher at the big meat factory in the city and secretly mixes the flesh of the God with common meat, infecting the unsuspecting miners who eat it. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. Frank replaced his missing arm with a home-made mechanical pincer with multiple functions. He takes care of their elderly mother Martha but tells her nothing of their plans.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act as the strongarm of the gang<br>2. I have control over all cultists<br>3. The power of The God Under the Mine has given me strength and endurance equal to that of five men</p><p>Agenda:<br>Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and find a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the day of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine with beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to add to the ranks of the gang</p><p>Gifts:<br>The Pincer: Frank replaced his left arm with a home-made mechanical arm with many functions. During a Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: 1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; 2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise or lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other subjects with him.<br>Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The middle Browne brother who lost an arm and a leg during the mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine and left Arthur trapped. Consuming with grief and driven by wild hope that Arthur wasn't dead, Frank dug a long vertical tunnel, eventually managing to create a communication channel with his brother. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed. Frank has managed to get hired as a butcher at the big meat factory in the city and secretly mixes the flesh of the God with common meat, infecting the unsuspecting miners who eat it. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. Frank replaced his missing arm with a home-made mechanical pincer with multiple functions. He takes care of their elderly mother Martha but tells her nothing of their plans.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act as the strongarm of the gang<br>2. I have control over all cultists<br>3. The power of The God Under the Mine has given me strength and endurance equal to that of five men</p><p>Agenda:<br>Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and find a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the day of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine with beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to add to the ranks of the gang</p><p>Gifts:<br>The Pincer: Frank replaced his left arm with a home-made mechanical arm with many functions. During a Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: 1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; 2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise or lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other subjects with him.<br>Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"008st289982ts800","name":"Genevieve the Chemist","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Genevieve the Chemist","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-genevieve-the-chemist","ownerKey":"genevieve-the-chemist","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Genevieve the Chemist","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Avoid being exposed for her past and stay useful to the village through her chemistry.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. I know how to summon spirits and talk with them.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Avoid being exposed for her past and stay useful to the village through her chemistry.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. I know how to summon spirits and talk with them.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00dupn1yy1npud00","name":"Genevieve the Chemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Genevieve the Chemist","ownerKey":"genevieve-the-chemist","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Genevieve the Chemist - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. I know how to summon spirits and talk with them.</p>","positive":"I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. I know how to summon spirits and talk with them."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. I know how to summon spirits and talk with them.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Genevieve the Chemist","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. I know how to summon spirits and talk with them.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00d8azziizza8d00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Genevieve the Chemist","ownerKey":"genevieve-the-chemist","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. I know how to summon spirits and talk with them.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Avoid being exposed for her past and stay useful to the village through her chemistry.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. I know how to summon spirits and talk with them.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Avoid being exposed for her past and stay useful to the village through her chemistry.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Genevieve the Chemist","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00koqnhqqhnqok00","name":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-geppetto-gullible-alchemist","ownerKey":"geppetto-gullible-alchemist","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Appears at the Gambero Rosso Inn playing the role of a worried father looking for his 'son' Carlo. Will describe Carlo's old elegant shoes as a clue.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Pretend to be Carlo's father and find him\nObtain the secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Appears at the Gambero Rosso Inn playing the role of a worried father looking for his 'son' Carlo. Will describe Carlo's old elegant shoes as a clue.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Pretend to be Carlo's father and find him\nObtain the secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"0031rtgmmgtr1300","name":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","ownerKey":"geppetto-gullible-alchemist","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor man who has always been looking for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy from master Antonio.</p>","positive":"I am a poor man who has always been looking for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy from master Antonio."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor man who has always been looking for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy from master Antonio.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a poor man who has always been looking for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy from master Antonio.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0105o934439o5010","name":"Improvised Alchemist","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","ownerKey":"geppetto-gullible-alchemist","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Improvised Alchemist","system":{"description":"<p>Geppetto can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, roll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact with the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty feet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 Stench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to all actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air Bomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked back and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can suffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his alchemical concoctions.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Geppetto can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, roll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact with the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty feet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 Stench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to all actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air Bomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked back and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can suffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his alchemical concoctions.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01q5cse66esc5q10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","ownerKey":"geppetto-gullible-alchemist","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>One of two alchemists who kidnapped people in Sinalunga to experiment on them. Geppetto believes Carlo is the key to eternal life and is desperately searching for the living puppet. Wears a tacky yellow wig that hides his alchemical vials.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a poor man who has always been looking for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy from master Antonio.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Pretend to be Carlo's father and find him<br>Obtain the secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy</p><p>Gifts:<br>Improvised Alchemist: Geppetto can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, roll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact with the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty feet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 Stench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to all actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air Bomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked back and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can suffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his alchemical concoctions.</p><p>Notes:<br>Appears at the Gambero Rosso Inn playing the role of a worried father looking for his 'son' Carlo. Will describe Carlo's old elegant shoes as a clue.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>One of two alchemists who kidnapped people in Sinalunga to experiment on them. Geppetto believes Carlo is the key to eternal life and is desperately searching for the living puppet. Wears a tacky yellow wig that hides his alchemical vials.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a poor man who has always been looking for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy from master Antonio.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Pretend to be Carlo's father and find him<br>Obtain the secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy</p><p>Gifts:<br>Improvised Alchemist: Geppetto can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, roll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact with the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty feet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 Stench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to all actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air Bomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked back and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can suffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his alchemical concoctions.</p><p>Notes:<br>Appears at the Gambero Rosso Inn playing the role of a worried father looking for his 'son' Carlo. Will describe Carlo's old elegant shoes as a clue.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01mgf77hh77fgm10","name":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-gerard-dubois-the-incapable-noble","ownerKey":"gerard-dubois-the-incapable-noble","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Gerard relies heavily on others to act in his name, particularly Vincent Arn and the town guards.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Fácil 3","impulse":"Put an end to the menacing werewolves and cover up any possible mischief.","oppositionLevel":3}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Gerard relies heavily on others to act in his name, particularly Vincent Arn and the town guards.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":1,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Put an end to the menacing werewolves and cover up any possible mischief.","oppositionLevel":3}},"items":[{"_id":"00ckld0990dlkc00","name":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble","ownerKey":"gerard-dubois-the-incapable-noble","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am the noble baron of Durfort and my word is law. I live in the shadow of my late father’s glory.</p>","positive":"I am the noble baron of Durfort and my word is law. I live in the shadow of my late father’s glory."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the noble baron of Durfort and my word is law. I live in the shadow of my late father’s glory.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am the noble baron of Durfort and my word is law. I live in the shadow of my late father’s glory.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"017ody4rr4ydo710","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble","ownerKey":"gerard-dubois-the-incapable-noble","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Gerard Dubois is the current baron of Durfort, a position inherited from his renowned father. Though he postures with authority, his reputation pales in comparison to the legacy of the man who came before him.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the noble baron of Durfort and my word is law. I live in the shadow of my late father’s glory.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Put an end to the menacing werewolves and cover up any possible mischief.</p><p>Notes:<br>Gerard relies heavily on others to act in his name, particularly Vincent Arn and the town guards.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Gerard Dubois is the current baron of Durfort, a position inherited from his renowned father. Though he postures with authority, his reputation pales in comparison to the legacy of the man who came before him.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the noble baron of Durfort and my word is law. I live in the shadow of my late father’s glory.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Put an end to the menacing werewolves and cover up any possible mischief.</p><p>Notes:<br>Gerard relies heavily on others to act in his name, particularly Vincent Arn and the town guards.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01imap5005pami10","name":"Greed's Guards","type":"villager","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-worn-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Greed's Guards","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-worn-blue.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-greeds-guards","ownerKey":"greeds-guards","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Greed's Guards","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>About a dozen men from Bardolf Greed's personal guard who stand with their backs to the wall in his mansion, staring at guests like silent statues. They are long-time mercenaries paid handsomely for their loyalty, making it clear that the wealthy industrialist does not feel safe despite his power and wealth. They protect Bardolf during meetings and ensure his orders are carried out throughout Whitehaven.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>About a dozen men from Bardolf Greed's personal guard who stand with their backs to the wall in his mansion, staring at guests like silent statues. They are long-time mercenaries paid handsomely for their loyalty, making it clear that the wealthy industrialist does not feel safe despite his power and wealth. They protect Bardolf during meetings and ensure his orders are carried out throughout Whitehaven.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>We are long-time mercenaries</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>About a dozen men from Bardolf Greed's personal guard who stand with their backs to the wall in his mansion, staring at guests like silent statues. They are long-time mercenaries paid handsomely for their loyalty, making it clear that the wealthy industrialist does not feel safe despite his power and wealth. They protect Bardolf during meetings and ensure his orders are carried out throughout Whitehaven.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>About a dozen men from Bardolf Greed's personal guard who stand with their backs to the wall in his mansion, staring at guests like silent statues. They are long-time mercenaries paid handsomely for their loyalty, making it clear that the wealthy industrialist does not feel safe despite his power and wealth. They protect Bardolf during meetings and ensure his orders are carried out throughout Whitehaven.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>We are long-time mercenaries</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01b7yyuwwuyy7b10","name":"Greed's Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Greed's Guards","ownerKey":"greeds-guards","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Greed's Guards - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are long-time mercenaries</p>","positive":"We are long-time mercenaries"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are long-time mercenaries</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Greed's Guards","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are long-time mercenaries","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01d96mcmmcm69d10","name":"Greed's Guards - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Greed's Guards","ownerKey":"greeds-guards","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Greed's Guards - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty</p>","positive":"Paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Greed's Guards","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00vwv8xllx8vwv00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Greed's Guards","ownerKey":"greeds-guards","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>About a dozen men from Bardolf Greed's personal guard who stand with their backs to the wall in his mansion, staring at guests like silent statues. They are long-time mercenaries paid handsomely for their loyalty, making it clear that the wealthy industrialist does not feel safe despite his power and wealth. They protect Bardolf during meetings and ensure his orders are carried out throughout Whitehaven.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are long-time mercenaries<br>2. Paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>About a dozen men from Bardolf Greed's personal guard who stand with their backs to the wall in his mansion, staring at guests like silent statues. They are long-time mercenaries paid handsomely for their loyalty, making it clear that the wealthy industrialist does not feel safe despite his power and wealth. They protect Bardolf during meetings and ensure his orders are carried out throughout Whitehaven.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are long-time mercenaries<br>2. Paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Greed's Guards","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00xj8i2hh2i8jx00","name":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-greskar-the-big-black-wolf","ownerKey":"greskar-the-big-black-wolf","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":""},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Protect Iskra and devour as many humans as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect Iskra and devour as many humans as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"018bwj2112jwb810","name":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","ownerKey":"greskar-the-big-black-wolf","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge, mighty werewolf. I have to constantly prove my strength to stay the alpha of the pack.</p>","positive":"I am a huge, mighty werewolf. I have to constantly prove my strength to stay the alpha of the pack."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge, mighty werewolf. I have to constantly prove my strength to stay the alpha of the pack.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a huge, mighty werewolf. I have to constantly prove my strength to stay the alpha of the pack.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01qpsajttjaspq10","name":"Big Wolf","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","ownerKey":"greskar-the-big-black-wolf","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Big Wolf","system":{"description":"<p>Greskar is an enormous black wolf, as big as a horse. When he grabs someone with his jaws, in addition to inflicting a Wound, he can drag or hurl them away as if they were a rag doll. Once per Scene, Greskar’s bite can inflict 1 additional Wound.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Greskar is an enormous black wolf, as big as a horse. When he grabs someone with his jaws, in addition to inflicting a Wound, he can drag or hurl them away as if they were a rag doll. Once per Scene, Greskar’s bite can inflict 1 additional Wound.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01az8tuqqut8za10","name":"The Wolf’s Smell","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","ownerKey":"greskar-the-big-black-wolf","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Wolf’s Smell","system":{"description":"<p>Greskar’s sense of smell is infallible. The big wolf will always be able to identify someone if he knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguises and even magic.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Greskar’s sense of smell is infallible. The big wolf will always be able to identify someone if he knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguises and even magic.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"009qlwz99zwlq900","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","ownerKey":"greskar-the-big-black-wolf","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a huge, mighty werewolf. I have to constantly prove my strength to stay the alpha of the pack.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect Iskra and devour as many humans as possible.</p><p>Gifts:<br>Big Wolf: Greskar is an enormous black wolf, as big as a horse. When he grabs someone with his jaws, in addition to inflicting a Wound, he can drag or hurl them away as if they were a rag doll. Once per Scene, Greskar’s bite can inflict 1 additional Wound.<br>The Wolf’s Smell: Greskar’s sense of smell is infallible. The big wolf will always be able to identify someone if he knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguises and even magic.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a huge, mighty werewolf. I have to constantly prove my strength to stay the alpha of the pack.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect Iskra and devour as many humans as possible.</p><p>Gifts:<br>Big Wolf: Greskar is an enormous black wolf, as big as a horse. When he grabs someone with his jaws, in addition to inflicting a Wound, he can drag or hurl them away as if they were a rag doll. Once per Scene, Greskar’s bite can inflict 1 additional Wound.<br>The Wolf’s Smell: Greskar’s sense of smell is infallible. The big wolf will always be able to identify someone if he knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguises and even magic.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Greskar the Big Black Wolf","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
