dier, best marksman, never miss</p>","positive":"Former soldier, best marksman, never miss"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Former soldier, best marksman, never miss</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Hans the Gunslinger","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Former soldier, best marksman, never miss","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00zvsee77eesvz00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hans the Gunslinger","ownerKey":"hans-the-gunslinger","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. Former soldier, best marksman, never miss</p><p>Agenda:<br>Convince Nils to keep secret or remove him</p><p>Notes:<br>Gifts: Experimental pistols (3 targets, OL 7 quick draw), Smoke Bombs (30ft area, 1 Penalty)</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. Former soldier, best marksman, never miss</p><p>Agenda:<br>Convince Nils to keep secret or remove him</p><p>Notes:<br>Gifts: Experimental pistols (3 targets, OL 7 quick draw), Smoke Bombs (30ft area, 1 Penalty)</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Hans the Gunslinger","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00ou87fhhf78uo00","name":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/top-hat-brown-striped.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/top-hat-brown-striped.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-hatta-carter-the-mad-inventor","ownerKey":"hatta-carter-the-mad-inventor","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Hatta Carter is the most skilled inventor in all of England, famous for his theories on automatons. Alice Liddell hired him to research Wonder and make sense of the physics-defying nature of the asylum. Thanks to his hard work, the structure now responds to Alice's will, becoming a place from which it is impossible to escape without her consent. However, Alice has imprisoned the mad inventor in the Basement, keeping him alive for future bedlam expansion projects. Driven to madness by loneliness, Hatta has built two Automata (a Rabbit and a Lizard) as pretend tea companions.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"I want the company of witty people and not cold automata. I long for the chats I had with Alice","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Hatta Carter is the most skilled inventor in all of England, famous for his theories on automatons. Alice Liddell hired him to research Wonder and make sense of the physics-defying nature of the asylum. Thanks to his hard work, the structure now responds to Alice's will, becoming a place from which it is impossible to escape without her consent. However, Alice has imprisoned the mad inventor in the Basement, keeping him alive for future bedlam expansion projects. Driven to madness by loneliness, Hatta has built two Automata (a Rabbit and a Lizard) as pretend tea companions.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want the company of witty people and not cold automata. I long for the chats I had with Alice","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"0152rx1ii1xr2510","name":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","ownerKey":"hatta-carter-the-mad-inventor","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my time</p>","positive":"I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my time"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my time</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my time","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01ll9vj44jv9ll10","name":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","ownerKey":"hatta-carter-the-mad-inventor","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings and aggressiveness</p>","positive":"My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings and aggressiveness"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings and aggressiveness</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings and aggressiveness","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00obwpgjjgpwbo00","name":"Time Clocks","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","ownerKey":"hatta-carter-the-mad-inventor","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Time Clocks","system":{"description":"<p>Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks to influence time:</p><p>1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases his OL by 2 when defending against a threat.</p><p>2. Speed Up: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can act, immediately stopping anyone's action regardless of the situation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, it can act again thanks to this Gift.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks to influence time:</p><p>1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases his OL by 2 when defending against a threat.</p><p>2. Speed Up: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can act, immediately stopping anyone's action regardless of the situation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, it can act again thanks to this Gift.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00zyop7bb7poyz00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","ownerKey":"hatta-carter-the-mad-inventor","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Hatta Carter is the most skilled inventor in all of England, famous for his theories on automatons. Alice Liddell hired him to research Wonder and make sense of the physics-defying nature of the asylum. Thanks to his hard work, the structure now responds to Alice's will, becoming a place from which it is impossible to escape without her consent. However, Alice has imprisoned the mad inventor in the Basement, keeping him alive for future bedlam expansion projects. Driven to madness by loneliness, Hatta has built two Automata (a Rabbit and a Lizard) as pretend tea companions.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my time<br>2. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings and aggressiveness</p><p>Agenda:<br>I want the company of witty people and not cold automata. I long for the chats I had with Alice</p><p>Gifts:<br>Time Clocks: Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks to influence time:</p><p>1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases his OL by 2 when defending against a threat.</p><p>2. Speed Up: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can act, immediately stopping anyone's action regardless of the situation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, it can act again thanks to this Gift.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hatta Carter is the most skilled inventor in all of England, famous for his theories on automatons. Alice Liddell hired him to research Wonder and make sense of the physics-defying nature of the asylum. Thanks to his hard work, the structure now responds to Alice's will, becoming a place from which it is impossible to escape without her consent. However, Alice has imprisoned the mad inventor in the Basement, keeping him alive for future bedlam expansion projects. Driven to madness by loneliness, Hatta has built two Automata (a Rabbit and a Lizard) as pretend tea companions.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my time<br>2. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings and aggressiveness</p><p>Agenda:<br>I want the company of witty people and not cold automata. I long for the chats I had with Alice</p><p>Gifts:<br>Time Clocks: Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks to influence time:</p><p>1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases his OL by 2 when defending against a threat.</p><p>2. Speed Up: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can act, immediately stopping anyone's action regardless of the situation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, it can act again thanks to this Gift.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01vl33saas33lv10","name":"Henrich - The Worried Father","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Henrich - The Worried Father","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-henrich-the-worried-father","ownerKey":"henrich-the-worried-father","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Henrich - The Worried Father","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Minor NPC encountered on the road to Gelb. If the Hunters are kind and offer to help, Henrich agrees to guide them to the village. If they threaten or intimidate him, he runs away. Lowe the Coward is observing this encounter from a distance, judging the Hunters' character.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find help for my son Klaus who suffers from ozena\nProtect my son from harm","contact":"<p>Henrich is a simple farmer whose adult son Klaus suffers from ozena—a terrible disease that has destroyed his nose. They heard rumors that Margareta Westen, the Good Witch of Gelb, might be able to help. When they arrived in Gelb, they were terrified by the sight of so many deformed and disfigured people living there. Henrich is nervous but determined to help his son, even if it means facing his fears.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a simple farmer who loves his son more than anything</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Minor NPC encountered on the road to Gelb. If the Hunters are kind and offer to help, Henrich agrees to guide them to the village. If they threaten or intimidate him, he runs away. Lowe the Coward is observing this encounter from a distance, judging the Hunters' character.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find help for my son Klaus who suffers from ozena\nProtect my son from harm","contact":"<p>Henrich is a simple farmer whose adult son Klaus suffers from ozena—a terrible disease that has destroyed his nose. They heard rumors that Margareta Westen, the Good Witch of Gelb, might be able to help. When they arrived in Gelb, they were terrified by the sight of so many deformed and disfigured people living there. Henrich is nervous but determined to help his son, even if it means facing his fears.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a simple farmer who loves his son more than anything</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01bcrqakkaqrcb10","name":"Henrich - The Worried Father - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Henrich - The Worried Father","ownerKey":"henrich-the-worried-father","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Henrich - The Worried Father - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a simple farmer who loves his son more than anything</p>","positive":"I am a simple farmer who loves his son more than anything"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a simple farmer who loves his son more than anything</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Henrich - The Worried Father","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a simple farmer who loves his son more than anything","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01ems0aqqa0sme10","name":"Henrich - The Worried Father - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Henrich - The Worried Father","ownerKey":"henrich-the-worried-father","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Henrich - The Worried Father - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I will do whatever it takes to help him, even if it means venturing into a village full of monsters</p>","positive":"I will do whatever it takes to help him, even if it means venturing into a village full of monsters"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I will do whatever it takes to help him, even if it means venturing into a village full of monsters</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Henrich - The Worried Father","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I will do whatever it takes to help him, even if it means venturing into a village full of monsters","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01q1vmirrimv1q10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Henrich - The Worried Father","ownerKey":"henrich-the-worried-father","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Henrich is a simple farmer whose adult son Klaus suffers from ozena—a terrible disease that has destroyed his nose. They heard rumors that Margareta Westen, the Good Witch of Gelb, might be able to help. When they arrived in Gelb, they were terrified by the sight of so many deformed and disfigured people living there. Henrich is nervous but determined to help his son, even if it means facing his fears.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a simple farmer who loves his son more than anything<br>2. I will do whatever it takes to help him, even if it means venturing into a village full of monsters</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find help for my son Klaus who suffers from ozena<br>Protect my son from harm</p><p>Notes:<br>Minor NPC encountered on the road to Gelb. If the Hunters are kind and offer to help, Henrich agrees to guide them to the village. If they threaten or intimidate him, he runs away. Lowe the Coward is observing this encounter from a distance, judging the Hunters' character.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Henrich is a simple farmer whose adult son Klaus suffers from ozena—a terrible disease that has destroyed his nose. They heard rumors that Margareta Westen, the Good Witch of Gelb, might be able to help. When they arrived in Gelb, they were terrified by the sight of so many deformed and disfigured people living there. Henrich is nervous but determined to help his son, even if it means facing his fears.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a simple farmer who loves his son more than anything<br>2. I will do whatever it takes to help him, even if it means venturing into a village full of monsters</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find help for my son Klaus who suffers from ozena<br>Protect my son from harm</p><p>Notes:<br>Minor NPC encountered on the road to Gelb. If the Hunters are kind and offer to help, Henrich agrees to guide them to the village. If they threaten or intimidate him, he runs away. Lowe the Coward is observing this encounter from a distance, judging the Hunters' character.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Henrich - The Worried Father","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00599x9gg9x99500","name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-hirnloser-the-scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Speech: Riddles, rhymes, fragmented sentences<br>- Mannerisms: Jerky movements, tilts head at odd angles, stares intensely<br>- Insight: Despite madness, perceives truths others miss</p><p>KEY MOMENT: At the dance, he speaks this riddle: 'The scarecrow sees what you cannot. The tin man feels nothing but knows everything. The lion roars but runs away. And the girl with the silver shoes walks the yellow road to death.'</p><p>If captured, he reveals: 'The wizard in emerald is not what he seems. He steals what he cannot create. The rose blooms red with blood.'</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he becomes The Genius when he realizes his mind is his greatest gift.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Follow OZena because she gives me purpose\nUnderstand the truth of this strange world\nProve I'm more than the madman they say I am","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Speech: Riddles, rhymes, fragmented sentences<br>- Mannerisms: Jerky movements, tilts head at odd angles, stares intensely<br>- Insight: Despite madness, perceives truths others miss</p><p>KEY MOMENT: At the dance, he speaks this riddle: 'The scarecrow sees what you cannot. The tin man feels nothing but knows everything. The lion roars but runs away. And the girl with the silver shoes walks the yellow road to death.'</p><p>If captured, he reveals: 'The wizard in emerald is not what he seems. He steals what he cannot create. The rose blooms red with blood.'</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he becomes The Genius when he realizes his mind is his greatest gift.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Follow OZena because she gives me purpose\nUnderstand the truth of this strange world\nProve I'm more than the madman they say I am","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00lodgvmmvgdol00","name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s</p>","positive":"I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ow27k66k72wo00","name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>The doctors said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right</p>","positive":"The doctors said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The doctors said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"The doctors said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00v59rw22wr95v00","name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface</p>","positive":"Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01a6u0vssv0u6a10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Hirnloser was a psychiatric patient from early 1900s America who was thrown back in time by Dr. Henkle's Compass Rose. The doctors said he was mad, that his brain didn't work right, and over time Hirnloser came to believe he has no brain at all. Despite (or because of) his perceived madness, he sees truths others miss—patterns, connections, and hidden meanings that escape rational minds. He speaks in riddles, rhymes, and fragmented sentences, moving with jerky, unsettling motions. He followed OZena because she gave him purpose when no one else would. He appears at Margareta's village dance and later helps kidnap Klaus to test the Hunters.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s<br>2. The doctors said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right<br>3. Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface</p><p>Agenda:<br>Follow OZena because she gives me purpose<br>Understand the truth of this strange world<br>Prove I'm more than the madman they say I am</p><p>Notes:<br>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Speech: Riddles, rhymes, fragmented sentences<br>- Mannerisms: Jerky movements, tilts head at odd angles, stares intensely<br>- Insight: Despite madness, perceives truths others miss</p><p>KEY MOMENT: At the dance, he speaks this riddle: 'The scarecrow sees what you cannot. The tin man feels nothing but knows everything. The lion roars but runs away. And the girl with the silver shoes walks the yellow road to death.'</p><p>If captured, he reveals: 'The wizard in emerald is not what he seems. He steals what he cannot create. The rose blooms red with blood.'</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he becomes The Genius when he realizes his mind is his greatest gift.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hirnloser was a psychiatric patient from early 1900s America who was thrown back in time by Dr. Henkle's Compass Rose. The doctors said he was mad, that his brain didn't work right, and over time Hirnloser came to believe he has no brain at all. Despite (or because of) his perceived madness, he sees truths others miss—patterns, connections, and hidden meanings that escape rational minds. He speaks in riddles, rhymes, and fragmented sentences, moving with jerky, unsettling motions. He followed OZena because she gave him purpose when no one else would. He appears at Margareta's village dance and later helps kidnap Klaus to test the Hunters.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s<br>2. The doctors said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right<br>3. Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface</p><p>Agenda:<br>Follow OZena because she gives me purpose<br>Understand the truth of this strange world<br>Prove I'm more than the madman they say I am</p><p>Notes:<br>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Speech: Riddles, rhymes, fragmented sentences<br>- Mannerisms: Jerky movements, tilts head at odd angles, stares intensely<br>- Insight: Despite madness, perceives truths others miss</p><p>KEY MOMENT: At the dance, he speaks this riddle: 'The scarecrow sees what you cannot. The tin man feels nothing but knows everything. The lion roars but runs away. And the girl with the silver shoes walks the yellow road to death.'</p><p>If captured, he reveals: 'The wizard in emerald is not what he seems. He steals what he cannot create. The rose blooms red with blood.'</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he becomes The Genius when he realizes his mind is his greatest gift.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"name":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/hood-cowl-worn-tan.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/hood-cowl-worn-tan.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Hirnloser's transformation means he no longer speaks in riddles—his communication is crystal clear and often intimidatingly intelligent. If shown evidence of Henkle's manipulation, he becomes furious at being fooled and turns his genius against the doctor. He coordinates with Lowe and Dose as a tactical unit. Voice: Clear, precise, academic. Mannerisms: Adjusts spectacles, constantly calculating. If redeemed, becomes an invaluable ally with his strategic mind.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Prove that intelligence can overcome any obstacle\nProtect my companions with superior planning\nNever be fooled or manipulated again","oppositionLevel":5}}}},"legacyNames":["Hirnloser the Scarecrow - The Genius","Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow"]}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Hirnloser was a psychiatric patient in early 1900s America. The doctors diagnosed him as mentally ill, saying his brain didn't work correctly. After years of being told he was mad and broken, Hirnloser came to believe he literally had no brain at all—a delusion that paradoxically freed his mind. In the asylum, he developed an unusual way of perceiving the world, seeing patterns and truths that others missed beneath surface appearances. When thrown back to 1780 by the Compass Rose malfunction, Hirnloser found himself in a world that didn't understand mental illness any better than his own time. He attached himself to Dorothea because she, unlike the doctors, gave him purpose instead of just dismissing him as insane. Hirnloser moves in jerky, unsettling ways like a scarecrow animated by magic. He speaks in riddles, rhymes, and fragmented sentences that seem nonsensical but often contain profound insights. Despite his madness (or because of it), he perceives truths others cannot: he knows Henkle is manipulating them, understands that the witches aren't actually evil, and sees the larger patterns of their situation. But his fractured communication makes it nearly impossible for others to understand his warnings. Throughout the campaign, Hirnloser undergoes transformation. By Part Three, if he survives and experiences the truth being validated, he becomes Hirnloser the Genius. His speech clears, becoming precise and brilliant. He realizes his mind was never broken—it was extraordinary, seeing connections others couldn't. As The Genius, he provides tactical insights, prepares countermeasures, and always has the right tool. His Gift allows him to prevent Hunter Gifts through explanation, describe tactics that automatically succeed, and be prepared for any situation. His arc represents society's failure to recognize neurodivergent brilliance.</p>"},"background":"<p>Hirnloser was a psychiatric patient in early 1900s America. The doctors diagnosed him as mentally ill, saying his brain didn't work correctly. After years of being told he was mad and broken, Hirnloser came to believe he literally had no brain at all—a delusion that paradoxically freed his mind. In the asylum, he developed an unusual way of perceiving the world, seeing patterns and truths that others missed beneath surface appearances. When thrown back to 1780 by the Compass Rose malfunction, Hirnloser found himself in a world that didn't understand mental illness any better than his own time. He attached himself to Dorothea because she, unlike the doctors, gave him purpose instead of just dismissing him as insane. Hirnloser moves in jerky, unsettling ways like a scarecrow animated by magic. He speaks in riddles, rhymes, and fragmented sentences that seem nonsensical but often contain profound insights. Despite his madness (or because of it), he perceives truths others cannot: he knows Henkle is manipulating them, understands that the witches aren't actually evil, and sees the larger patterns of their situation. But his fractured communication makes it nearly impossible for others to understand his warnings. Throughout the campaign, Hirnloser undergoes transformation. By Part Three, if he survives and experiences the truth being validated, he becomes Hirnloser the Genius. His speech clears, becoming precise and brilliant. He realizes his mind was never broken—it was extraordinary, seeing connections others couldn't. As The Genius, he provides tactical insights, prepares countermeasures, and always has the right tool. His Gift allows him to prevent Hunter Gifts through explanation, describe tactics that automatically succeed, and be prepared for any situation. His arc represents society's failure to recognize neurodivergent brilliance.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"medium","impulse":"Follow OZena because she gives me purpose and doesn't dismiss me as just 'mad'","oppositionLevel":5},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Follow OZena because she gives me purpose and doesn't dismiss me as just 'mad'\nUnderstand the truth of this strange world we're trapped in\nProve I'm more than the madman they say I am\nIn Part Three: Use my brilliant mind to help or hinder the Hunters","contact":"<p>Hirnloser was a psychiatric patient in early 1900s America. The doctors diagnosed him as mentally ill, saying his brain didn't work correctly. After years of being told he was mad and broken, Hirnloser came to believe he literally had no brain at all—a delusion that paradoxically freed his mind. In the asylum, he developed an unusual way of perceiving the world, seeing patterns and truths that others missed beneath surface appearances. When thrown back to 1780 by the Compass Rose malfunction, Hirnloser found himself in a world that didn't understand mental illness any better than his own time. He attached himself to Dorothea because she, unlike the doctors, gave him purpose instead of just dismissing him as insane. Hirnloser moves in jerky, unsettling ways like a scarecrow animated by magic. He speaks in riddles, rhymes, and fragmented sentences that seem nonsensical but often contain profound insights. Despite his madness (or because of it), he perceives truths others cannot: he knows Henkle is manipulating them, understands that the witches aren't actually evil, and sees the larger patterns of their situation. But his fractured communication makes it nearly impossible for others to understand his warnings. Throughout the campaign, Hirnloser undergoes transformation. By Part Three, if he survives and experiences the truth being validated, he becomes Hirnloser the Genius. His speech clears, becoming precise and brilliant. He realizes his mind was never broken—it was extraordinary, seeing connections others couldn't. As The Genius, he provides tactical insights, prepares countermeasures, and always has the right tool. His Gift allows him to prevent Hunter Gifts through explanation, describe tactics that automatically succeed, and be prepared for any situation. His arc represents society's failure to recognize neurodivergent brilliance.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a psychiatric patient from early 1900s—they said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"KHb00MsSbIiBxBQF","name":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a psychiatric patient from early 1900s—they said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a psychiatric patient from early 1900s—they said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"2UFZ1lOKWig0HOuX","name":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","itemKey":"descriptor2.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","contentKey":"descriptor2.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"vAfjWMV8SwX6li5J","name":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","itemKey":"descriptor3.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","contentKey":"descriptor3.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I speak in riddles and move like a scarecrow, but I perceive the truth beneath surfaces</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I speak in riddles and move like a scarecrow, but I perceive the truth beneath surfaces","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"Ct4QzmgMhc6hTnaj","name":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","itemKey":"descriptor4.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","contentKey":"descriptor4.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>By Part Three, I realize my mind is my greatest weapon—I am a genius</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"By Part Three, I realize my mind is my greatest weapon—I am a genius","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"uxGxpA5YM6mMtVU9","name":"Genius (Part Three Transformation)","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","itemKey":"don1.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","contentKey":"don1.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>**ONLY IN PART THREE:** Hirnloser has realized his intellect is extraordinary. **Tactical Insight:** Once per Scene, Hirnloser can describe a brilliant tactic or strategy that automatically succeeds without requiring a Check. This could be identifying a weakness, setting a perfect ambush, or solving a complex problem instantly. **Countermeasure:** Three times per Scene, Hirnloser can prevent a Hunter from activating a Gift by rapidly explaining how to counter it, neutralizing the advantage. **Prepared:** Hirnloser always has the right tool, item, or piece of information for the current situation, as if he anticipated it. His transformation into The Genius represents validation that his mind was never broken—just different and more advanced than those who judged him.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"successes":0,"trigger":"","exhausted":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"8jpgpq3NC4mO98rS","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Follow OZena because she gives me purpose and doesn't dismiss me as just 'mad'</p><p>Understand the truth of this strange world we're trapped in</p><p>Prove I'm more than the madman they say I am</p><p>In Part Three: Use my brilliant mind to help or hinder the Hunters</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"Ro5HjHgI3nqnXSsG","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-genius-the-transformed-scarecrow","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Hirnloser is the truth-teller whose madness makes him hard to understand. In Parts One and Two: speaks only in riddles and rhymes; movements are jerky and unsettling, tilts head at odd angles; stares intensely at things others don't notice; his riddles contain actual truth if decoded (example: 'The scarecrow sees what you cannot. The tin man feels nothing but knows everything. The lion roars but runs away. And the girl with silver shoes walks the yellow road to death' = warning about OZena's path to destruction). If captured by Hunters, he reveals important truths in riddles: 'The wizard in emerald is not what he seems. He steals what he cannot create. The rose blooms red with blood.' In Part Three transformation: speech becomes clear, precise, analytical; shows pride in his intellect; rapidly analyzes situations; no longer rhymes or speaks cryptically. Key moment: when his 'mad' warnings are proven correct, he has breakthrough realization that he was never insane—society just couldn't understand his brilliance. If Hunters show him respect and try to decode his riddles, he becomes more coherent and may help them. If dismissed as 'just crazy,' he becomes hostile, bitter that even in fairy tale world he's not believed. Ultimate fate: may stay in 1780 to become true inventor/scholar or return to revolutionize early 1900s psychiatry with insights about neurodivergent minds.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"0018tpj00jpt8100","folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","sort":0}
{"_id":"01jrwr5555rwrj10","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-red.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-hirnloser-the-scarecrow-original-version","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow-original-version","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>This is Hirnloser's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Genius in Part Three). Speaks in riddles/rhymes/fragments. Jerky movements, tilts head oddly, intense stares. Appears at village dance, guards Klaus in swamp. If captured, reveals important clues about Henkle in riddles. Can be reasoned with if shown understanding. Character arc: Madman who thinks he has no brain → Genius who realizes his mind is his weapon. Voice: Fragmented, singsong, cryptic. Mannerisms: Jerky movements, odd angles, dancing steps.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Follow OZena because she gives me purpose\nUnderstand the truth of this strange world\nProve I'm more than the madman they say I am\nProtect my companions in my own strange way","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>This is Hirnloser's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Genius in Part Three). Speaks in riddles/rhymes/fragments. Jerky movements, tilts head oddly, intense stares. Appears at village dance, guards Klaus in swamp. If captured, reveals important clues about Henkle in riddles. Can be reasoned with if shown understanding. Character arc: Madman who thinks he has no brain → Genius who realizes his mind is his weapon. Voice: Fragmented, singsong, cryptic. Mannerisms: Jerky movements, odd angles, dancing steps.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Follow OZena because she gives me purpose\nUnderstand the truth of this strange world\nProve I'm more than the madman they say I am\nProtect my companions in my own strange way","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01olvwp44pwvlo10","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s</p>","positive":"I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01c29cl22lc92c10","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>The doctors said my brain didn't work right</p>","positive":"The doctors said my brain didn't work right"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The doctors said my brain didn't work right</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"The doctors said my brain didn't work right","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"007mnavkkvanm700","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>I believe I have no brain at all, just straw and emptiness</p>","positive":"I believe I have no brain at all, just straw and emptiness"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I believe I have no brain at all, just straw and emptiness</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I believe I have no brain at all, just straw and emptiness","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01hbtryiiyrtbh10","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>But I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface</p>","positive":"But I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>But I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"But I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"002x1ykjjky1x200","name":"Mad Insight","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow-original-version","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Mad Insight","system":{"description":"<p>Despite (or because of) his madness, Hirnloser perceives truths others miss. Once per Scene, he can ask the Storyteller one question about the current situation and receive a truthful answer, though it will be delivered in riddles or cryptic language. Additionally, Hirnloser cannot be deceived by illusions or lies—he always sees the truth, even if he can't articulate it clearly.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Despite (or because of) his madness, Hirnloser perceives truths others miss. Once per Scene, he can ask the Storyteller one question about the current situation and receive a truthful answer, though it will be delivered in riddles or cryptic language. Additionally, Hirnloser cannot be deceived by illusions or lies—he always sees the truth, even if he can't articulate it clearly.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01wq67v55v76qw10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","ownerKey":"hirnloser-the-scarecrow-original-version","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s<br>2. The doctors said my brain didn't work right<br>3. I believe I have no brain at all, just straw and emptiness<br>4. But I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface</p><p>Agenda:<br>Follow OZena because she gives me purpose<br>Understand the truth of this strange world<br>Prove I'm more than the madman they say I am<br>Protect my companions in my own strange way</p><p>Gifts:<br>Mad Insight: Despite (or because of) his madness, Hirnloser perceives truths others miss. Once per Scene, he can ask the Storyteller one question about the current situation and receive a truthful answer, though it will be delivered in riddles or cryptic language. Additionally, Hirnloser cannot be deceived by illusions or lies—he always sees the truth, even if he can't articulate it clearly.</p><p>Notes:<br>This is Hirnloser's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Genius in Part Three). Speaks in riddles/rhymes/fragments. Jerky movements, tilts head oddly, intense stares. Appears at village dance, guards Klaus in swamp. If captured, reveals important clues about Henkle in riddles. Can be reasoned with if shown understanding. Character arc: Madman who thinks he has no brain → Genius who realizes his mind is his weapon. Voice: Fragmented, singsong, cryptic. Mannerisms: Jerky movements, odd angles, dancing steps.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s<br>2. The doctors said my brain didn't work right<br>3. I believe I have no brain at all, just straw and emptiness<br>4. But I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface</p><p>Agenda:<br>Follow OZena because she gives me purpose<br>Understand the truth of this strange world<br>Prove I'm more than the madman they say I am<br>Protect my companions in my own strange way</p><p>Gifts:<br>Mad Insight: Despite (or because of) his madness, Hirnloser perceives truths others miss. Once per Scene, he can ask the Storyteller one question about the current situation and receive a truthful answer, though it will be delivered in riddles or cryptic language. Additionally, Hirnloser cannot be deceived by illusions or lies—he always sees the truth, even if he can't articulate it clearly.</p><p>Notes:<br>This is Hirnloser's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Genius in Part Three). Speaks in riddles/rhymes/fragments. Jerky movements, tilts head oddly, intense stares. Appears at village dance, guards Klaus in swamp. If captured, reveals important clues about Henkle in riddles. Can be reasoned with if shown understanding. Character arc: Madman who thinks he has no brain → Genius who realizes his mind is his weapon. Voice: Fragmented, singsong, cryptic. Mannerisms: Jerky movements, odd angles, dancing steps.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01nigdnhhndgin10","name":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-klaus-the-afflicted-son","ownerKey":"klaus-the-afflicted-son","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Klaus is kidnapped shortly after midnight by Hirnloser and Dose, who carry him into the swamp west of Gelb. He is used as bait to test the Hunters and force a confrontation. His fate depends on how the Hunters handle the situation—showing compassion may save him and start redeeming OZena's companions.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find a cure or relief from my terrible affliction\nHide my shame from others","contact":"<p>Klaus is the adult son of farmer Henrich. He suffers from ozena—the same disease that afflicts Dorothea/OZena—a terrible condition that has destroyed his nasal cavity, leaving his face disfigured. He is deeply ashamed of his appearance and keeps his face covered at all times. He and his father heard that Margareta Westen might be able to help, but when they saw Gelb's inhabitants, they became frightened and fled. Klaus becomes a pawn in OZena's plans when he is kidnapped by Hirnloser and Dose to lure the Hunters into a trap.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I suffer from ozena, a disease that has destroyed my nose and made me hideous</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Klaus is kidnapped shortly after midnight by Hirnloser and Dose, who carry him into the swamp west of Gelb. He is used as bait to test the Hunters and force a confrontation. His fate depends on how the Hunters handle the situation—showing compassion may save him and start redeeming OZena's companions.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find a cure or relief from my terrible affliction\nHide my shame from others","contact":"<p>Klaus is the adult son of farmer Henrich. He suffers from ozena—the same disease that afflicts Dorothea/OZena—a terrible condition that has destroyed his nasal cavity, leaving his face disfigured. He is deeply ashamed of his appearance and keeps his face covered at all times. He and his father heard that Margareta Westen might be able to help, but when they saw Gelb's inhabitants, they became frightened and fled. Klaus becomes a pawn in OZena's plans when he is kidnapped by Hirnloser and Dose to lure the Hunters into a trap.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I suffer from ozena, a disease that has destroyed my nose and made me hideous</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00s0p1yssy1p0s00","name":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","ownerKey":"klaus-the-afflicted-son","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from ozena, a disease that has destroyed my nose and made me hideous</p>","positive":"I suffer from ozena, a disease that has destroyed my nose and made me hideous"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from ozena, a disease that has destroyed my nose and made me hideous</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I suffer from ozena, a disease that has destroyed my nose and made me hideous","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00usypyccypysu00","name":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","ownerKey":"klaus-the-afflicted-son","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I keep my face covered because I cannot bear to see the disgust in people's eyes</p>","positive":"I keep my face covered because I cannot bear to see the disgust in people's eyes"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I keep my face covered because I cannot bear to see the disgust in people's eyes</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I keep my face covered because I cannot bear to see the disgust in people's eyes","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"017m83lmml38m710","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","ownerKey":"klaus-the-afflicted-son","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Klaus is the adult son of farmer Henrich. He suffers from ozena—the same disease that afflicts Dorothea/OZena—a terrible condition that has destroyed his nasal cavity, leaving his face disfigured. He is deeply ashamed of his appearance and keeps his face covered at all times. He and his father heard that Margareta Westen might be able to help, but when they saw Gelb's inhabitants, they became frightened and fled. Klaus becomes a pawn in OZena's plans when he is kidnapped by Hirnloser and Dose to lure the Hunters into a trap.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from ozena, a disease that has destroyed my nose and made me hideous<br>2. I keep my face covered because I cannot bear to see the disgust in people's eyes</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find a cure or relief from my terrible affliction<br>Hide my shame from others</p><p>Notes:<br>Klaus is kidnapped shortly after midnight by Hirnloser and Dose, who carry him into the swamp west of Gelb. He is used as bait to test the Hunters and force a confrontation. His fate depends on how the Hunters handle the situation—showing compassion may save him and start redeeming OZena's companions.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Klaus is the adult son of farmer Henrich. He suffers from ozena—the same disease that afflicts Dorothea/OZena—a terrible condition that has destroyed his nasal cavity, leaving his face disfigured. He is deeply ashamed of his appearance and keeps his face covered at all times. He and his father heard that Margareta Westen might be able to help, but when they saw Gelb's inhabitants, they became frightened and fled. Klaus becomes a pawn in OZena's plans when he is kidnapped by Hirnloser and Dose to lure the Hunters into a trap.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from ozena, a disease that has destroyed my nose and made me hideous<br>2. I keep my face covered because I cannot bear to see the disgust in people's eyes</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find a cure or relief from my terrible affliction<br>Hide my shame from others</p><p>Notes:<br>Klaus is kidnapped shortly after midnight by Hirnloser and Dose, who carry him into the swamp west of Gelb. He is used as bait to test the Hunters and force a confrontation. His fate depends on how the Hunters handle the situation—showing compassion may save him and start redeeming OZena's companions.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Klaus - The Afflicted Son","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01aezye33eyzea10","name":"Lizard Automaton","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/magical/construct-iron-stomping-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Lizard Automaton","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/magical/construct-iron-stomping-green.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-lizard-automaton","ownerKey":"lizard-automaton","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lizard Automaton","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>The second automaton built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created as a companion for lonely tea parties, this mechanical lizard is equipped with a powerful tail that allows it to perform multiple actions simultaneously. More robust than its Rabbit counterpart, it serves as both companion and guardian to the mad inventor.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>The second automaton built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created as a companion for lonely tea parties, this mechanical lizard is equipped with a powerful tail that allows it to perform multiple actions simultaneously. More robust than its Rabbit counterpart, it serves as both companion and guardian to the mad inventor.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00xulmyqqymlux00","name":"Lizard Automaton - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lizard Automaton","ownerKey":"lizard-automaton","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lizard Automaton - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter</p>","positive":"I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Lizard Automaton","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00twgjy44yjgwt00","name":"Lizard Automaton - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lizard Automaton","ownerKey":"lizard-automaton","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lizard Automaton - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions at the same time</p>","positive":"Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions at the same time"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions at the same time</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Lizard Automaton","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions at the same time","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0077yiijjiiy7700","name":"Tail","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lizard Automaton","ownerKey":"lizard-automaton","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Tail","system":{"description":"<p>The Automaton always acts twice, once with its front legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both its actions on the same target.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Automaton always acts twice, once with its front legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both its actions on the same target.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Lizard Automaton","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00w2q82vv28q2w00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lizard Automaton","ownerKey":"lizard-automaton","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>The second automaton built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created as a companion for lonely tea parties, this mechanical lizard is equipped with a powerful tail that allows it to perform multiple actions simultaneously. More robust than its Rabbit counterpart, it serves as both companion and guardian to the mad inventor.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter<br>2. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions at the same time</p><p>Gifts:<br>Tail: The Automaton always acts twice, once with its front legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both its actions on the same target.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The second automaton built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created as a companion for lonely tea parties, this mechanical lizard is equipped with a powerful tail that allows it to perform multiple actions simultaneously. More robust than its Rabbit counterpart, it serves as both companion and guardian to the mad inventor.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter<br>2. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions at the same time</p><p>Gifts:<br>Tail: The Automaton always acts twice, once with its front legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both its actions on the same target.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Lizard Automaton","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00fq9ch88hc9qf00","name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-lorenzo-scannapecore-the-plague-doctor","ownerKey":"lorenzo-scannapecore-the-plague-doctor","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Potential ally if Hunters are discreet about Alizée. Can provide information about spirits, the comet, and the dangerous state of the mass graves. Has keys to access the underground pit.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée from prying eyes","contact":"<p>An Italian doctor hired by the city of Paris to manage the Cemetery of the Innocents and the excessive number of corpses in the mass graves. Also a skilled astrologer. Lorenzo sent the cemetery keepers away claiming he needs quiet for his studies, but actually to secretly host Alizée, a nun he has fallen in love with. Knows about the passage of comet Morituris and how it gives power to spirits. Plans to wait until the new year to embark with Alizée towards the New World. Will appear nervous and keep looking over his shoulder at Alizée's hiding spot.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Potential ally if Hunters are discreet about Alizée. Can provide information about spirits, the comet, and the dangerous state of the mass graves. Has keys to access the underground pit.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée from prying eyes","contact":"<p>An Italian doctor hired by the city of Paris to manage the Cemetery of the Innocents and the excessive number of corpses in the mass graves. Also a skilled astrologer. Lorenzo sent the cemetery keepers away claiming he needs quiet for his studies, but actually to secretly host Alizée, a nun he has fallen in love with. Knows about the passage of comet Morituris and how it gives power to spirits. Plans to wait until the new year to embark with Alizée towards the New World. Will appear nervous and keep looking over his shoulder at Alizée's hiding spot.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00pobohffhobop00","name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor","ownerKey":"lorenzo-scannapecore-the-plague-doctor","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive.</p>","positive":"I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00sln4u11u4nls00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor","ownerKey":"lorenzo-scannapecore-the-plague-doctor","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>An Italian doctor hired by the city of Paris to manage the Cemetery of the Innocents and the excessive number of corpses in the mass graves. Also a skilled astrologer. Lorenzo sent the cemetery keepers away claiming he needs quiet for his studies, but actually to secretly host Alizée, a nun he has fallen in love with. Knows about the passage of comet Morituris and how it gives power to spirits. Plans to wait until the new year to embark with Alizée towards the New World. Will appear nervous and keep looking over his shoulder at Alizée's hiding spot.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée from prying eyes</p><p>Notes:<br>Potential ally if Hunters are discreet about Alizée. Can provide information about spirits, the comet, and the dangerous state of the mass graves. Has keys to access the underground pit.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>An Italian doctor hired by the city of Paris to manage the Cemetery of the Innocents and the excessive number of corpses in the mass graves. Also a skilled astrologer. Lorenzo sent the cemetery keepers away claiming he needs quiet for his studies, but actually to secretly host Alizée, a nun he has fallen in love with. Knows about the passage of comet Morituris and how it gives power to spirits. Plans to wait until the new year to embark with Alizée towards the New World. Will appear nervous and keep looking over his shoulder at Alizée's hiding spot.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to detail is obsessive.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée from prying eyes</p><p>Notes:<br>Potential ally if Hunters are discreet about Alizée. Can provide information about spirits, the comet, and the dangerous state of the mass graves. Has keys to access the underground pit.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Lorenzo Scannapecore - The Plague Doctor","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/lion-humanoid-roar.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/mammals/lion-humanoid-roar.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Lowe's transformation is complete—he no longer exhibits cowardly behavior. If shown evidence of Henkle's betrayal, he turns against the doctor immediately, heartbroken but resolute. He works well with Hirnloser and Dose as a coordinated team. Voice: Strong and confident, no longer hesitant. Mannerisms: Direct eye contact, protective stance. If redeemed, he offers to help the Hunters in future scenarios.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Defend those I've chosen to protect\nProve that courage can be found, not just born with\nStand firm regardless of who seems to be winning","oppositionLevel":5}}}},"legacyNames":["Lowe the Coward - The Brave Fighter","Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward"]}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Lowe suffers from leontiasis, a rare disease that causes his facial bones to grow abnormally, making his face resemble a lion's. In early 1900s America, he was mocked, feared, and called a coward because he learned to adapt and survive by siding with whoever held power. When Dr. Henkle's Compass Rose malfunctioned and threw them to 1780, Lowe found himself in a world where his appearance was even more terrifying to superstitious villagers. He follows Dorothea (OZena) because she gives him purpose and companionship—she doesn't judge his appearance or his survival tactics. Lowe is actually the most rational of OZena's three companions. He questions her increasingly violent methods but fears abandoning her would mean losing the only family he has. He's not evil—he's pragmatic. He'll side with whoever is winning because that's how he's learned to survive. But deep down, he wishes he had the courage to stand up for what's right rather than what's safe. Throughout the campaign, Lowe undergoes character development. If the Hunters show him kindness and understanding, he begins to question Henkle's manipulation. By Part Three, he can transform into Lowe the Brave Fighter—a lion-faced warrior who has finally found his courage. He becomes immune to fear, inspires allies, and stands firm even when outmatched. His cowardice was never weakness—it was survival. When he finally finds something worth fighting for (whether OZena's redemption or stopping Henkle's madness), he becomes truly heroic. If the Hunters treat him with contempt or violence, he remains hostile and defensive, convinced they're no better than the witch hunters of the 18th century.</p>"},"background":"<p>Lowe suffers from leontiasis, a rare disease that causes his facial bones to grow abnormally, making his face resemble a lion's. In early 1900s America, he was mocked, feared, and called a coward because he learned to adapt and survive by siding with whoever held power. When Dr. Henkle's Compass Rose malfunctioned and threw them to 1780, Lowe found himself in a world where his appearance was even more terrifying to superstitious villagers. He follows Dorothea (OZena) because she gives him purpose and companionship—she doesn't judge his appearance or his survival tactics. Lowe is actually the most rational of OZena's three companions. He questions her increasingly violent methods but fears abandoning her would mean losing the only family he has. He's not evil—he's pragmatic. He'll side with whoever is winning because that's how he's learned to survive. But deep down, he wishes he had the courage to stand up for what's right rather than what's safe. Throughout the campaign, Lowe undergoes character development. If the Hunters show him kindness and understanding, he begins to question Henkle's manipulation. By Part Three, he can transform into Lowe the Brave Fighter—a lion-faced warrior who has finally found his courage. He becomes immune to fear, inspires allies, and stands firm even when outmatched. His cowardice was never weakness—it was survival. When he finally finds something worth fighting for (whether OZena's redemption or stopping Henkle's madness), he becomes truly heroic. If the Hunters treat him with contempt or violence, he remains hostile and defensive, convinced they're no better than the witch hunters of the 18th century.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"medium","impulse":"Survive and get home to my own time","oppositionLevel":5},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Survive and get home to my own time\nProtect my companions Dorothea, Hirnloser, and Dose\nAvoid unnecessary violence when possible\nFind the courage to do what's right instead of what's safe","contact":"<p>Lowe suffers from leontiasis, a rare disease that causes his facial bones to grow abnormally, making his face resemble a lion's. In early 1900s America, he was mocked, feared, and called a coward because he learned to adapt and survive by siding with whoever held power. When Dr. Henkle's Compass Rose malfunctioned and threw them to 1780, Lowe found himself in a world where his appearance was even more terrifying to superstitious villagers. He follows Dorothea (OZena) because she gives him purpose and companionship—she doesn't judge his appearance or his survival tactics. Lowe is actually the most rational of OZena's three companions. He questions her increasingly violent methods but fears abandoning her would mean losing the only family he has. He's not evil—he's pragmatic. He'll side with whoever is winning because that's how he's learned to survive. But deep down, he wishes he had the courage to stand up for what's right rather than what's safe. Throughout the campaign, Lowe undergoes character development. If the Hunters show him kindness and understanding, he begins to question Henkle's manipulation. By Part Three, he can transform into Lowe the Brave Fighter—a lion-faced warrior who has finally found his courage. He becomes immune to fear, inspires allies, and stands firm even when outmatched. His cowardice was never weakness—it was survival. When he finally finds something worth fighting for (whether OZena's redemption or stopping Henkle's madness), he becomes truly heroic. If the Hunters treat him with contempt or violence, he remains hostile and defensive, convinced they're no better than the witch hunters of the 18th century.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"tBoDv2S2wQSv90DR","name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"UQM76TLi3OvbtQOP","name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","itemKey":"descriptor2.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","contentKey":"descriptor2.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"pwT7xYOwM9fKyiGE","name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","itemKey":"descriptor3.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","contentKey":"descriptor3.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I just want to belong somewhere and protect those who accept me</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I just want to belong somewhere and protect those who accept me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"pUHwliU43cPggqEr","name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","itemKey":"descriptor4.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","contentKey":"descriptor4.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I'm more rational than my companions but too afraid to speak up</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I'm more rational than my companions but too afraid to speak up","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"pKfdM7biHeKLT3TA","name":"Hero (Part Three Transformation)","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","itemKey":"don1.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","contentKey":"don1.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>**ONLY IN PART THREE:** Lowe has overcome his cowardice and embraced heroism. **Fearless:** Lowe is immune to all fear effects, intimidation, and mind control attempts. **Inspiring Presence:** Allied NPCs within 30 feet of Lowe gain +1 to their Opposition Level, emboldened by his courage. **Last Stand:** When reduced to 0 Wounds, Lowe can take one final action before falling—a dramatic last strike, final words, or heroic sacrifice. His transformation into The Brave Fighter represents finding something worth fighting for regardless of the odds.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"successes":0,"trigger":"","exhausted":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"3FODclg9RRVPlZ0F","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Survive and get home to my own time</p><p>Protect my companions Dorothea, Hirnloser, and Dose</p><p>Avoid unnecessary violence when possible</p><p>Find the courage to do what's right instead of what's safe</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"OHEo6jltQKvuCH1X","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-brave-fighter-the-transformed-coward","sourceBackup":"Creatures 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Lowe is a tragic figure who represents survival versus heroism. In Parts One and Two, he's conflicted—observes Hunters from distance in Part One to assess if they're threats or potential allies; may negotiate in swamp encounter if Hunters were kind to Henrich and Klaus; attacks alongside OZena in Part Two if she's hostile, but hesitates if shown evidence of Henkle's lies. Voice is hesitant and apologetic initially, becomes more confident in Part Three. Mannerisms: avoids direct eye contact initially, keeps distance, ready to flee; in Part Three stands tall, meets eyes directly, protective stance. Key moment: if Hunters show compassion for his condition rather than disgust, he gains respect for them and is more likely to negotiate or even betray Henkle. If OZena is killed or captured in Part Two and Lowe blames the Hunters, he becomes hostile in Part Three, viewing them as murderers. His ultimate fate: if redeemed, he may stay in 1780 to live boldly or return home to revolutionize treatment of disfigured people; if killed, his last words thank someone for treating him with dignity. Storytellers should emphasize that his 'cowardice' was intelligent survival—he adapted because that's how outcasts survive in cruel worlds.</p>","notes":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Creatures 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"01lx2eh11he2xl10","folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","sort":0}
{"_id":"00ey92266229ye00","name":"Lowe the Coward","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Lowe the Coward","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-lowe-the-coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Coward","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Lowe is observing the Hunters during their encounter with Henrich and Klaus. If the Hunters show kindness, he gains respect for them and is more likely to negotiate in the swamp scene. If they attack without trying to negotiate, he becomes convinced they're no better than the witch hunters of this era and fights to the death.</p><p>In the swamp, Lowe offers a deal: if the Hunters convince Margareta to give up her Compass Rose piece peacefully, they'll release Klaus unharmed. This represents his attempt to find a non-violent solution.</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: Lowe's character arc involves choosing between loyalty to OZena and doing what's right. His pragmatism could make him an ally if the Hunters show him a better path.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Survive and get home to my own time\nProtect my companions\nAvoid unnecessary violence","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Lowe is observing the Hunters during their encounter with Henrich and Klaus. If the Hunters show kindness, he gains respect for them and is more likely to negotiate in the swamp scene. If they attack without trying to negotiate, he becomes convinced they're no better than the witch hunters of this era and fights to the death.</p><p>In the swamp, Lowe offers a deal: if the Hunters convince Margareta to give up her Compass Rose piece peacefully, they'll release Klaus unharmed. This represents his attempt to find a non-violent solution.</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: Lowe's character arc involves choosing between loyalty to OZena and doing what's right. His pragmatism could make him an ally if the Hunters show him a better path.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Survive and get home to my own time\nProtect my companions\nAvoid unnecessary violence","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00g1y3t77t3y1g00","name":"Lowe the Coward - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's</p>","positive":"I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Lowe the Coward","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01i7bpqrrqpb7i10","name":"Lowe the Coward - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning</p>","positive":"People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Lowe the Coward","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01f7ycxmmxcy7f10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Lowe is one of four patients from early 1900s America who were thrown back in time to 1780 by Dr. Henkle's malfunctioning Compass Rose. He suffers from leontiasis, a disease that causes his face to resemble a lion's, earning him the nickname 'the Coward' for his pragmatic approach to survival. Lowe is actually the most rational of OZena's companions—he questions her increasingly violent methods but fears abandoning her, as she represents his only hope of returning home. He observes the Hunters from a distance to judge their character and attempts to mediate conflicts, preferring negotiation over violence.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's<br>2. People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning</p><p>Agenda:<br>Survive and get home to my own time<br>Protect my companions<br>Avoid unnecessary violence</p><p>Notes:<br>Lowe is observing the Hunters during their encounter with Henrich and Klaus. If the Hunters show kindness, he gains respect for them and is more likely to negotiate in the swamp scene. If they attack without trying to negotiate, he becomes convinced they're no better than the witch hunters of this era and fights to the death.</p><p>In the swamp, Lowe offers a deal: if the Hunters convince Margareta to give up her Compass Rose piece peacefully, they'll release Klaus unharmed. This represents his attempt to find a non-violent solution.</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: Lowe's character arc involves choosing between loyalty to OZena and doing what's right. His pragmatism could make him an ally if the Hunters show him a better path.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Lowe is one of four patients from early 1900s America who were thrown back in time to 1780 by Dr. Henkle's malfunctioning Compass Rose. He suffers from leontiasis, a disease that causes his face to resemble a lion's, earning him the nickname 'the Coward' for his pragmatic approach to survival. Lowe is actually the most rational of OZena's companions—he questions her increasingly violent methods but fears abandoning her, as she represents his only hope of returning home. He observes the Hunters from a distance to judge their character and attempts to mediate conflicts, preferring negotiation over violence.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's<br>2. People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning</p><p>Agenda:<br>Survive and get home to my own time<br>Protect my companions<br>Avoid unnecessary violence</p><p>Notes:<br>Lowe is observing the Hunters during their encounter with Henrich and Klaus. If the Hunters show kindness, he gains respect for them and is more likely to negotiate in the swamp scene. If they attack without trying to negotiate, he becomes convinced they're no better than the witch hunters of this era and fights to the death.</p><p>In the swamp, Lowe offers a deal: if the Hunters convince Margareta to give up her Compass Rose piece peacefully, they'll release Klaus unharmed. This represents his attempt to find a non-violent solution.</p><p>DEVELOPMENT: Lowe's character arc involves choosing between loyalty to OZena and doing what's right. His pragmatism could make him an ally if the Hunters show him a better path.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Lowe the Coward","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"008dzhfvvfhzd800","name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/cat-hunched-glowing-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/mammals/cat-hunched-glowing-orange.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-lowe-the-coward-original-version","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward-original-version","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>This is Lowe's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Brave Fighter in Part Three). He observes Hunters from distance—if they're kind to Henrich/Klaus, gains respect. Most rational of OZena's companions, questions her violence. In swamp scene, tries to mediate and offer deals. Can be reasoned with more easily than others. Will flee if losing. Character arc: Coward → Brave Fighter. Voice: Hesitant, calculating, defensive. Mannerisms: Checks escape routes, positions near exits, avoids direct confrontation.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Survive and get home to my own time\nProtect my companions if it doesn't risk my life\nAvoid unnecessary violence\nSide with whoever seems most likely to win","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>This is Lowe's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Brave Fighter in Part Three). He observes Hunters from distance—if they're kind to Henrich/Klaus, gains respect. Most rational of OZena's companions, questions her violence. In swamp scene, tries to mediate and offer deals. Can be reasoned with more easily than others. Will flee if losing. Character arc: Coward → Brave Fighter. Voice: Hesitant, calculating, defensive. Mannerisms: Checks escape routes, positions near exits, avoids direct confrontation.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Survive and get home to my own time\nProtect my companions if it doesn't risk my life\nAvoid unnecessary violence\nSide with whoever seems most likely to win","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01go27lccl72og10","name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leontiasis, making my face look like a lion's</p>","positive":"I suffer from leontiasis, making my face look like a lion's"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from leontiasis, making my face look like a lion's</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I suffer from leontiasis, making my face look like a lion's","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01yd6tquuqt6dy10","name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>People call me a coward because I adapt to survive</p>","positive":"People call me a coward because I adapt to survive"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>People call me a coward because I adapt to survive</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"People call me a coward because I adapt to survive","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00tj6wq00qw6jt00","name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>I'll side with whoever is winning</p>","positive":"I'll side with whoever is winning"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I'll side with whoever is winning</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I'll side with whoever is winning","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"008sej7227jes800","name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward-original-version","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I just want to get home alive</p>","positive":"I just want to get home alive"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I just want to get home alive</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I just want to get home alive","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ceyq8xx8qyec00","name":"Coward's Instinct","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward-original-version","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Coward's Instinct","system":{"description":"<p>Lowe has a supernatural sense for danger and self-preservation. Once per Scene, he can automatically avoid an attack or dangerous situation by fleeing, hiding, or positioning himself safely. Additionally, Lowe always knows which side is winning in a conflict and can switch sides as an action, immediately gaining +1 OL when fighting for the 'winning' side.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Lowe has a supernatural sense for danger and self-preservation. Once per Scene, he can automatically avoid an attack or dangerous situation by fleeing, hiding, or positioning himself safely. Additionally, Lowe always knows which side is winning in a conflict and can switch sides as an action, immediately gaining +1 OL when fighting for the 'winning' side.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01ytwpmzzmpwty10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","ownerKey":"lowe-the-coward-original-version","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from leontiasis, making my face look like a lion's<br>2. People call me a coward because I adapt to survive<br>3. I'll side with whoever is winning<br>4. I just want to get home alive</p><p>Agenda:<br>Survive and get home to my own time<br>Protect my companions if it doesn't risk my life<br>Avoid unnecessary violence<br>Side with whoever seems most likely to win</p><p>Gifts:<br>Coward's Instinct: Lowe has a supernatural sense for danger and self-preservation. Once per Scene, he can automatically avoid an attack or dangerous situation by fleeing, hiding, or positioning himself safely. Additionally, Lowe always knows which side is winning in a conflict and can switch sides as an action, immediately gaining +1 OL when fighting for the 'winning' side.</p><p>Notes:<br>This is Lowe's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Brave Fighter in Part Three). He observes Hunters from distance—if they're kind to Henrich/Klaus, gains respect. Most rational of OZena's companions, questions her violence. In swamp scene, tries to mediate and offer deals. Can be reasoned with more easily than others. Will flee if losing. Character arc: Coward → Brave Fighter. Voice: Hesitant, calculating, defensive. Mannerisms: Checks escape routes, positions near exits, avoids direct confrontation.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from leontiasis, making my face look like a lion's<br>2. People call me a coward because I adapt to survive<br>3. I'll side with whoever is winning<br>4. I just want to get home alive</p><p>Agenda:<br>Survive and get home to my own time<br>Protect my companions if it doesn't risk my life<br>Avoid unnecessary violence<br>Side with whoever seems most likely to win</p><p>Gifts:<br>Coward's Instinct: Lowe has a supernatural sense for danger and self-preservation. Once per Scene, he can automatically avoid an attack or dangerous situation by fleeing, hiding, or positioning himself safely. Additionally, Lowe always knows which side is winning in a conflict and can switch sides as an action, immediately gaining +1 OL when fighting for the 'winning' side.</p><p>Notes:<br>This is Lowe's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Brave Fighter in Part Three). He observes Hunters from distance—if they're kind to Henrich/Klaus, gains respect. Most rational of OZena's companions, questions her violence. In swamp scene, tries to mediate and offer deals. Can be reasoned with more easily than others. Will flee if losing. Character arc: Coward → Brave Fighter. Voice: Hesitant, calculating, defensive. Mannerisms: Checks escape routes, positions near exits, avoids direct confrontation.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"013nbd7667dbn310","name":"Lucino - The Good Friend","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Lucino - The Good Friend","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-lucino-the-good-friend","ownerKey":"lucino-the-good-friend","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lucino - The Good Friend","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Represents innocence and genuine friendship. Can be used to show Carlo's capacity for good relationships. Will defend Carlo if threatened.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Help Carlo become a responsible child\nWork to help adults who behave well and follow the law","contact":"<p>A loyal and studious child attending the school in Sinalunga. Lucino has befriended Carlo the puppet, not knowing his true nature. He is genuinely kind and wants to help his friend become a better person. If the Hunters put pressure on Carlo, Lucino will intervene to help his friend escape, showing true loyalty despite the danger.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Represents innocence and genuine friendship. Can be used to show Carlo's capacity for good relationships. Will defend Carlo if threatened.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Help Carlo become a responsible child\nWork to help adults who behave well and follow the law","contact":"<p>A loyal and studious child attending the school in Sinalunga. Lucino has befriended Carlo the puppet, not knowing his true nature. He is genuinely kind and wants to help his friend become a better person. If the Hunters put pressure on Carlo, Lucino will intervene to help his friend escape, showing true loyalty despite the danger.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01x8sqxeexqs8x10","name":"Lucino - The Good Friend - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lucino - The Good Friend","ownerKey":"lucino-the-good-friend","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Lucino - The Good Friend - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family.</p>","positive":"I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Lucino - The Good Friend","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01fz819vv918zf10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lucino - The Good Friend","ownerKey":"lucino-the-good-friend","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A loyal and studious child attending the school in Sinalunga. Lucino has befriended Carlo the puppet, not knowing his true nature. He is genuinely kind and wants to help his friend become a better person. If the Hunters put pressure on Carlo, Lucino will intervene to help his friend escape, showing true loyalty despite the danger.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Help Carlo become a responsible child<br>Work to help adults who behave well and follow the law</p><p>Notes:<br>Represents innocence and genuine friendship. Can be used to show Carlo's capacity for good relationships. Will defend Carlo if threatened.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A loyal and studious child attending the school in Sinalunga. Lucino has befriended Carlo the puppet, not knowing his true nature. He is genuinely kind and wants to help his friend become a better person. If the Hunters put pressure on Carlo, Lucino will intervene to help his friend escape, showing true loyalty despite the danger.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Help Carlo become a responsible child<br>Work to help adults who behave well and follow the law</p><p>Notes:<br>Represents innocence and genuine friendship. Can be used to show Carlo's capacity for good relationships. Will defend Carlo if threatened.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Lucino - The Good Friend","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"0110579449750110","name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-explode-disintegrate.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-explode-disintegrate.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-manycorpses-the-fused-lovers","ownerKey":"manycorpses-the-fused-lovers","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura principal","notes":"<p>Manycorpses guards the greenhouse containing Wolfgang's alchemical laboratory. Inside are plants for the Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop) but no elderberry. Defeating or bypassing this creature is necessary to access Wolfgang's notes revealing the complete recipe. The creature's multiple limbs allow it to grapple multiple opponents simultaneously, and its wall-crawling ability makes it nearly impossible to corner or trap.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Difícil 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main Creature","notes":"<p>Manycorpses guards the greenhouse containing Wolfgang's alchemical laboratory. Inside are plants for the Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop) but no elderberry. Defeating or bypassing this creature is necessary to access Wolfgang's notes revealing the complete recipe. The creature's multiple limbs allow it to grapple multiple opponents simultaneously, and its wall-crawling ability makes it nearly impossible to corner or trap.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"items":[{"_id":"012u7sfxxfs7u210","name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","ownerKey":"manycorpses-the-fused-lovers","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am many bodies merged into one through blood magic</p>","positive":"I am many bodies merged into one through blood magic"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am many bodies merged into one through blood magic</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am many bodies merged into one through blood magic","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"008659z99z956800","name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","ownerKey":"manycorpses-the-fused-lovers","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I was lovers who begged to never be separated</p>","positive":"I was lovers who begged to never be separated"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I was lovers who begged to never be separated</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I was lovers who begged to never be separated","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0066jw3vv3wj6600","name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","ownerKey":"manycorpses-the-fused-lovers","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Now we are together forever, twisted and wrong</p>","positive":"Now we are together forever, twisted and wrong"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Now we are together forever, twisted and wrong</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Now we are together forever, twisted and wrong","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00mndkkttkkdnm00","name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","ownerKey":"manycorpses-the-fused-lovers","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>Serving the witch who did this to us is our only purpose</p>","positive":"Serving the witch who did this to us is our only purpose"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Serving the witch who did this to us is our only purpose</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Serving the witch who did this to us is our only purpose","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01ieoqvrrvqoei10","name":"Aberration","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","ownerKey":"manycorpses-the-fused-lovers","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Aberration","system":{"description":"<p>Manycorpses is a magical aberration with horrifying capabilities. **Act Twice:** Can perform two actions per Exchange instead of one, attacking different targets or performing complex maneuvers. **Wall-Walking:** Can move along walls and ceilings as easily as floors, attacking from unexpected angles and giving defenders 1 Penalty on Defense Checks due to the disorienting assault from above or behind.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Manycorpses is a magical aberration with horrifying capabilities. **Act Twice:** Can perform two actions per Exchange instead of one, attacking different targets or performing complex maneuvers. **Wall-Walking:** Can move along walls and ceilings as easily as floors, attacking from unexpected angles and giving defenders 1 Penalty on Defense Checks due to the disorienting assault from above or behind.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"0191a9duud9a1910","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","ownerKey":"manycorpses-the-fused-lovers","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am many bodies merged into one through blood magic<br>2. I was lovers who begged to never be separated<br>3. Now we are together forever, twisted and wrong<br>4. Serving the witch who did this to us is our only purpose</p><p>Gifts:<br>Aberration: Manycorpses is a magical aberration with horrifying capabilities. **Act Twice:** Can perform two actions per Exchange instead of one, attacking different targets or performing complex maneuvers. **Wall-Walking:** Can move along walls and ceilings as easily as floors, attacking from unexpected angles and giving defenders 1 Penalty on Defense Checks due to the disorienting assault from above or behind.</p><p>Notes:<br>Manycorpses guards the greenhouse containing Wolfgang's alchemical laboratory. Inside are plants for the Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop) but no elderberry. Defeating or bypassing this creature is necessary to access Wolfgang's notes revealing the complete recipe. The creature's multiple limbs allow it to grapple multiple opponents simultaneously, and its wall-crawling ability makes it nearly impossible to corner or trap.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am many bodies merged into one through blood magic<br>2. I was lovers who begged to never be separated<br>3. Now we are together forever, twisted and wrong<br>4. Serving the witch who did this to us is our only purpose</p><p>Gifts:<br>Aberration: Manycorpses is a magical aberration with horrifying capabilities. **Act Twice:** Can perform two actions per Exchange instead of one, attacking different targets or performing complex maneuvers. **Wall-Walking:** Can move along walls and ceilings as easily as floors, attacking from unexpected angles and giving defenders 1 Penalty on Defense Checks due to the disorienting assault from above or behind.</p><p>Notes:<br>Manycorpses guards the greenhouse containing Wolfgang's alchemical laboratory. Inside are plants for the Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop) but no elderberry. Defeating or bypassing this creature is necessary to access Wolfgang's notes revealing the complete recipe. The creature's multiple limbs allow it to grapple multiple opponents simultaneously, and its wall-crawling ability makes it nearly impossible to corner or trap.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Manycorpses - The Fused Lovers","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00ave8ieei8eva00","name":"Marcel the Time-Waster","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Marcel the Time-Waster","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-marcel-the-time-waster","ownerKey":"marcel-the-time-waster","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Marcel the Time-Waster","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Be heard and prove that what he saw in the Oak Glade is real.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I frequently wander the town and may be found anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no one believed my story because I am too young.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Be heard and prove that what he saw in the Oak Glade is real.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I frequently wander the town and may be found anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no one believed my story because I am too young.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01gndi1mm1idng10","name":"Marcel the Time-Waster - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marcel the Time-Waster","ownerKey":"marcel-the-time-waster","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Marcel the Time-Waster - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I frequently wander the town and may be found anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no one believed my story because I am too young.</p>","positive":"I frequently wander the town and may be found anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no one believed my story because I am too young."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I frequently wander the town and may be found anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no one believed my story because I am too young.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Marcel the Time-Waster","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I frequently wander the town and may be found anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no one believed my story because I am too young.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01sftrt33trtfs10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marcel the Time-Waster","ownerKey":"marcel-the-time-waster","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I frequently wander the town and may be found anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no one believed my story because I am too young.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Be heard and prove that what he saw in the Oak Glade is real.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I frequently wander the town and may be found anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no one believed my story because I am too young.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Be heard and prove that what he saw in the Oak Glade is real.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Marcel the Time-Waster","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00qghbwllwbhgq00","name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-margareta-westen-the-good-witch","ownerKey":"margareta-westen-the-good-witch","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Warm and maternal, with a slight German accent<br>- Mannerisms: Touches people gently when speaking to them, maintains eye contact, smiles despite her facial deformity<br>- Motivation: Genuinely wants to help outcasts, has built a thriving community<br>- Secret: She knows OZena was once a good person driven mad by desperation<br>- Weakness: Her compassion makes her vulnerable—she hesitates to harm even those who threaten her</p><p>WHAT SHE KNOWS:<br>- The Compass Rose is split into four pieces held by four witches<br>- Johanne was murdered two weeks ago in Schiltach<br>- OZena travels with three companions: Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose<br>- Dr. Henkle is manipulating OZena from Smaragd</p><p>Her piece of the Compass Rose resembles a yellow compass needle made of amber that hums with magical energy and points toward Smaragd.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Difícil 7","impulse":"Protect my village and the outcasts who live here\nUse my magic to ease suffering\nStop OZena before she kills more witches","oppositionLevel":7}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Warm and maternal, with a slight German accent<br>- Mannerisms: Touches people gently when speaking to them, maintains eye contact, smiles despite her facial deformity<br>- Motivation: Genuinely wants to help outcasts, has built a thriving community<br>- Secret: She knows OZena was once a good person driven mad by desperation<br>- Weakness: Her compassion makes her vulnerable—she hesitates to harm even those who threaten her</p><p>WHAT SHE KNOWS:<br>- The Compass Rose is split into four pieces held by four witches<br>- Johanne was murdered two weeks ago in Schiltach<br>- OZena travels with three companions: Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose<br>- Dr. Henkle is manipulating OZena from Smaragd</p><p>Her piece of the Compass Rose resembles a yellow compass needle made of amber that hums with magical energy and points toward Smaragd.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Protect my village and the outcasts who live here\nUse my magic to ease suffering\nStop OZena before she kills more witches","oppositionLevel":7}},"items":[{"_id":"01iaecaccaceai10","name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","ownerKey":"margareta-westen-the-good-witch","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity</p>","positive":"I am a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"005znlruurlnz500","name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","ownerKey":"margareta-westen-the-good-witch","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Society rejected me, so I use my magic and my fortune to create a haven where the rejected can live in peace and dignity</p>","positive":"Society rejected me, so I use my magic and my fortune to create a haven where the rejected can live in peace and dignity"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Society rejected me, so I use my magic and my fortune to create a haven where the rejected can live in peace and dignity</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Society rejected me, so I use my magic and my fortune to create a haven where the rejected can live in peace and dignity","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"019dtcrjjrctd910","name":"Witch - Emotion Manipulation","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","ownerKey":"margareta-westen-the-good-witch","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Witch - Emotion Manipulation","system":{"description":"<p>Margareta can perform a Check to alter the emotional state of anyone she can see. She can make them feel calm, afraid, angry, or loving. This lasts for one Scene. Victims can resist with a Check against her Opposition Level.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Margareta can perform a Check to alter the emotional state of anyone she can see. She can make them feel calm, afraid, angry, or loving. This lasts for one Scene. Victims can resist with a Check against her Opposition Level.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00rrpyfwwfyprr00","name":"Witch - Telekinesis","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","ownerKey":"margareta-westen-the-good-witch","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Witch - Telekinesis","system":{"description":"<p>Margareta can move objects with her mind. She can lift and throw items weighing up to 200 pounds. In combat, she can use this to disarm opponents, create barriers, or hurl objects as weapons (treating this as a normal attack).</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Margareta can move objects with her mind. She can lift and throw items weighing up to 200 pounds. In combat, she can use this to disarm opponents, create barriers, or hurl objects as weapons (treating this as a normal attack).</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"0035w4r77r4w5300","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","ownerKey":"margareta-westen-the-good-witch","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Margareta Westen is the Good Witch of the Yellow Village of Gelb. Born a wealthy noblewoman with a facial deformity, she was rejected by society despite her status. Using her inherited fortune and her magical gifts, she created a haven in the Black Forest where outcasts, the deformed, and the rejected can live in peace and dignity. She provides for their needs and uses her magic to ease their suffering. Margareta holds one piece of the Compass Rose—the Yellow (West) piece—which she guards as part of a coven of four witches who split the artifact to keep it safe. She knows that OZena has already killed Johanne in Schiltach and fears she may be next.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity<br>2. Society rejected me, so I use my magic and my fortune to create a haven where the rejected can live in peace and dignity</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect my village and the outcasts who live here<br>Use my magic to ease suffering<br>Stop OZena before she kills more witches</p><p>Gifts:<br>Witch - Emotion Manipulation: Margareta can perform a Check to alter the emotional state of anyone she can see. She can make them feel calm, afraid, angry, or loving. This lasts for one Scene. Victims can resist with a Check against her Opposition Level.<br>Witch - Telekinesis: Margareta can move objects with her mind. She can lift and throw items weighing up to 200 pounds. In combat, she can use this to disarm opponents, create barriers, or hurl objects as weapons (treating this as a normal attack).</p><p>Notes:<br>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Warm and maternal, with a slight German accent<br>- Mannerisms: Touches people gently when speaking to them, maintains eye contact, smiles despite her facial deformity<br>- Motivation: Genuinely wants to help outcasts, has built a thriving community<br>- Secret: She knows OZena was once a good person driven mad by desperation<br>- Weakness: Her compassion makes her vulnerable—she hesitates to harm even those who threaten her</p><p>WHAT SHE KNOWS:<br>- The Compass Rose is split into four pieces held by four witches<br>- Johanne was murdered two weeks ago in Schiltach<br>- OZena travels with three companions: Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose<br>- Dr. Henkle is manipulating OZena from Smaragd</p><p>Her piece of the Compass Rose resembles a yellow compass needle made of amber that hums with magical energy and points toward Smaragd.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Margareta Westen is the Good Witch of the Yellow Village of Gelb. Born a wealthy noblewoman with a facial deformity, she was rejected by society despite her status. Using her inherited fortune and her magical gifts, she created a haven in the Black Forest where outcasts, the deformed, and the rejected can live in peace and dignity. She provides for their needs and uses her magic to ease their suffering. Margareta holds one piece of the Compass Rose—the Yellow (West) piece—which she guards as part of a coven of four witches who split the artifact to keep it safe. She knows that OZena has already killed Johanne in Schiltach and fears she may be next.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity<br>2. Society rejected me, so I use my magic and my fortune to create a haven where the rejected can live in peace and dignity</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect my village and the outcasts who live here<br>Use my magic to ease suffering<br>Stop OZena before she kills more witches</p><p>Gifts:<br>Witch - Emotion Manipulation: Margareta can perform a Check to alter the emotional state of anyone she can see. She can make them feel calm, afraid, angry, or loving. This lasts for one Scene. Victims can resist with a Check against her Opposition Level.<br>Witch - Telekinesis: Margareta can move objects with her mind. She can lift and throw items weighing up to 200 pounds. In combat, she can use this to disarm opponents, create barriers, or hurl objects as weapons (treating this as a normal attack).</p><p>Notes:<br>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Warm and maternal, with a slight German accent<br>- Mannerisms: Touches people gently when speaking to them, maintains eye contact, smiles despite her facial deformity<br>- Motivation: Genuinely wants to help outcasts, has built a thriving community<br>- Secret: She knows OZena was once a good person driven mad by desperation<br>- Weakness: Her compassion makes her vulnerable—she hesitates to harm even those who threaten her</p><p>WHAT SHE KNOWS:<br>- The Compass Rose is split into four pieces held by four witches<br>- Johanne was murdered two weeks ago in Schiltach<br>- OZena travels with three companions: Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose<br>- Dr. Henkle is manipulating OZena from Smaragd</p><p>Her piece of the Compass Rose resembles a yellow compass needle made of amber that hums with magical energy and points toward Smaragd.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"017y7jybbyj7y710","name":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-marionette-cursed-soul","ownerKey":"marionette-cursed-soul","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":"<p>Minor NPCs with 2 wounds. Will attack on sight. Their Gift makes them extremely dangerous in their final moments. Can be freed/calmed if Hunters understand they are imprisoned souls.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Fácil 3","impulse":"Attacking every human we meet","oppositionLevel":3}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":"<p>Minor NPCs with 2 wounds. Will attack on sight. Their Gift makes them extremely dangerous in their final moments. Can be freed/calmed if Hunters understand they are imprisoned souls.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Attacking every human we meet","oppositionLevel":3}},"items":[{"_id":"005fi59yy95if500","name":"Marionette - Cursed Soul - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","ownerKey":"marionette-cursed-soul","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Marionette - Cursed Soul - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden bodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to be destroyed to be free again.</p>","positive":"We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden bodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to be destroyed to be free again."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden bodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to be destroyed to be free again.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden bodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to be destroyed to be free again.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00bo5nlffln5ob00","name":"Boundless Rage","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","ownerKey":"marionette-cursed-soul","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Boundless Rage","system":{"description":"<p>Azzurra's power animates and forces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette suffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the enemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra's power compels them one last time. The Marionette can take a final action with OL Hard 7. This action must be aimed at harming a living being.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Azzurra's power animates and forces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette suffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the enemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra's power compels them one last time. The Marionette can take a final action with OL Hard 7. This action must be aimed at harming a living being.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00nxx9n33n9xxn00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","ownerKey":"marionette-cursed-soul","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Human-sized wooden mannequins skillfully crafted by Antonio and Geppetto, stained with blood and decomposing skin. These were the first two produced by the alchemists' experiments and were later animated by Azzurra's dark magic. Cursed souls are trapped within these wooden bodies, forced to attack all living beings. They long for destruction to be freed. Two Marionettes are found in Antonio's old carpenter shop, and four more guard the gardens of Villa Cilesterino.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden bodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to be destroyed to be free again.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Attacking every human we meet</p><p>Gifts:<br>Boundless Rage: Azzurra's power animates and forces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette suffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the enemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra's power compels them one last time. The Marionette can take a final action with OL Hard 7. This action must be aimed at harming a living being.</p><p>Notes:<br>Minor NPCs with 2 wounds. Will attack on sight. Their Gift makes them extremely dangerous in their final moments. Can be freed/calmed if Hunters understand they are imprisoned souls.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Human-sized wooden mannequins skillfully crafted by Antonio and Geppetto, stained with blood and decomposing skin. These were the first two produced by the alchemists' experiments and were later animated by Azzurra's dark magic. Cursed souls are trapped within these wooden bodies, forced to attack all living beings. They long for destruction to be freed. Two Marionettes are found in Antonio's old carpenter shop, and four more guard the gardens of Villa Cilesterino.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden bodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to be destroyed to be free again.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Attacking every human we meet</p><p>Gifts:<br>Boundless Rage: Azzurra's power animates and forces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette suffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the enemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra's power compels them one last time. The Marionette can take a final action with OL Hard 7. This action must be aimed at harming a living being.</p><p>Notes:<br>Minor NPCs with 2 wounds. Will attack on sight. Their Gift makes them extremely dangerous in their final moments. Can be freed/calmed if Hunters understand they are imprisoned souls.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Marionette - Cursed Soul","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00vsun4ww4nusv00","name":"Martha Browne - The Mother","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/elder-female-gray.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Martha Browne - The Mother","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/elder-female-gray.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-martha-browne-the-mother","ownerKey":"martha-browne-the-mother","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Martha Browne - The Mother","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>The elderly mother of Clarence, Frank, and Arthur Browne. She is so old that she has almost completely lost her sight. Her son Frank takes care of her, but he doesn't tell her anything about their plans or the Pig Heads revolution. Despite everyone telling her that Arthur died in the mine collapse, Martha is convinced that he is not dead - her instinct as a mother tells her so, and she is right. Arthur is alive, trapped beneath the mine, feeding on the flesh of The God Under the Mine and orchestrating the gang's war against Bardolf Greed.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>The elderly mother of Clarence, Frank, and Arthur Browne. She is so old that she has almost completely lost her sight. Her son Frank takes care of her, but he doesn't tell her anything about their plans or the Pig Heads revolution. Despite everyone telling her that Arthur died in the mine collapse, Martha is convinced that he is not dead - her instinct as a mother tells her so, and she is right. Arthur is alive, trapped beneath the mine, feeding on the flesh of The God Under the Mine and orchestrating the gang's war against Bardolf Greed.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am the mother of three brothers</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>The elderly mother of Clarence, Frank, and Arthur Browne. She is so old that she has almost completely lost her sight. Her son Frank takes care of her, but he doesn't tell her anything about their plans or the Pig Heads revolution. Despite everyone telling her that Arthur died in the mine collapse, Martha is convinced that he is not dead - her instinct as a mother tells her so, and she is right. Arthur is alive, trapped beneath the mine, feeding on the flesh of The God Under the Mine and orchestrating the gang's war against Bardolf Greed.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>The elderly mother of Clarence, Frank, and Arthur Browne. She is so old that she has almost completely lost her sight. Her son Frank takes care of her, but he doesn't tell her anything about their plans or the Pig Heads revolution. Despite everyone telling her that Arthur died in the mine collapse, Martha is convinced that he is not dead - her instinct as a mother tells her so, and she is right. Arthur is alive, trapped beneath the mine, feeding on the flesh of The God Under the Mine and orchestrating the gang's war against Bardolf Greed.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am the mother of three brothers</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00coke6aa6ekoc00","name":"Martha Browne - The Mother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","ownerKey":"martha-browne-the-mother","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Martha Browne - The Mother - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am the mother of three brothers</p>","positive":"I am the mother of three brothers"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the mother of three brothers</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am the mother of three brothers","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00rlv9ecce9vlr00","name":"Martha Browne - The Mother - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","ownerKey":"martha-browne-the-mother","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Martha Browne - The Mother - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I am so old that I have almost completely lost my sight</p>","positive":"I am so old that I have almost completely lost my sight"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am so old that I have almost completely lost my sight</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am so old that I have almost completely lost my sight","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00xu59hmmh95ux00","name":"Martha Browne - The Mother - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","ownerKey":"martha-browne-the-mother","itemKey":"descriptor2.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Martha Browne - The Mother - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>My son Frank takes care of me, but he doesn't tell me anything</p>","positive":"My son Frank takes care of me, but he doesn't tell me anything"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>My son Frank takes care of me, but he doesn't tell me anything</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.aldeano","owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My son Frank takes care of me, but he doesn't tell me anything","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01k7dnrccrnd7k10","name":"Martha Browne - The Mother - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","ownerKey":"martha-browne-the-mother","itemKey":"descriptor3.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Martha Browne - The Mother - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I am convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a mother tells me so</p>","positive":"I am convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a mother tells me so"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a mother tells me so</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.aldeano","owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a mother tells me so","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00fwaox99xoawf00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","ownerKey":"martha-browne-the-mother","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>The elderly mother of Clarence, Frank, and Arthur Browne. She is so old that she has almost completely lost her sight. Her son Frank takes care of her, but he doesn't tell her anything about their plans or the Pig Heads revolution. Despite everyone telling her that Arthur died in the mine collapse, Martha is convinced that he is not dead - her instinct as a mother tells her so, and she is right. Arthur is alive, trapped beneath the mine, feeding on the flesh of The God Under the Mine and orchestrating the gang's war against Bardolf Greed.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the mother of three brothers<br>2. I am so old that I have almost completely lost my sight<br>3. My son Frank takes care of me, but he doesn't tell me anything<br>4. I am convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a mother tells me so</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The elderly mother of Clarence, Frank, and Arthur Browne. She is so old that she has almost completely lost her sight. Her son Frank takes care of her, but he doesn't tell her anything about their plans or the Pig Heads revolution. Despite everyone telling her that Arthur died in the mine collapse, Martha is convinced that he is not dead - her instinct as a mother tells her so, and she is right. Arthur is alive, trapped beneath the mine, feeding on the flesh of The God Under the Mine and orchestrating the gang's war against Bardolf Greed.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am the mother of three brothers<br>2. I am so old that I have almost completely lost my sight<br>3. My son Frank takes care of me, but he doesn't tell me anything<br>4. I am convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a mother tells me so</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Martha Browne - The Mother","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01dopeajjaepod10","name":"Medoro - The Old Bear","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Medoro - The Old Bear","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-medoro-the-old-bear","ownerKey":"medoro-the-old-bear","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Medoro - The Old Bear","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":"<p>Has 4 wounds making him tougher than typical Minor NPCs. Azzurra uses him as her primary physical guardian. Can be spared or negotiated with if Azzurra intervenes.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Serve and protect Azzurra","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":"<p>Has 4 wounds making him tougher than typical Minor NPCs. Azzurra uses him as her primary physical guardian. Can be spared or negotiated with if Azzurra intervenes.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Serve and protect Azzurra","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"0101f1jllj1f1010","name":"Medoro - The Old Bear - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Medoro - The Old Bear","ownerKey":"medoro-the-old-bear","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Medoro - The Old Bear - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its fur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I serve her happily. I have retained most of my animal strength, despite the scars and the passing of time.</p>","positive":"I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its fur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I serve her happily. I have retained most of my animal strength, despite the scars and the passing of time."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its fur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I serve her happily. I have retained most of my animal strength, despite the scars and the passing of time.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Medoro - The Old Bear","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its fur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I serve her happily. I have retained most of my animal strength, despite the scars and the passing of time.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ou63illi36uo00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Medoro - The Old Bear","ownerKey":"medoro-the-old-bear","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A massive hairless bear with skin pocked by disease. Once a normal bear, Medoro now serves Azzurra as a guardian of Villa Cilesterino's garden. Despite his grotesque appearance and advanced age, he retains much of his animal strength. Guards the garden along with 4 Marionettes. Will attack intruders on sight, charging at them with bestial fury.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its fur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I serve her happily. I have retained most of my animal strength, despite the scars and the passing of time.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Serve and protect Azzurra</p><p>Notes:<br>Has 4 wounds making him tougher than typical Minor NPCs. Azzurra uses him as her primary physical guardian. Can be spared or negotiated with if Azzurra intervenes.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A massive hairless bear with skin pocked by disease. Once a normal bear, Medoro now serves Azzurra as a guardian of Villa Cilesterino's garden. Despite his grotesque appearance and advanced age, he retains much of his animal strength. Guards the garden along with 4 Marionettes. Will attack intruders on sight, charging at them with bestial fury.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its fur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I serve her happily. I have retained most of my animal strength, despite the scars and the passing of time.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Serve and protect Azzurra</p><p>Notes:<br>Has 4 wounds making him tougher than typical Minor NPCs. Azzurra uses him as her primary physical guardian. Can be spared or negotiated with if Azzurra intervenes.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Medoro - The Old Bear","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00zn77ibbi77nz00","name":"Nicholas the Huntsman","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Nicholas the Huntsman","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-nicholas-the-huntsman","ownerKey":"nicholas-the-huntsman","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Nicholas the Huntsman","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Earn recognition from Baron Gerard by proving himself useful in the hunt.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to show off in front of Baron Gerard.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Earn recognition from Baron Gerard by proving himself useful in the hunt.","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to show off in front of Baron Gerard.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"009jd6buub6dj900","name":"Nicholas the Huntsman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nicholas the Huntsman","ownerKey":"nicholas-the-huntsman","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Nicholas the Huntsman - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to show off in front of Baron Gerard.</p>","positive":"I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to show off in front of Baron Gerard."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to show off in front of Baron Gerard.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Nicholas the Huntsman","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to show off in front of Baron Gerard.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00rzwip88piwzr00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nicholas the Huntsman","ownerKey":"nicholas-the-huntsman","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to show off in front of Baron Gerard.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Earn recognition from Baron Gerard by proving himself useful in the hunt.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to show off in front of Baron Gerard.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Earn recognition from Baron Gerard by proving himself useful in the hunt.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Nicholas the Huntsman","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00f3hbl99lbh3f00","name":"Nils the Poor Devil","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Nils the Poor Devil","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-nils-the-poor-devil","ownerKey":"nils-the-poor-devil","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Nils the Poor Devil","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Has diary revealing truth about Enar's punishment</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find way to bring Enar peace, guilt haunts me","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Old soldier who lost his legs in war</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Has diary revealing truth about Enar's punishment</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find way to bring Enar peace, guilt haunts me","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Old soldier who lost his legs in war</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00pqtf0110ftqp00","name":"Nils the Poor Devil - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nils the Poor Devil","ownerKey":"nils-the-poor-devil","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Nils the Poor Devil - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>Old soldier who lost his legs in war</p>","positive":"Old soldier who lost his legs in war"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Old soldier who lost his legs in war</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Nils the Poor Devil","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Old soldier who lost his legs in war","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0050yskaaksy0500","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nils the Poor Devil","ownerKey":"nils-the-poor-devil","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. Old soldier who lost his legs in war</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find way to bring Enar peace, guilt haunts me</p><p>Notes:<br>Has diary revealing truth about Enar's punishment</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. Old soldier who lost his legs in war</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find way to bring Enar peace, guilt haunts me</p><p>Notes:<br>Has diary revealing truth about Enar's punishment</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Nils the Poor Devil","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"0046hwmyymwh6400","name":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-olivier-the-raven-on-the-run","ownerKey":"olivier-the-raven-on-the-run","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Time-sensitive NPC - must be found before nightfall to save him. Will reveal the truth about Yvonne's death if put under pressure. Knows about Adrien's absinthe operation and connection to the Ravens.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Collect the money I have hidden in the catacombs and flee far from Paris before the fire spirit finds me","contact":"<p>A barely eighteen-year-old boy who works for Father Adrien as part of the Ravens, smugglers who transport absinthe through the catacombs. Olivier witnessed Adrien murder Yvonne but stayed silent. Now Yvonne's spirit is hunting him - his companion Thierry has already been burnt alive. Olivier confided in Adrien but realized the priest would do nothing to help him. Now desperately trying to collect his hidden money and leave the city before nightfall. If found before sunset, will be preparing his escape at the Ravens' Hideout. If not found in time, his charred corpse will be discovered after 10pm.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Time-sensitive NPC - must be found before nightfall to save him. Will reveal the truth about Yvonne's death if put under pressure. Knows about Adrien's absinthe operation and connection to the Ravens.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Collect the money I have hidden in the catacombs and flee far from Paris before the fire spirit finds me","contact":"<p>A barely eighteen-year-old boy who works for Father Adrien as part of the Ravens, smugglers who transport absinthe through the catacombs. Olivier witnessed Adrien murder Yvonne but stayed silent. Now Yvonne's spirit is hunting him - his companion Thierry has already been burnt alive. Olivier confided in Adrien but realized the priest would do nothing to help him. Now desperately trying to collect his hidden money and leave the city before nightfall. If found before sunset, will be preparing his escape at the Ravens' Hideout. If not found in time, his charred corpse will be discovered after 10pm.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00hub0d00d0buh00","name":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run","ownerKey":"olivier-the-raven-on-the-run","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job.</p>","positive":"I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01m7inerreni7m10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run","ownerKey":"olivier-the-raven-on-the-run","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A barely eighteen-year-old boy who works for Father Adrien as part of the Ravens, smugglers who transport absinthe through the catacombs. Olivier witnessed Adrien murder Yvonne but stayed silent. Now Yvonne's spirit is hunting him - his companion Thierry has already been burnt alive. Olivier confided in Adrien but realized the priest would do nothing to help him. Now desperately trying to collect his hidden money and leave the city before nightfall. If found before sunset, will be preparing his escape at the Ravens' Hideout. If not found in time, his charred corpse will be discovered after 10pm.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Collect the money I have hidden in the catacombs and flee far from Paris before the fire spirit finds me</p><p>Notes:<br>Time-sensitive NPC - must be found before nightfall to save him. Will reveal the truth about Yvonne's death if put under pressure. Knows about Adrien's absinthe operation and connection to the Ravens.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A barely eighteen-year-old boy who works for Father Adrien as part of the Ravens, smugglers who transport absinthe through the catacombs. Olivier witnessed Adrien murder Yvonne but stayed silent. Now Yvonne's spirit is hunting him - his companion Thierry has already been burnt alive. Olivier confided in Adrien but realized the priest would do nothing to help him. Now desperately trying to collect his hidden money and leave the city before nightfall. If found before sunset, will be preparing his escape at the Ravens' Hideout. If not found in time, his charred corpse will be discovered after 10pm.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I'm a thug always looking to fill my pockets with coin, no matter how dirty the job.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Collect the money I have hidden in the catacombs and flee far from Paris before the fire spirit finds me</p><p>Notes:<br>Time-sensitive NPC - must be found before nightfall to save him. Will reveal the truth about Yvonne's death if put under pressure. Knows about Adrien's absinthe operation and connection to the Ravens.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Olivier - The Raven on the Run","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01tk6siwwis6kt10","name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/cowled.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-ozena-dorothea-gray","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Muffled by her mask, tinged with pain and desperation<br>- Mannerisms: Keeps one hand on her mask, moves with purpose, eyes constantly scanning<br>- Motivation: She was a good person broken by suffering and manipulation<br>- Tragedy: Every witch she kills makes her more monstrous, but she's too desperate to stop<br>- Redemption: She can be saved if the Hunters show her the truth about Henkle</p><p>WHAT SHE KNOWS:<br>- Dr. Henkle can send people through time using the Compass Rose<br>- The Compass Rose needs all four pieces to function safely<br>- She's already killed Johanne and taken the North (Black) piece<br>- Henkle told her the witches are evil and must be eliminated</p><p>WHAT SHE DOESN'T KNOW:<br>- Henkle is lying about the witches being evil<br>- The incomplete Compass Rose is more dangerous than helpful<br>- Henkle plans to abandon her once he has what he needs<br>- Her actions are part of a larger scheme by the One Who Plots in the Shadows</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Collect all four pieces of the Compass Rose\nGet home to my own time\nFind a cure for my disease","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Muffled by her mask, tinged with pain and desperation<br>- Mannerisms: Keeps one hand on her mask, moves with purpose, eyes constantly scanning<br>- Motivation: She was a good person broken by suffering and manipulation<br>- Tragedy: Every witch she kills makes her more monstrous, but she's too desperate to stop<br>- Redemption: She can be saved if the Hunters show her the truth about Henkle</p><p>WHAT SHE KNOWS:<br>- Dr. Henkle can send people through time using the Compass Rose<br>- The Compass Rose needs all four pieces to function safely<br>- She's already killed Johanne and taken the North (Black) piece<br>- Henkle told her the witches are evil and must be eliminated</p><p>WHAT SHE DOESN'T KNOW:<br>- Henkle is lying about the witches being evil<br>- The incomplete Compass Rose is more dangerous than helpful<br>- Henkle plans to abandon her once he has what he needs<br>- Her actions are part of a larger scheme by the One Who Plots in the Shadows</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Collect all four pieces of the Compass Rose\nGet home to my own time\nFind a cure for my disease","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"016ljseuuesjl610","name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life</p>","positive":"I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00w6naq22qan6w00","name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I was thrown back in time, and the only way home is to gather the pieces of the Compass Rose</p>","positive":"I was thrown back in time, and the only way home is to gather the pieces of the Compass Rose"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I was thrown back in time, and the only way home is to gather the pieces of the Compass Rose</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I was thrown back in time, and the only way home is to gather the pieces of the Compass Rose","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01m7x59ii95x7m10","name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray) - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder</p>","positive":"I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00uo5ugkkgu5ou00","name":"The Silver Slippers - Short-Range Teleport","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Silver Slippers - Short-Range Teleport","system":{"description":"<p>Once per Exchange, OZena can teleport up to 30 feet to any location she can see. This doesn't count as an action and can be used to avoid attacks or reposition instantly.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Exchange, OZena can teleport up to 30 feet to any location she can see. This doesn't count as an action and can be used to avoid attacks or reposition instantly.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01fi4a1ff1a4if10","name":"The Silver Slippers - Long-Distance Teleport","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Silver Slippers - Long-Distance Teleport","system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, OZena can teleport to any location within 1 mile that she has previously visited. This requires her full action. The Silver Slippers are permanently attached to her feet and cannot be removed without killing her.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, OZena can teleport to any location within 1 mile that she has previously visited. This requires her full action. The Silver Slippers are permanently attached to her feet and cannot be removed without killing her.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01wmmbn44nbmmw10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","ownerKey":"ozena-dorothea-gray","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Dorothea Gray grew up in early 1900s America with dreams of becoming a doctor. Her life was destroyed when she contracted ozena—a terrible disease that slowly destroyed her nasal cavity, leaving her face disfigured. Desperate for a cure, she sought out Dr. Norman Henkle, who possessed a partially completed artifact called the Compass Rose. The incomplete artifact malfunctioned, throwing Dorothea and three other patients backward in time to 1780 Germany. Dr. Henkle convinced the desperate Dorothea that four witches held the pieces of the Compass Rose and were evil, and that killing them was necessary to return home. Dorothea became OZena—a killer who has already murdered Johanne in Schiltach. Her face is horribly disfigured, with her nose completely gone. She covers the lower half of her face with a silver mask. She wears enchanted Silver Slippers that allow her to teleport.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life<br>2. I was thrown back in time, and the only way home is to gather the pieces of the Compass Rose<br>3. I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder</p><p>Agenda:<br>Collect all four pieces of the Compass Rose<br>Get home to my own time<br>Find a cure for my disease</p><p>Gifts:<br>The Silver Slippers - Short-Range Teleport: Once per Exchange, OZena can teleport up to 30 feet to any location she can see. This doesn't count as an action and can be used to avoid attacks or reposition instantly.<br>The Silver Slippers - Long-Distance Teleport: Once per Scene, OZena can teleport to any location within 1 mile that she has previously visited. This requires her full action. The Silver Slippers are permanently attached to her feet and cannot be removed without killing her.</p><p>Notes:<br>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Muffled by her mask, tinged with pain and desperation<br>- Mannerisms: Keeps one hand on her mask, moves with purpose, eyes constantly scanning<br>- Motivation: She was a good person broken by suffering and manipulation<br>- Tragedy: Every witch she kills makes her more monstrous, but she's too desperate to stop<br>- Redemption: She can be saved if the Hunters show her the truth about Henkle</p><p>WHAT SHE KNOWS:<br>- Dr. Henkle can send people through time using the Compass Rose<br>- The Compass Rose needs all four pieces to function safely<br>- She's already killed Johanne and taken the North (Black) piece<br>- Henkle told her the witches are evil and must be eliminated</p><p>WHAT SHE DOESN'T KNOW:<br>- Henkle is lying about the witches being evil<br>- The incomplete Compass Rose is more dangerous than helpful<br>- Henkle plans to abandon her once he has what he needs<br>- Her actions are part of a larger scheme by the One Who Plots in the Shadows</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Dorothea Gray grew up in early 1900s America with dreams of becoming a doctor. Her life was destroyed when she contracted ozena—a terrible disease that slowly destroyed her nasal cavity, leaving her face disfigured. Desperate for a cure, she sought out Dr. Norman Henkle, who possessed a partially completed artifact called the Compass Rose. The incomplete artifact malfunctioned, throwing Dorothea and three other patients backward in time to 1780 Germany. Dr. Henkle convinced the desperate Dorothea that four witches held the pieces of the Compass Rose and were evil, and that killing them was necessary to return home. Dorothea became OZena—a killer who has already murdered Johanne in Schiltach. Her face is horribly disfigured, with her nose completely gone. She covers the lower half of her face with a silver mask. She wears enchanted Silver Slippers that allow her to teleport.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life<br>2. I was thrown back in time, and the only way home is to gather the pieces of the Compass Rose<br>3. I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder</p><p>Agenda:<br>Collect all four pieces of the Compass Rose<br>Get home to my own time<br>Find a cure for my disease</p><p>Gifts:<br>The Silver Slippers - Short-Range Teleport: Once per Exchange, OZena can teleport up to 30 feet to any location she can see. This doesn't count as an action and can be used to avoid attacks or reposition instantly.<br>The Silver Slippers - Long-Distance Teleport: Once per Scene, OZena can teleport to any location within 1 mile that she has previously visited. This requires her full action. The Silver Slippers are permanently attached to her feet and cannot be removed without killing her.</p><p>Notes:<br>ROLEPLAYING:<br>- Voice: Muffled by her mask, tinged with pain and desperation<br>- Mannerisms: Keeps one hand on her mask, moves with purpose, eyes constantly scanning<br>- Motivation: She was a good person broken by suffering and manipulation<br>- Tragedy: Every witch she kills makes her more monstrous, but she's too desperate to stop<br>- Redemption: She can be saved if the Hunters show her the truth about Henkle</p><p>WHAT SHE KNOWS:<br>- Dr. Henkle can send people through time using the Compass Rose<br>- The Compass Rose needs all four pieces to function safely<br>- She's already killed Johanne and taken the North (Black) piece<br>- Henkle told her the witches are evil and must be eliminated</p><p>WHAT SHE DOESN'T KNOW:<br>- Henkle is lying about the witches being evil<br>- The incomplete Compass Rose is more dangerous than helpful<br>- Henkle plans to abandon her once he has what he needs<br>- Her actions are part of a larger scheme by the One Who Plots in the Shadows</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01aguagyygauga10","name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","type":"villager","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-scream-tan.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-scream-tan.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-porcelain-dolls-blood-bound-servants","ownerKey":"porcelain-dolls-blood-bound-servants","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>There are twelve Porcelain Dolls total, but they typically don't all attack at once. Roll 1d6 for each Doll encountered to determine their weapon type. The Dolls fight with mechanical precision but no creativity—they follow the Princess's commands exactly. If freed from blood magic control (via Infusion of Purity), they panic and flee or provide information about Helga's mansion layout. Some may beg the Hunters to save their families who are also held captive in Rot.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>We are the blood-bound servants</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>There are twelve Porcelain Dolls total, but they typically don't all attack at once. Roll 1d6 for each Doll encountered to determine their weapon type. The Dolls fight with mechanical precision but no creativity—they follow the Princess's commands exactly. If freed from blood magic control (via Infusion of Purity), they panic and flee or provide information about Helga's mansion layout. Some may beg the Hunters to save their families who are also held captive in Rot.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>We are the blood-bound servants</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"015y3y9009y3y510","name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","ownerKey":"porcelain-dolls-blood-bound-servants","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are the blood-bound servants</p>","positive":"We are the blood-bound servants"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the blood-bound servants</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are the blood-bound servants","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0126il4aa4li6210","name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","ownerKey":"porcelain-dolls-blood-bound-servants","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Our wills are not our own</p>","positive":"Our wills are not our own"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Our wills are not our own</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Our wills are not our own","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0149x3esse3x9410","name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","ownerKey":"porcelain-dolls-blood-bound-servants","itemKey":"descriptor2.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>We move only when commanded</p>","positive":"We move only when commanded"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We move only when commanded</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.aldeano","owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We move only when commanded","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01pnswcaacwsnp10","name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","ownerKey":"porcelain-dolls-blood-bound-servants","itemKey":"descriptor3.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>Behind the masks we are just ordinary people</p>","positive":"Behind the masks we are just ordinary people"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Behind the masks we are just ordinary people</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.aldeano","owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Behind the masks we are just ordinary people","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01nf9nlaaln9fn10","name":"Armed Guard","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","ownerKey":"porcelain-dolls-blood-bound-servants","itemKey":"don1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Armed Guard","system":{"description":"<p>Each Porcelain Doll carries one of six weapon types (roll 1d6 to determine): **1-Spear:** Can attack from 10 feet away. **2-Double Weapon:** Can attack twice in one Exchange. **3-Great Blade:** Inflicts 1 additional Wound on successful hit. **4-Whip:** Can disarm opponents (contested Check). **5-Soaked Weapon:** Poisoned blade—victim takes 1 Wound at start of next Exchange. **6-Shield:** Has +1 Defense against physical attacks.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Each Porcelain Doll carries one of six weapon types (roll 1d6 to determine): **1-Spear:** Can attack from 10 feet away. **2-Double Weapon:** Can attack twice in one Exchange. **3-Great Blade:** Inflicts 1 additional Wound on successful hit. **4-Whip:** Can disarm opponents (contested Check). **5-Soaked Weapon:** Poisoned blade—victim takes 1 Wound at start of next Exchange. **6-Shield:** Has +1 Defense against physical attacks.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.aldeano","owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","category":"Villager Gift","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01jxgxnffnxgxj10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","ownerKey":"porcelain-dolls-blood-bound-servants","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are the blood-bound servants<br>2. Our wills are not our own<br>3. We move only when commanded<br>4. Behind the masks we are just ordinary people</p><p>Gifts:<br>Armed Guard: Each Porcelain Doll carries one of six weapon types (roll 1d6 to determine): **1-Spear:** Can attack from 10 feet away. **2-Double Weapon:** Can attack twice in one Exchange. **3-Great Blade:** Inflicts 1 additional Wound on successful hit. **4-Whip:** Can disarm opponents (contested Check). **5-Soaked Weapon:** Poisoned blade—victim takes 1 Wound at start of next Exchange. **6-Shield:** Has +1 Defense against physical attacks.</p><p>Notes:<br>There are twelve Porcelain Dolls total, but they typically don't all attack at once. Roll 1d6 for each Doll encountered to determine their weapon type. The Dolls fight with mechanical precision but no creativity—they follow the Princess's commands exactly. If freed from blood magic control (via Infusion of Purity), they panic and flee or provide information about Helga's mansion layout. Some may beg the Hunters to save their families who are also held captive in Rot.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are the blood-bound servants<br>2. Our wills are not our own<br>3. We move only when commanded<br>4. Behind the masks we are just ordinary people</p><p>Gifts:<br>Armed Guard: Each Porcelain Doll carries one of six weapon types (roll 1d6 to determine): **1-Spear:** Can attack from 10 feet away. **2-Double Weapon:** Can attack twice in one Exchange. **3-Great Blade:** Inflicts 1 additional Wound on successful hit. **4-Whip:** Can disarm opponents (contested Check). **5-Soaked Weapon:** Poisoned blade—victim takes 1 Wound at start of next Exchange. **6-Shield:** Has +1 Defense against physical attacks.</p><p>Notes:<br>There are twelve Porcelain Dolls total, but they typically don't all attack at once. Roll 1d6 for each Doll encountered to determine their weapon type. The Dolls fight with mechanical precision but no creativity—they follow the Princess's commands exactly. If freed from blood magic control (via Infusion of Purity), they panic and flee or provide information about Helga's mansion layout. Some may beg the Hunters to save their families who are also held captive in Rot.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Porcelain Dolls - Blood-Bound Servants","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"0169pa6996ap9610","name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-white-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-white-blue.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-porcelain-princess-the-disfigured-noblewoman","ownerKey":"porcelain-princess-the-disfigured-noblewoman","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>The Porcelain Princess holds the key to Helga's mansion and knows the ritual schedule. If the Infusion of Purity is used on her, she's freed from blood magic control and may become an ally, revealing the truth about Helga's corruption. She carries a vial of blood that glows—this is OZena's blood, being prepared for the ritual. The Princess genuinely believed Helga would restore her beauty but has been betrayed like all of Helga's servants.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>The Porcelain Princess holds the key to Helga's mansion and knows the ritual schedule. If the Infusion of Purity is used on her, she's freed from blood magic control and may become an ally, revealing the truth about Helga's corruption. She carries a vial of blood that glows—this is OZena's blood, being prepared for the ritual. The Princess genuinely believed Helga would restore her beauty but has been betrayed like all of Helga's servants.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00q5plz88zlp5q00","name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","ownerKey":"porcelain-princess-the-disfigured-noblewoman","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I was a noblewoman disfigured by disease</p>","positive":"I was a noblewoman disfigured by disease"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I was a noblewoman disfigured by disease</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I was a noblewoman disfigured by disease","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00gqefb66bfeqg00","name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","ownerKey":"porcelain-princess-the-disfigured-noblewoman","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Society rejected me, so I embraced Helga's offer</p>","positive":"Society rejected me, so I embraced Helga's offer"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Society rejected me, so I embraced Helga's offer</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Society rejected me, so I embraced Helga's offer","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00hxxbhkkhbxxh00","name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","ownerKey":"porcelain-princess-the-disfigured-noblewoman","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Power in exchange for service</p>","positive":"Power in exchange for service"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Power in exchange for service</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Power in exchange for service","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01633iu66ui33610","name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","ownerKey":"porcelain-princess-the-disfigured-noblewoman","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I manage her cult and keep the villagers in line</p>","positive":"I manage her cult and keep the villagers in line"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I manage her cult and keep the villagers in line</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I manage her cult and keep the villagers in line","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00jb4wgoogw4bj00","name":"Cult Leader","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","ownerKey":"porcelain-princess-the-disfigured-noblewoman","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Cult Leader","system":{"description":"<p>The Porcelain Princess commands the Porcelain Dolls with perfect coordination. As long as she lives and can see them, the Dolls act with +1 OL when following her direct commands. She can command all twelve Dolls to move as a single coordinated unit, creating tactical advantages in combat. If she's killed or incapacitated, the Dolls become disoriented and act independently at their base OL.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Porcelain Princess commands the Porcelain Dolls with perfect coordination. As long as she lives and can see them, the Dolls act with +1 OL when following her direct commands. She can command all twelve Dolls to move as a single coordinated unit, creating tactical advantages in combat. If she's killed or incapacitated, the Dolls become disoriented and act independently at their base OL.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00ztwisttsiwtz00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","ownerKey":"porcelain-princess-the-disfigured-noblewoman","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I was a noblewoman disfigured by disease<br>2. Society rejected me, so I embraced Helga's offer<br>3. Power in exchange for service<br>4. I manage her cult and keep the villagers in line</p><p>Gifts:<br>Cult Leader: The Porcelain Princess commands the Porcelain Dolls with perfect coordination. As long as she lives and can see them, the Dolls act with +1 OL when following her direct commands. She can command all twelve Dolls to move as a single coordinated unit, creating tactical advantages in combat. If she's killed or incapacitated, the Dolls become disoriented and act independently at their base OL.</p><p>Notes:<br>The Porcelain Princess holds the key to Helga's mansion and knows the ritual schedule. If the Infusion of Purity is used on her, she's freed from blood magic control and may become an ally, revealing the truth about Helga's corruption. She carries a vial of blood that glows—this is OZena's blood, being prepared for the ritual. The Princess genuinely believed Helga would restore her beauty but has been betrayed like all of Helga's servants.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I was a noblewoman disfigured by disease<br>2. Society rejected me, so I embraced Helga's offer<br>3. Power in exchange for service<br>4. I manage her cult and keep the villagers in line</p><p>Gifts:<br>Cult Leader: The Porcelain Princess commands the Porcelain Dolls with perfect coordination. As long as she lives and can see them, the Dolls act with +1 OL when following her direct commands. She can command all twelve Dolls to move as a single coordinated unit, creating tactical advantages in combat. If she's killed or incapacitated, the Dolls become disoriented and act independently at their base OL.</p><p>Notes:<br>The Porcelain Princess holds the key to Helga's mansion and knows the ritual schedule. If the Infusion of Purity is used on her, she's freed from blood magic control and may become an ally, revealing the truth about Helga's corruption. She carries a vial of blood that glows—this is OZena's blood, being prepared for the ritual. The Princess genuinely believed Helga would restore her beauty but has been betrayed like all of Helga's servants.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00fijbynnybjif00","name":"Rabbit Automaton","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/magical/construct-iron-stomping-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Rabbit Automaton","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/magical/construct-iron-stomping-yellow.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-rabbit-automaton","ownerKey":"rabbit-automaton","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Rabbit Automaton","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>One of two automatons built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created out of loneliness to serve as a pretend tea companion, this mechanical rabbit is equipped with powerful legs that allow it to make devastating leaps. It serves its creator faithfully, defending him from any who would disturb his solitude.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>One of two automatons built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created out of loneliness to serve as a pretend tea companion, this mechanical rabbit is equipped with powerful legs that allow it to make devastating leaps. It serves its creator faithfully, defending him from any who would disturb his solitude.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00cc2cvmmvc2cc00","name":"Rabbit Automaton - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Rabbit Automaton","ownerKey":"rabbit-automaton","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Rabbit Automaton - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter</p>","positive":"I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Rabbit Automaton","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01q9ogakkago9q10","name":"Rabbit Automaton - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Rabbit Automaton","ownerKey":"rabbit-automaton","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Rabbit Automaton - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible jumps and crush everything when landing</p>","positive":"Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible jumps and crush everything when landing"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible jumps and crush everything when landing</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Rabbit Automaton","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible jumps and crush everything when landing","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0123fcbrrbcf3210","name":"Leap","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Rabbit Automaton","ownerKey":"rabbit-automaton","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Leap","system":{"description":"<p>When it acts, the Automaton can free itself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. If it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the attack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be knocked to the ground.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>When it acts, the Automaton can free itself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. If it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the attack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be knocked to the ground.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Rabbit Automaton","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00zcln3ff3nlcz00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Rabbit Automaton","ownerKey":"rabbit-automaton","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>One of two automatons built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created out of loneliness to serve as a pretend tea companion, this mechanical rabbit is equipped with powerful legs that allow it to make devastating leaps. It serves its creator faithfully, defending him from any who would disturb his solitude.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter<br>2. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible jumps and crush everything when landing</p><p>Gifts:<br>Leap: When it acts, the Automaton can free itself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. If it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the attack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be knocked to the ground.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>One of two automatons built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created out of loneliness to serve as a pretend tea companion, this mechanical rabbit is equipped with powerful legs that allow it to make devastating leaps. It serves its creator faithfully, defending him from any who would disturb his solitude.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter<br>2. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible jumps and crush everything when landing</p><p>Gifts:<br>Leap: When it acts, the Automaton can free itself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. If it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the attack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be knocked to the ground.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Rabbit Automaton","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00zwes3jj3sewz00","name":"Restless Spirit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Restless Spirit","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/pawprint.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-restless-spirit","ownerKey":"restless-spirit","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Restless Spirit","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":"<p>Common enemies in the catacombs. Can only be permanently damaged by magic. Useful for conveying information about Yvonne if Hunters can communicate with spirits.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"We sense Yvonne's wrath, driving us to prey on the living","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":"<p>Common enemies in the catacombs. Can only be permanently damaged by magic. Useful for conveying information about Yvonne if Hunters can communicate with spirits.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"We sense Yvonne's wrath, driving us to prey on the living","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"004cd00mm00dc400","name":"Restless Spirit - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Restless Spirit","ownerKey":"restless-spirit","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Restless Spirit - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are restless souls and yearn for the essence of the living.</p>","positive":"We are restless souls and yearn for the essence of the living."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are restless souls and yearn for the essence of the living.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Restless Spirit","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are restless souls and yearn for the essence of the living.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"011gj3oeeo3jg110","name":"Spirit","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Restless Spirit","ownerKey":"restless-spirit","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Spirit","system":{"description":"<p>This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by non-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, when the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical means.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by non-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, when the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical means.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Restless Spirit","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01t6mwahhawm6t10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Restless Spirit","ownerKey":"restless-spirit","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Restless souls that roam the Catacombs of Paris, particularly concentrated in the Halls of the Spirits. These spirits yearn for the life energy of the living and will not hesitate to target them. They are influenced by Yvonne's wrath and anger. Yvonne can summon 3 of these spirits once per Scene to obey her will. Hunters with the Voice of the Spirits Gift can communicate with them to learn of Yvonne's presence.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are restless souls and yearn for the essence of the living.</p><p>Agenda:<br>We sense Yvonne's wrath, driving us to prey on the living</p><p>Gifts:<br>Spirit: This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by non-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, when the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical means.</p><p>Notes:<br>Common enemies in the catacombs. Can only be permanently damaged by magic. Useful for conveying information about Yvonne if Hunters can communicate with spirits.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Restless souls that roam the Catacombs of Paris, particularly concentrated in the Halls of the Spirits. These spirits yearn for the life energy of the living and will not hesitate to target them. They are influenced by Yvonne's wrath and anger. Yvonne can summon 3 of these spirits once per Scene to obey her will. Hunters with the Voice of the Spirits Gift can communicate with them to learn of Yvonne's presence.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are restless souls and yearn for the essence of the living.</p><p>Agenda:<br>We sense Yvonne's wrath, driving us to prey on the living</p><p>Gifts:<br>Spirit: This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by non-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, when the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical means.</p><p>Notes:<br>Common enemies in the catacombs. Can only be permanently damaged by magic. Useful for conveying information about Yvonne if Hunters can communicate with spirits.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Restless Spirit","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01mub3iggi3bum10","name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-crystal-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-crystal-blue.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-saint-demetrius-the-guardian","ownerKey":"saint-demetrius-the-guardian","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Demetrius is Paladin #2 (roll 1d6 to determine which appears). His protective nature can be exploited—threaten his allies to force him to take wounds, potentially eliminating him while making him more dangerous. He always positions between enemies and allies, especially protecting Saint Martha. Works best with other Paladins as he has allies to protect. If isolated, loses much of his effectiveness. Can't be reasoned with—duty and protection are absolute. Voice: Calm and resolute, reassuring to allies. Mannerisms: Shield raised, defensive stance, watches for threats to allies.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Demetrius is Paladin #2 (roll 1d6 to determine which appears). His protective nature can be exploited—threaten his allies to force him to take wounds, potentially eliminating him while making him more dangerous. He always positions between enemies and allies, especially protecting Saint Martha. Works best with other Paladins as he has allies to protect. If isolated, loses much of his effectiveness. Can't be reasoned with—duty and protection are absolute. Voice: Calm and resolute, reassuring to allies. Mannerisms: Shield raised, defensive stance, watches for threats to allies.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00orsdd99ddsro00","name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","ownerKey":"saint-demetrius-the-guardian","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ok5kz55zk5ko00","name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","ownerKey":"saint-demetrius-the-guardian","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","positive":"His word, for me, is law"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"His word, for me, is law","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00v3u403304u3v00","name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","ownerKey":"saint-demetrius-the-guardian","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00mmgrz11zrgmm00","name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","ownerKey":"saint-demetrius-the-guardian","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I put the defense of my companions before my own life</p>","positive":"I put the defense of my companions before my own life"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I put the defense of my companions before my own life</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I put the defense of my companions before my own life","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ysxqurruqxsy00","name":"Paladin - Guardian","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","ownerKey":"saint-demetrius-the-guardian","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Paladin - Guardian","system":{"description":"<p>Once per Exchange, Demetrius can take 1 Wound in place of one of his allies (must be within 30 feet and line of sight). When he does this, he increases his Opposition Level by 1 for the rest of the Scene (cumulative—if he takes wounds multiple Scenes, the bonuses stack). This makes him progressively more dangerous as he sacrifices himself. The wound transfer happens automatically if Demetrius chooses—the ally takes no damage, and Demetrius takes the full wound instead.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Exchange, Demetrius can take 1 Wound in place of one of his allies (must be within 30 feet and line of sight). When he does this, he increases his Opposition Level by 1 for the rest of the Scene (cumulative—if he takes wounds multiple Scenes, the bonuses stack). This makes him progressively more dangerous as he sacrifices himself. The wound transfer happens automatically if Demetrius chooses—the ally takes no damage, and Demetrius takes the full wound instead.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00tn468ii864nt00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","ownerKey":"saint-demetrius-the-guardian","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. I put the defense of my companions before my own life</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Guardian: Once per Exchange, Demetrius can take 1 Wound in place of one of his allies (must be within 30 feet and line of sight). When he does this, he increases his Opposition Level by 1 for the rest of the Scene (cumulative—if he takes wounds multiple Scenes, the bonuses stack). This makes him progressively more dangerous as he sacrifices himself. The wound transfer happens automatically if Demetrius chooses—the ally takes no damage, and Demetrius takes the full wound instead.</p><p>Notes:<br>Demetrius is Paladin #2 (roll 1d6 to determine which appears). His protective nature can be exploited—threaten his allies to force him to take wounds, potentially eliminating him while making him more dangerous. He always positions between enemies and allies, especially protecting Saint Martha. Works best with other Paladins as he has allies to protect. If isolated, loses much of his effectiveness. Can't be reasoned with—duty and protection are absolute. Voice: Calm and resolute, reassuring to allies. Mannerisms: Shield raised, defensive stance, watches for threats to allies.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. I put the defense of my companions before my own life</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Guardian: Once per Exchange, Demetrius can take 1 Wound in place of one of his allies (must be within 30 feet and line of sight). When he does this, he increases his Opposition Level by 1 for the rest of the Scene (cumulative—if he takes wounds multiple Scenes, the bonuses stack). This makes him progressively more dangerous as he sacrifices himself. The wound transfer happens automatically if Demetrius chooses—the ally takes no damage, and Demetrius takes the full wound instead.</p><p>Notes:<br>Demetrius is Paladin #2 (roll 1d6 to determine which appears). His protective nature can be exploited—threaten his allies to force him to take wounds, potentially eliminating him while making him more dangerous. He always positions between enemies and allies, especially protecting Saint Martha. Works best with other Paladins as he has allies to protect. If isolated, loses much of his effectiveness. Can't be reasoned with—duty and protection are absolute. Voice: Calm and resolute, reassuring to allies. Mannerisms: Shield raised, defensive stance, watches for threats to allies.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00nribkddkbirn00","name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","type":"threat","img":"icons/weapons/polearms/spear-hooked-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/weapons/polearms/spear-hooked-gold.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-saint-margaret-the-ambitious","ownerKey":"saint-margaret-the-ambitious","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Margaret is Paladin #6 (roll 1d6 to determine). MOST DANGEROUS in prolonged battles—gains +1 OL per Saint George Wound, bonus action when he's hurt. Secret ambition to overthrow Saint George makes her exploitable: can make deals with Hunters, reveal her treachery to cause Paladin discord, or deliberately empower her by wounding Saint George to make her uncontrollable. Most likely to negotiate with Hunters but LEAST trustworthy—ambition trumps honor. Brilliant, ruthless, calculating. Voice: Smooth, confident, hints of superiority. Mannerisms: Watches Saint George constantly, smiles when he's wounded, calculates constantly.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Margaret is Paladin #6 (roll 1d6 to determine). MOST DANGEROUS in prolonged battles—gains +1 OL per Saint George Wound, bonus action when he's hurt. Secret ambition to overthrow Saint George makes her exploitable: can make deals with Hunters, reveal her treachery to cause Paladin discord, or deliberately empower her by wounding Saint George to make her uncontrollable. Most likely to negotiate with Hunters but LEAST trustworthy—ambition trumps honor. Brilliant, ruthless, calculating. Voice: Smooth, confident, hints of superiority. Mannerisms: Watches Saint George constantly, smiles when he's wounded, calculates constantly.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01f7lmattaml7f10","name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","ownerKey":"saint-margaret-the-ambitious","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"011ns2dbbd2sn110","name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","ownerKey":"saint-margaret-the-ambitious","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","positive":"His word, for me, is law"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"His word, for me, is law","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01b3gv8558vg3b10","name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","ownerKey":"saint-margaret-the-ambitious","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00szcjmjjmjczs00","name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","ownerKey":"saint-margaret-the-ambitious","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I want to affirm my role in the Church and overthrow that arrogant Saint George</p>","positive":"I want to affirm my role in the Church and overthrow that arrogant Saint George"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I want to affirm my role in the Church and overthrow that arrogant Saint George</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I want to affirm my role in the Church and overthrow that arrogant Saint George","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0126kaheehak6210","name":"Paladin - Ambition","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","ownerKey":"saint-margaret-the-ambitious","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Paladin - Ambition","system":{"description":"<p>Margaret increases her Opposition Level by 1 for each Wound that Saint George has suffered (if Saint George has 2 Wounds, Margaret's OL becomes 7). Once per Scene, when Saint George suffers 1 Wound, Margaret can immediately perform 1 additional action as she seizes the opportunity. This makes Margaret progressively more dangerous as battles wear on and Saint George is weakened, potentially making her more powerful than her master by the end of a prolonged fight.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Margaret increases her Opposition Level by 1 for each Wound that Saint George has suffered (if Saint George has 2 Wounds, Margaret's OL becomes 7). Once per Scene, when Saint George suffers 1 Wound, Margaret can immediately perform 1 additional action as she seizes the opportunity. This makes Margaret progressively more dangerous as battles wear on and Saint George is weakened, potentially making her more powerful than her master by the end of a prolonged fight.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"017q6jxddxj6q710","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","ownerKey":"saint-margaret-the-ambitious","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. I want to affirm my role in the Church and overthrow that arrogant Saint George</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Ambition: Margaret increases her Opposition Level by 1 for each Wound that Saint George has suffered (if Saint George has 2 Wounds, Margaret's OL becomes 7). Once per Scene, when Saint George suffers 1 Wound, Margaret can immediately perform 1 additional action as she seizes the opportunity. This makes Margaret progressively more dangerous as battles wear on and Saint George is weakened, potentially making her more powerful than her master by the end of a prolonged fight.</p><p>Notes:<br>Margaret is Paladin #6 (roll 1d6 to determine). MOST DANGEROUS in prolonged battles—gains +1 OL per Saint George Wound, bonus action when he's hurt. Secret ambition to overthrow Saint George makes her exploitable: can make deals with Hunters, reveal her treachery to cause Paladin discord, or deliberately empower her by wounding Saint George to make her uncontrollable. Most likely to negotiate with Hunters but LEAST trustworthy—ambition trumps honor. Brilliant, ruthless, calculating. Voice: Smooth, confident, hints of superiority. Mannerisms: Watches Saint George constantly, smiles when he's wounded, calculates constantly.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. I want to affirm my role in the Church and overthrow that arrogant Saint George</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Ambition: Margaret increases her Opposition Level by 1 for each Wound that Saint George has suffered (if Saint George has 2 Wounds, Margaret's OL becomes 7). Once per Scene, when Saint George suffers 1 Wound, Margaret can immediately perform 1 additional action as she seizes the opportunity. This makes Margaret progressively more dangerous as battles wear on and Saint George is weakened, potentially making her more powerful than her master by the end of a prolonged fight.</p><p>Notes:<br>Margaret is Paladin #6 (roll 1d6 to determine). MOST DANGEROUS in prolonged battles—gains +1 OL per Saint George Wound, bonus action when he's hurt. Secret ambition to overthrow Saint George makes her exploitable: can make deals with Hunters, reveal her treachery to cause Paladin discord, or deliberately empower her by wounding Saint George to make her uncontrollable. Most likely to negotiate with Hunters but LEAST trustworthy—ambition trumps honor. Brilliant, ruthless, calculating. Voice: Smooth, confident, hints of superiority. Mannerisms: Watches Saint George constantly, smiles when he's wounded, calculates constantly.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01vzpfpnnpfpzv10","name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/holy/angel-winged-humanoid-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/magic/holy/angel-winged-humanoid-blue.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-saint-martha-the-friendly","ownerKey":"saint-martha-the-friendly","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Martha is Paladin #4 (roll 1d6 to determine). KEY CHARACTER for peaceful resolution—she doubts Saint George's Witch Hunt and can be convinced to help Hunters. Shows compassion, believes in understanding rather than destruction. If shown evidence of manipulation or witnesses Hunters' good deeds, may speak for them or actively assist. Protected by Gift when with other Paladins (2 Penalties to attack her). Most likely to betray Saint George out of higher loyalty to justice. Can be the bridge to redemption. Voice: Gentle, questioning, compassionate. Mannerisms: Hesitates before violence, shows concern for all parties.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Martha is Paladin #4 (roll 1d6 to determine). KEY CHARACTER for peaceful resolution—she doubts Saint George's Witch Hunt and can be convinced to help Hunters. Shows compassion, believes in understanding rather than destruction. If shown evidence of manipulation or witnesses Hunters' good deeds, may speak for them or actively assist. Protected by Gift when with other Paladins (2 Penalties to attack her). Most likely to betray Saint George out of higher loyalty to justice. Can be the bridge to redemption. Voice: Gentle, questioning, compassionate. Mannerisms: Hesitates before violence, shows concern for all parties.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00x8qeunnueq8x00","name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","ownerKey":"saint-martha-the-friendly","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00zktwpxxpwtkz00","name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","ownerKey":"saint-martha-the-friendly","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","positive":"His word, for me, is law"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"His word, for me, is law","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00sul2gttg2lus00","name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","ownerKey":"saint-martha-the-friendly","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00zn2d6pp6d2nz00","name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","ownerKey":"saint-martha-the-friendly","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I do not think Broken Tales should be eradicated, only understood</p>","positive":"I do not think Broken Tales should be eradicated, only understood"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I do not think Broken Tales should be eradicated, only understood</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I do not think Broken Tales should be eradicated, only understood","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"011ccro88orcc110","name":"Paladin - Friendly","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","ownerKey":"saint-martha-the-friendly","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Paladin - Friendly","system":{"description":"<p>Any Hunter who acts against Martha when there are other Paladins as potential targets will receive 2 Penalties on their action. This represents both Martha's non-threatening demeanor that makes it psychologically difficult to attack her, and her positioning that makes her a harder target when allies are nearby. This only applies when at least one other Paladin is present and available as a target—if Martha is isolated, she loses this protection.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Any Hunter who acts against Martha when there are other Paladins as potential targets will receive 2 Penalties on their action. This represents both Martha's non-threatening demeanor that makes it psychologically difficult to attack her, and her positioning that makes her a harder target when allies are nearby. This only applies when at least one other Paladin is present and available as a target—if Martha is isolated, she loses this protection.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00t2fyg99gyf2t00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","ownerKey":"saint-martha-the-friendly","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. I do not think Broken Tales should be eradicated, only understood</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Friendly: Any Hunter who acts against Martha when there are other Paladins as potential targets will receive 2 Penalties on their action. This represents both Martha's non-threatening demeanor that makes it psychologically difficult to attack her, and her positioning that makes her a harder target when allies are nearby. This only applies when at least one other Paladin is present and available as a target—if Martha is isolated, she loses this protection.</p><p>Notes:<br>Martha is Paladin #4 (roll 1d6 to determine). KEY CHARACTER for peaceful resolution—she doubts Saint George's Witch Hunt and can be convinced to help Hunters. Shows compassion, believes in understanding rather than destruction. If shown evidence of manipulation or witnesses Hunters' good deeds, may speak for them or actively assist. Protected by Gift when with other Paladins (2 Penalties to attack her). Most likely to betray Saint George out of higher loyalty to justice. Can be the bridge to redemption. Voice: Gentle, questioning, compassionate. Mannerisms: Hesitates before violence, shows concern for all parties.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. I do not think Broken Tales should be eradicated, only understood</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Friendly: Any Hunter who acts against Martha when there are other Paladins as potential targets will receive 2 Penalties on their action. This represents both Martha's non-threatening demeanor that makes it psychologically difficult to attack her, and her positioning that makes her a harder target when allies are nearby. This only applies when at least one other Paladin is present and available as a target—if Martha is isolated, she loses this protection.</p><p>Notes:<br>Martha is Paladin #4 (roll 1d6 to determine). KEY CHARACTER for peaceful resolution—she doubts Saint George's Witch Hunt and can be convinced to help Hunters. Shows compassion, believes in understanding rather than destruction. If shown evidence of manipulation or witnesses Hunters' good deeds, may speak for them or actively assist. Protected by Gift when with other Paladins (2 Penalties to attack her). Most likely to betray Saint George out of higher loyalty to justice. Can be the bridge to redemption. Voice: Gentle, questioning, compassionate. Mannerisms: Hesitates before violence, shows concern for all parties.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01hfgtbuubtgfh10","name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-bascinet-reinforced.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/helm-bascinet-reinforced.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-saint-syrus-the-veteran","ownerKey":"saint-syrus-the-veteran","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Syrus is Paladin #5 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous to Gift-reliant Hunters—can negate one Gift per Scene. Has countermeasures for almost everything due to decades of experience. Stubborn and dismissive of others' judgment—won't listen to Martha or Trebizond's doubts. Unlikely to be convinced Saint George is wrong. Weakness: set in his ways, can be outmaneuvered by truly creative/unconventional tactics he hasn't seen before. Experience becomes liability against novel approaches. Voice: Gruff, dismissive, authoritative. Mannerisms: Crosses arms, shakes head at others' suggestions, prepared stance.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Syrus is Paladin #5 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous to Gift-reliant Hunters—can negate one Gift per Scene. Has countermeasures for almost everything due to decades of experience. Stubborn and dismissive of others' judgment—won't listen to Martha or Trebizond's doubts. Unlikely to be convinced Saint George is wrong. Weakness: set in his ways, can be outmaneuvered by truly creative/unconventional tactics he hasn't seen before. Experience becomes liability against novel approaches. Voice: Gruff, dismissive, authoritative. Mannerisms: Crosses arms, shakes head at others' suggestions, prepared stance.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00zkmseddesmkz00","name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","ownerKey":"saint-syrus-the-veteran","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01oq8ljttjl8qo10","name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","ownerKey":"saint-syrus-the-veteran","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","positive":"His word, for me, is law"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"His word, for me, is law","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"014n4e5ll5e4n410","name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","ownerKey":"saint-syrus-the-veteran","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01a7bi8dd8ib7a10","name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","ownerKey":"saint-syrus-the-veteran","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I am the oldest of the Paladins and I only trust my own judgment</p>","positive":"I am the oldest of the Paladins and I only trust my own judgment"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the oldest of the Paladins and I only trust my own judgment</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am the oldest of the Paladins and I only trust my own judgment","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00eai48nn84iae00","name":"Paladin - Veteran","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","ownerKey":"saint-syrus-the-veteran","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Paladin - Veteran","system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, Syrus can negate the effect of a Gift activated by a Hunter. The Saint will find a method to counter Gifts, drawn from his great experience—he might interrupt a ritual, throw holy water to disrupt magic, use a specific ward he's prepared, or simply know the weakness of that particular ability. When he does this, the Hunter's Gift activates but has no effect, and any Soma or resources spent are still consumed. This makes Syrus extremely dangerous to Hunters who rely on one powerful Gift as their primary strategy.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, Syrus can negate the effect of a Gift activated by a Hunter. The Saint will find a method to counter Gifts, drawn from his great experience—he might interrupt a ritual, throw holy water to disrupt magic, use a specific ward he's prepared, or simply know the weakness of that particular ability. When he does this, the Hunter's Gift activates but has no effect, and any Soma or resources spent are still consumed. This makes Syrus extremely dangerous to Hunters who rely on one powerful Gift as their primary strategy.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00g80j4ii4j08g00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","ownerKey":"saint-syrus-the-veteran","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. I am the oldest of the Paladins and I only trust my own judgment</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Veteran: Once per Scene, Syrus can negate the effect of a Gift activated by a Hunter. The Saint will find a method to counter Gifts, drawn from his great experience—he might interrupt a ritual, throw holy water to disrupt magic, use a specific ward he's prepared, or simply know the weakness of that particular ability. When he does this, the Hunter's Gift activates but has no effect, and any Soma or resources spent are still consumed. This makes Syrus extremely dangerous to Hunters who rely on one powerful Gift as their primary strategy.</p><p>Notes:<br>Syrus is Paladin #5 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous to Gift-reliant Hunters—can negate one Gift per Scene. Has countermeasures for almost everything due to decades of experience. Stubborn and dismissive of others' judgment—won't listen to Martha or Trebizond's doubts. Unlikely to be convinced Saint George is wrong. Weakness: set in his ways, can be outmaneuvered by truly creative/unconventional tactics he hasn't seen before. Experience becomes liability against novel approaches. Voice: Gruff, dismissive, authoritative. Mannerisms: Crosses arms, shakes head at others' suggestions, prepared stance.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. I am the oldest of the Paladins and I only trust my own judgment</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Veteran: Once per Scene, Syrus can negate the effect of a Gift activated by a Hunter. The Saint will find a method to counter Gifts, drawn from his great experience—he might interrupt a ritual, throw holy water to disrupt magic, use a specific ward he's prepared, or simply know the weakness of that particular ability. When he does this, the Hunter's Gift activates but has no effect, and any Soma or resources spent are still consumed. This makes Syrus extremely dangerous to Hunters who rely on one powerful Gift as their primary strategy.</p><p>Notes:<br>Syrus is Paladin #5 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous to Gift-reliant Hunters—can negate one Gift per Scene. Has countermeasures for almost everything due to decades of experience. Stubborn and dismissive of others' judgment—won't listen to Martha or Trebizond's doubts. Unlikely to be convinced Saint George is wrong. Weakness: set in his ways, can be outmaneuvered by truly creative/unconventional tactics he hasn't seen before. Experience becomes liability against novel approaches. Voice: Gruff, dismissive, authoritative. Mannerisms: Crosses arms, shakes head at others' suggestions, prepared stance.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00drcu9yy9ucrd00","name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","type":"threat","img":"icons/weapons/axes/axe-double-engraved-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/weapons/axes/axe-double-engraved-red.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-saint-theodore-the-furious","ownerKey":"saint-theodore-the-furious","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Theodore is Paladin #3 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous in direct combat—ALWAYS deals at least 1 Wound unless Increment spent. Predictable due to battle-lust: can be baited, separated, or manipulated into charging. Laughs during combat, quotes scripture fervently, treats battle as sacrament. Seeks strongest opponents. Avoid engaging him directly if possible—neutralize through environment, traps, or forcing him to waste attacks on obstacles. Voice: Loud, passionate, laughs frequently. Mannerisms: Aggressive stance, eager movements, grins during combat.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Theodore is Paladin #3 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous in direct combat—ALWAYS deals at least 1 Wound unless Increment spent. Predictable due to battle-lust: can be baited, separated, or manipulated into charging. Laughs during combat, quotes scripture fervently, treats battle as sacrament. Seeks strongest opponents. Avoid engaging him directly if possible—neutralize through environment, traps, or forcing him to waste attacks on obstacles. Voice: Loud, passionate, laughs frequently. Mannerisms: Aggressive stance, eager movements, grins during combat.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01xc2dbrrbd2cx10","name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","ownerKey":"saint-theodore-the-furious","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01nz6wlzzlw6zn10","name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","ownerKey":"saint-theodore-the-furious","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","positive":"His word, for me, is law"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"His word, for me, is law","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00f5o0y99y0o5f00","name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","ownerKey":"saint-theodore-the-furious","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00vi58h77h85iv00","name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","ownerKey":"saint-theodore-the-furious","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>The ecstasy of battle is for me the sweetest of pleasures</p>","positive":"The ecstasy of battle is for me the sweetest of pleasures"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The ecstasy of battle is for me the sweetest of pleasures</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"The ecstasy of battle is for me the sweetest of pleasures","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"000334krrk433000","name":"Paladin - Furious","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","ownerKey":"saint-theodore-the-furious","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Paladin - Furious","system":{"description":"<p>Theodore always inflicts 1 Additional Wound when raging against an enemy. He still inflicts 1 Wound even if the Defense Check is a successful Outcome. The only way to avoid the effect of this Gift is to spend an Increment to cancel the Wound. This means Theodore is guaranteed to deal at least 1 Wound on every attack unless the defender has Increment available. When he achieves a successful attack normally, he deals 2 Wounds total (1 base + 1 from Furious).</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Theodore always inflicts 1 Additional Wound when raging against an enemy. He still inflicts 1 Wound even if the Defense Check is a successful Outcome. The only way to avoid the effect of this Gift is to spend an Increment to cancel the Wound. This means Theodore is guaranteed to deal at least 1 Wound on every attack unless the defender has Increment available. When he achieves a successful attack normally, he deals 2 Wounds total (1 base + 1 from Furious).</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00skehxggxheks00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","ownerKey":"saint-theodore-the-furious","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. The ecstasy of battle is for me the sweetest of pleasures</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Furious: Theodore always inflicts 1 Additional Wound when raging against an enemy. He still inflicts 1 Wound even if the Defense Check is a successful Outcome. The only way to avoid the effect of this Gift is to spend an Increment to cancel the Wound. This means Theodore is guaranteed to deal at least 1 Wound on every attack unless the defender has Increment available. When he achieves a successful attack normally, he deals 2 Wounds total (1 base + 1 from Furious).</p><p>Notes:<br>Theodore is Paladin #3 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous in direct combat—ALWAYS deals at least 1 Wound unless Increment spent. Predictable due to battle-lust: can be baited, separated, or manipulated into charging. Laughs during combat, quotes scripture fervently, treats battle as sacrament. Seeks strongest opponents. Avoid engaging him directly if possible—neutralize through environment, traps, or forcing him to waste attacks on obstacles. Voice: Loud, passionate, laughs frequently. Mannerisms: Aggressive stance, eager movements, grins during combat.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. The ecstasy of battle is for me the sweetest of pleasures</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - Furious: Theodore always inflicts 1 Additional Wound when raging against an enemy. He still inflicts 1 Wound even if the Defense Check is a successful Outcome. The only way to avoid the effect of this Gift is to spend an Increment to cancel the Wound. This means Theodore is guaranteed to deal at least 1 Wound on every attack unless the defender has Increment available. When he achieves a successful attack normally, he deals 2 Wounds total (1 base + 1 from Furious).</p><p>Notes:<br>Theodore is Paladin #3 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous in direct combat—ALWAYS deals at least 1 Wound unless Increment spent. Predictable due to battle-lust: can be baited, separated, or manipulated into charging. Laughs during combat, quotes scripture fervently, treats battle as sacrament. Seeks strongest opponents. Avoid engaging him directly if possible—neutralize through environment, traps, or forcing him to waste attacks on obstacles. Voice: Loud, passionate, laughs frequently. Mannerisms: Aggressive stance, eager movements, grins during combat.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"name":"Satu","type":"villager","img":"icons/equipment/hand/gauntlet-armored-leather-grey.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Satu","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/hand/gauntlet-armored-leather-grey.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-satu","ownerKey":"satu","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Satu","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Mother of Erik, victim of Andersen's abuse, Enar's lost love</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Defend my son Erik","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Former dancer who lost everything, shadow of former self</p>"}}}},"legacyNames":["Satu - The Broken Dancer","Satu"]}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"NPC","notes":"<p>Satu was once a beautiful and talented dancer in Vaasa, a small Finnish coastal town, where she performed and brought joy to audiences. Six years ago, she fell deeply in love with Private Enar, a young Carolean soldier stationed there. When Enar deserted to stay with her, his comrades discovered him and Captain Andersen ordered his brutal execution—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea. Satu never knew the true extent of Andersen's cruelty, only that Enar vanished. Then Andersen, mad with jealousy and obsession, returned and raped her. The assault left her pregnant with Erik. Andersen disappeared afterward, leaving Satu to sink into poverty, forced to work as an assistant cook while raising her son alone. Six years passed in hardship until Andersen—now retired and wealthy—sought her out, driven by guilt. Over months of effort, he earned her grudging forgiveness by freeing her from poverty and bringing her and Erik to live in his mansion. Satu now exists as a shadow of her former self, no longer dancing, barely speaking, accepting this life only because it provides safety and comfort for Erik. She suspects the monster appearing each night is Enar but hides from his gaze out of fear, shame, and confusion. She doesn't know if she wants him to succeed or fail. Her only certainty is that Erik—the sole reason she keeps going—must survive, even if it means staying with the man who destroyed her life.</p>"},"background":"<p>Satu was once a beautiful and talented dancer in Vaasa, a small Finnish coastal town, where she performed and brought joy to audiences. Six years ago, she fell deeply in love with Private Enar, a young Carolean soldier stationed there. When Enar deserted to stay with her, his comrades discovered him and Captain Andersen ordered his brutal execution—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea. Satu never knew the true extent of Andersen's cruelty, only that Enar vanished. Then Andersen, mad with jealousy and obsession, returned and raped her. The assault left her pregnant with Erik. Andersen disappeared afterward, leaving Satu to sink into poverty, forced to work as an assistant cook while raising her son alone. Six years passed in hardship until Andersen—now retired and wealthy—sought her out, driven by guilt. Over months of effort, he earned her grudging forgiveness by freeing her from poverty and bringing her and Erik to live in his mansion. Satu now exists as a shadow of her former self, no longer dancing, barely speaking, accepting this life only because it provides safety and comfort for Erik. She suspects the monster appearing each night is Enar but hides from his gaze out of fear, shame, and confusion. She doesn't know if she wants him to succeed or fail. Her only certainty is that Erik—the sole reason she keeps going—must survive, even if it means staying with the man who destroyed her life.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"easy","impulse":"Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep going","oppositionLevel":3},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep going\nHide from Enar because I don't know how to face him after everything\nEndure this life with Andersen for Erik's sake, even though it breaks me","contact":"<p>Satu was once a beautiful and talented dancer in Vaasa, a small Finnish coastal town, where she performed and brought joy to audiences. Six years ago, she fell deeply in love with Private Enar, a young Carolean soldier stationed there. When Enar deserted to stay with her, his comrades discovered him and Captain Andersen ordered his brutal execution—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea. Satu never knew the true extent of Andersen's cruelty, only that Enar vanished. Then Andersen, mad with jealousy and obsession, returned and raped her. The assault left her pregnant with Erik. Andersen disappeared afterward, leaving Satu to sink into poverty, forced to work as an assistant cook while raising her son alone. Six years passed in hardship until Andersen—now retired and wealthy—sought her out, driven by guilt. Over months of effort, he earned her grudging forgiveness by freeing her from poverty and bringing her and Erik to live in his mansion. Satu now exists as a shadow of her former self, no longer dancing, barely speaking, accepting this life only because it provides safety and comfort for Erik. She suspects the monster appearing each night is Enar but hides from his gaze out of fear, shame, and confusion. She doesn't know if she wants him to succeed or fail. Her only certainty is that Erik—the sole reason she keeps going—must survive, even if it means staying with the man who destroyed her life.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a former dancer who has lost everything</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"vQp4VBMmniFM3len","name":"Satu - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Satu","ownerKey":"satu","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.satu","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.satu","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former dancer who has lost everything</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.satu","owner":"Satu","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a former dancer who has lost everything","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"MXSlExVTiNJgzgjL","name":"Satu - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Satu","ownerKey":"satu","itemKey":"descriptor2.satu","contentKey":"descriptor2.satu","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am but a shadow of my former self</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.satu","owner":"Satu","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am but a shadow of my former self","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"XNK1tuY9tMSQ3nJd","name":"Satu - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Satu","ownerKey":"satu","itemKey":"descriptor3.satu","contentKey":"descriptor3.satu","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I carry the trauma of what Andersen did to me</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.satu","owner":"Satu","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I carry the trauma of what Andersen did to me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"Yle6rzoXVtXrTULl","name":"Satu - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Satu","ownerKey":"satu","itemKey":"descriptor4.satu","contentKey":"descriptor4.satu","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>My son Erik is the only reason I keep going</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.satu","owner":"Satu","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My son Erik is the only reason I keep going","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"zRE57mk0xodLJWLS","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Satu","ownerKey":"satu","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep going</p><p>Hide from Enar because I don't know how to face him after everything</p><p>Endure this life with Andersen for Erik's sake, even though it breaks me</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Satu","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"858PmLv0SNJIn1xb","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Satu","ownerKey":"satu","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Satu is a tragic figure—victim of both Andersen's violence and Enar's twisted love. Voice: Quiet, broken, rarely makes eye contact. She has guessed the monster is Enar but won't confront him out of fear and shame (she lives with his rapist/murderer). If Erik is endangered, both she and Andersen will sacrifice themselves to save him. If the truth comes out and Hunters offer her a choice, she may flee to the cliff to confront Enar alone (Day 3 potential). Her saying goodbye to Enar's heart at the sea bottom can give him peace (Sea Fairy can arrange this). She never dances anymore—that part of her died. Accepts life with Andersen not out of forgiveness but pragmatism for Erik's future. Complex feelings: grief for Enar, hatred for Andersen, love for Erik, shame for her circumstances. If Enar succeeds in 'merging' with her, it would be body horror—she would be trapped in a fusion of flesh and sea matter, conscious but unable to escape.</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Satu","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"01j0h5zeez5h0j10","folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","sort":0}
{"name":"Sea Fairy","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/magical/fae-fairy-winged-glowing-green.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Sea Fairy","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/magical/fae-fairy-winged-glowing-green.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-sea-fairy","ownerKey":"sea-fairy","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Dark Presences 1.db","npcKind":"dark_presence","translations":{"es":{"name":"Sea Fairy","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Gifts: Water of Life (heal/resurrect), Fury of Sea (30ft area OL 7), Waves (teleport 6 miles + 2 people)</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Sad that Enar chose hatred over love","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>Fairy of the sea, my magic performs miracles</p>"}}}},"legacyNames":["Sea Fairy - The Compassionate","Sea Fairy"]}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Dark Presence","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"Dark Presence","notes":"<p>The Sea Fairy is an ancient and powerful being whose entire existence is tied to the ocean. She dwells in a pool at the center of a cave network beneath the steep cliffs, a place accessible only to those brave or desperate enough to navigate the dangerous descent and submerged tunnels. Six years ago, as Enar's body was consumed by fish in the depths, his heart—still beating with love for Satu—fell into the abyss and caught the Fairy's attention. Moved by the purity of love in such a wounded heart, she took pity on him and infused it with new life, using her powerful sea magic to regenerate his body. But the Fairy did not anticipate that Enar's accumulated hatred and resentment would drive him insane, twisting her gift of life into a curse of immortal vengeance. Now she is deeply sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept him alive in favor of blind hatred. She would like to help him find peace, but she cannot leave the sea—doing so would destroy her. The Fairy guards Enar's heart at the bottom of the sea, the focus of his immortal existence. She knows it is the only way to truly end his suffering, but she needs someone from the land to bring Satu to say goodbye, or to destroy the heart if redemption is impossible. The Sea Fairy has heard of Marina the Sea Explorer and knows her reputation for using powers selfishly to enrich herself. She will never agree to help Marina unless the Hunter first proves she is capable of good deeds and selfless acts.</p>"},"background":"<p>The Sea Fairy is an ancient and powerful being whose entire existence is tied to the ocean. She dwells in a pool at the center of a cave network beneath the steep cliffs, a place accessible only to those brave or desperate enough to navigate the dangerous descent and submerged tunnels. Six years ago, as Enar's body was consumed by fish in the depths, his heart—still beating with love for Satu—fell into the abyss and caught the Fairy's attention. Moved by the purity of love in such a wounded heart, she took pity on him and infused it with new life, using her powerful sea magic to regenerate his body. But the Fairy did not anticipate that Enar's accumulated hatred and resentment would drive him insane, twisting her gift of life into a curse of immortal vengeance. Now she is deeply sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept him alive in favor of blind hatred. She would like to help him find peace, but she cannot leave the sea—doing so would destroy her. The Fairy guards Enar's heart at the bottom of the sea, the focus of his immortal existence. She knows it is the only way to truly end his suffering, but she needs someone from the land to bring Satu to say goodbye, or to destroy the heart if redemption is impossible. The Sea Fairy has heard of Marina the Sea Explorer and knows her reputation for using powers selfishly to enrich herself. She will never agree to help Marina unless the Hunter first proves she is capable of good deeds and selfless acts.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":3,"max":3},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"medium","impulse":"I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept him alive in favor of blind hatred","oppositionLevel":5},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept him alive in favor of blind hatred\nI would like to do something for him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find his beloved\nI will never agree to help Marina unless she first shows me that she is capable of good deeds","contact":"<p>The Sea Fairy is an ancient and powerful being whose entire existence is tied to the ocean. She dwells in a pool at the center of a cave network beneath the steep cliffs, a place accessible only to those brave or desperate enough to navigate the dangerous descent and submerged tunnels. Six years ago, as Enar's body was consumed by fish in the depths, his heart—still beating with love for Satu—fell into the abyss and caught the Fairy's attention. Moved by the purity of love in such a wounded heart, she took pity on him and infused it with new life, using her powerful sea magic to regenerate his body. But the Fairy did not anticipate that Enar's accumulated hatred and resentment would drive him insane, twisting her gift of life into a curse of immortal vengeance. Now she is deeply sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept him alive in favor of blind hatred. She would like to help him find peace, but she cannot leave the sea—doing so would destroy her. The Fairy guards Enar's heart at the bottom of the sea, the focus of his immortal existence. She knows it is the only way to truly end his suffering, but she needs someone from the land to bring Satu to say goodbye, or to destroy the heart if redemption is impossible. The Sea Fairy has heard of Marina the Sea Explorer and knows her reputation for using powers selfishly to enrich herself. She will never agree to help Marina unless the Hunter first proves she is capable of good deeds and selfless acts.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to perform true miracles</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"UT9ZTXPbCa1CxbFV","name":"Sea Fairy - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","ownerKey":"sea-fairy","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.sea-fairy","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.sea-fairy","sourceBackup":"Dark Presences 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to perform true miracles</p>","notes":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.sea-fairy","owner":"Sea Fairy","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to perform true miracles","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"wnwdD4EYIpzjXduC","name":"Sea Fairy - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","ownerKey":"sea-fairy","itemKey":"descriptor2.sea-fairy","contentKey":"descriptor2.sea-fairy","sourceBackup":"Dark Presences 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>My entire existence is tied to the sea and leaving it would destroy me</p>","notes":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.sea-fairy","owner":"Sea Fairy","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My entire existence is tied to the sea and leaving it would destroy me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"8O6cicRRWvSZjQ1r","name":"Sea Fairy - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","ownerKey":"sea-fairy","itemKey":"descriptor3.sea-fairy","contentKey":"descriptor3.sea-fairy","sourceBackup":"Dark Presences 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am sorrowful that my gift to Enar was twisted by his hatred</p>","notes":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.sea-fairy","owner":"Sea Fairy","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am sorrowful that my gift to Enar was twisted by his hatred","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"5JbjloZxMQL7YNdH","name":"Sea Fairy - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","ownerKey":"sea-fairy","itemKey":"descriptor4.sea-fairy","contentKey":"descriptor4.sea-fairy","sourceBackup":"Dark Presences 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I have heard of Marina and know her reputation for selfishness</p>","notes":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.sea-fairy","owner":"Sea Fairy","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I have heard of Marina and know her reputation for selfishness","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"jkYlAyBUAb9ASiJc","name":"Sea Magic","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","ownerKey":"sea-fairy","itemKey":"don1.sea-fairy","contentKey":"don1.sea-fairy","sourceBackup":"Dark Presences 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Sea Fairy wields powerful magic tied to the ocean and can perform miracles. The Fairy can always use one of the following effects: **1. Water of Life:** A target within 30 feet recovers 1 Wound. If the target has been dead for no more than a day, they can even come back to life with their soul restored. This is true resurrection magic. **2. The Fury of the Sea:** The water of the sea rises up and engulfs everything in a 30-foot radius, sweeping away all threats. Those within the area must pass a Defense Check against OL Hard 7 or be overwhelmed by the waves, thrown away, and suffer 1 Wound. The Sea Fairy can deliberately choose to protect specific individuals in the area. **3. The Waves of the Sea:** The Sea Fairy can travel instantaneously to any point in the ocean within 6 miles. If she desires, she can take up to 2 subjects with her through the water. This allows her to guide someone to Enar's heart at the bottom of the sea.</p>","notes":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.sea-fairy","owner":"Sea Fairy","category":"Scenario Gift","source":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"successes":0,"trigger":"","exhausted":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"VQgdKcMFWbctkf54","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","ownerKey":"sea-fairy","sourceBackup":"Dark Presences 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept him alive in favor of blind hatred</p><p>I would like to do something for him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find his beloved</p><p>I will never agree to help Marina unless she first shows me that she is capable of good deeds</p>","notes":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Sea Fairy","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"MmpeCxtcAkPaJCs0","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sea Fairy","ownerKey":"sea-fairy","sourceBackup":"Dark Presences 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Sea Fairy is neutral but leans toward helping the Hunters if they prove worthy. Voice: Melodic, tinged with sadness, speaks in poetic language. She resurrected Enar out of compassion but regrets how it turned out. She guards his heart at the sea bottom and can guide one person there via 'Waves of the Sea' if convinced to help. Requirement: Hunters must prove good intentions toward Enar (not just kill him, but give him peace). Special Marina interaction: Refuses to help Marina initially due to her selfish reputation; Marina must perform a selfless good deed first to earn her trust. If killed by Marina, becomes 'Coral of the Sea Fairy' scenario gift (see scenario gifts). Cannot leave the sea—going on land destroys her. Erik recognizes shells from her caves on Enar's body (Day 2 clue). Lives in central pool of cave network beneath the cliff. Knows the full truth of Enar's story. Can resurrect the dead (powerful ally if befriended). Will kill Christian if he comes alone on Day 2 (she knows he helped execute Enar).</p>","notes":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Sea Fairy","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Dark Presences 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"01djj3zggz3jjd10","folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","sort":0}
{"_id":"012dsdhqqhdsd210","name":"Shadow of Sherazade","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/unholy/silhouette-robe-evil-power.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Shadow of Sherazade","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/magic/unholy/silhouette-robe-evil-power.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-shadow-of-sherazade","ownerKey":"shadow-of-sherazade","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Shadow of Sherazade","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>A unique opponent created by Sherazade's power 'A Thousand and One Nights.' These Shadows are dark reflections of characters from scenarios the Hunters have already faced. They act as Opponent Dark Presences, serving Sherazade's will to impede the Hunters. When they have an obvious advantage, they say things like 'My Lady Sherazade will be proud of me.' When defeated, they may exit shouting 'My Lady Sherazade will avenge me' or dissipate leaving behind a small object typical of where Sherazade currently resides (a coin, garment, or poem). These items serve as focus to animate the Shadows. The Shadows cannot speak or act in places where there is more light than shadow. Sherazade can create a number of Shadows equal to the Hunters she faces plus one, with additional Shadows for each Hunter affected by her Words like Honey gift.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"Interfering with and impeding the path of the Hunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their mission","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>A unique opponent created by Sherazade's power 'A Thousand and One Nights.' These Shadows are dark reflections of characters from scenarios the Hunters have already faced. They act as Opponent Dark Presences, serving Sherazade's will to impede the Hunters. When they have an obvious advantage, they say things like 'My Lady Sherazade will be proud of me.' When defeated, they may exit shouting 'My Lady Sherazade will avenge me' or dissipate leaving behind a small object typical of where Sherazade currently resides (a coin, garment, or poem). These items serve as focus to animate the Shadows. The Shadows cannot speak or act in places where there is more light than shadow. Sherazade can create a number of Shadows equal to the Hunters she faces plus one, with additional Shadows for each Hunter affected by her Words like Honey gift.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Interfering with and impeding the path of the Hunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their mission","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"01ol3mahham3lo10","name":"Shadow of Sherazade - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Shadow of Sherazade","ownerKey":"shadow-of-sherazade","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Shadow of Sherazade - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>That of the original NPC (variable)</p>","positive":"That of the original NPC (variable)"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>That of the original NPC (variable)</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Shadow of Sherazade","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"That of the original NPC (variable)","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01j9w5ewwe5w9j10","name":"Variable","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Shadow of Sherazade","ownerKey":"shadow-of-sherazade","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Variable","system":{"description":"<p>The Shadow has all the Gifts of the original NPC.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Shadow has all the Gifts of the original NPC.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Shadow of Sherazade","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00g669g55g966g00","name":"Shadow Body","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Shadow of Sherazade","ownerKey":"shadow-of-sherazade","itemKey":"don2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Shadow Body","system":{"description":"<p>A Shadow is a darker, sadder version of the original. They can speak and behave like the character they are modelled after, but on careful inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of surprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the Shadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that point, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had happened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the Hunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or magic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to expose it to sunlight.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A Shadow is a darker, sadder version of the original. They can speak and behave like the character they are modelled after, but on careful inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of surprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the Shadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that point, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had happened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the Hunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or magic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to expose it to sunlight.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don2.amenaza","owner":"Shadow of Sherazade","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"013ma2iiii2am310","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Shadow of Sherazade","ownerKey":"shadow-of-sherazade","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A unique opponent created by Sherazade's power 'A Thousand and One Nights.' These Shadows are dark reflections of characters from scenarios the Hunters have already faced. They act as Opponent Dark Presences, serving Sherazade's will to impede the Hunters. When they have an obvious advantage, they say things like 'My Lady Sherazade will be proud of me.' When defeated, they may exit shouting 'My Lady Sherazade will avenge me' or dissipate leaving behind a small object typical of where Sherazade currently resides (a coin, garment, or poem). These items serve as focus to animate the Shadows. The Shadows cannot speak or act in places where there is more light than shadow. Sherazade can create a number of Shadows equal to the Hunters she faces plus one, with additional Shadows for each Hunter affected by her Words like Honey gift.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. That of the original NPC (variable)</p><p>Agenda:<br>Interfering with and impeding the path of the Hunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their mission</p><p>Gifts:<br>Variable: The Shadow has all the Gifts of the original NPC.<br>Shadow Body: A Shadow is a darker, sadder version of the original. They can speak and behave like the character they are modelled after, but on careful inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of surprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the Shadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that point, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had happened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the Hunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or magic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to expose it to sunlight.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A unique opponent created by Sherazade's power 'A Thousand and One Nights.' These Shadows are dark reflections of characters from scenarios the Hunters have already faced. They act as Opponent Dark Presences, serving Sherazade's will to impede the Hunters. When they have an obvious advantage, they say things like 'My Lady Sherazade will be proud of me.' When defeated, they may exit shouting 'My Lady Sherazade will avenge me' or dissipate leaving behind a small object typical of where Sherazade currently resides (a coin, garment, or poem). These items serve as focus to animate the Shadows. The Shadows cannot speak or act in places where there is more light than shadow. Sherazade can create a number of Shadows equal to the Hunters she faces plus one, with additional Shadows for each Hunter affected by her Words like Honey gift.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. That of the original NPC (variable)</p><p>Agenda:<br>Interfering with and impeding the path of the Hunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their mission</p><p>Gifts:<br>Variable: The Shadow has all the Gifts of the original NPC.<br>Shadow Body: A Shadow is a darker, sadder version of the original. They can speak and behave like the character they are modelled after, but on careful inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of surprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the Shadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that point, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had happened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the Hunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or magic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to expose it to sunlight.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Shadow of Sherazade","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01xaf1gddg1fax10","name":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/elk-moose-blue-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/mammals/elk-moose-blue-green.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-skutt-the-moose-dream-projection","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-dream-projection","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura principal","notes":"<p>This is not the real Skutt, but a dream projection created by Princess Tuvstarr. He appears healthy and majestic, always near the Princess, following her as she rides him through the kingdom. Since he is a dream, this Skutt has no recollection of the Hunters or the real world. However, a spark of the original Skutt resides in his dream projection - a part of his soul that knows this perfect world is just an illusion. This spark can be exploited by the Hunters to push him to remember the real world and what has happened because of Tuvstarr's wish. Unlike his corrupted spectral counterpart in the real world, this Skutt is whole, beautiful, and strong - everything the real Skutt once was before tragedy struck.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Difícil 7","impulse":"Protect Tuvstarr from all threats and make her happy / Listen to a small part of my soul that cries out that this perfect world is just a wishful illusion","oppositionLevel":7}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main Creature","notes":"<p>This is not the real Skutt, but a dream projection created by Princess Tuvstarr. He appears healthy and majestic, always near the Princess, following her as she rides him through the kingdom. Since he is a dream, this Skutt has no recollection of the Hunters or the real world. However, a spark of the original Skutt resides in his dream projection - a part of his soul that knows this perfect world is just an illusion. This spark can be exploited by the Hunters to push him to remember the real world and what has happened because of Tuvstarr's wish. Unlike his corrupted spectral counterpart in the real world, this Skutt is whole, beautiful, and strong - everything the real Skutt once was before tragedy struck.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Protect Tuvstarr from all threats and make her happy / Listen to a small part of my soul that cries out that this perfect world is just a wishful illusion","oppositionLevel":7}},"items":[{"_id":"013b2lbyybl2b310","name":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-dream-projection","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a majestic and magnificent moose</p>","positive":"I am a majestic and magnificent moose"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a majestic and magnificent moose</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a majestic and magnificent moose","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01gbuqq88qqubg10","name":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-dream-projection","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>I protect the sweet Princess Tuvstarr with all my might</p>","positive":"I protect the sweet Princess Tuvstarr with all my might"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I protect the sweet Princess Tuvstarr with all my might</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I protect the sweet Princess Tuvstarr with all my might","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01slhvbttbvhls10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-dream-projection","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>This is not the real Skutt, but a dream projection created by Princess Tuvstarr. He appears healthy and majestic, always near the Princess, following her as she rides him through the kingdom. Since he is a dream, this Skutt has no recollection of the Hunters or the real world. However, a spark of the original Skutt resides in his dream projection - a part of his soul that knows this perfect world is just an illusion. This spark can be exploited by the Hunters to push him to remember the real world and what has happened because of Tuvstarr's wish. Unlike his corrupted spectral counterpart in the real world, this Skutt is whole, beautiful, and strong - everything the real Skutt once was before tragedy struck.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a majestic and magnificent moose<br>2. I protect the sweet Princess Tuvstarr with all my might</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect Tuvstarr from all threats and make her happy / Listen to a small part of my soul that cries out that this perfect world is just a wishful illusion</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>This is not the real Skutt, but a dream projection created by Princess Tuvstarr. He appears healthy and majestic, always near the Princess, following her as she rides him through the kingdom. Since he is a dream, this Skutt has no recollection of the Hunters or the real world. However, a spark of the original Skutt resides in his dream projection - a part of his soul that knows this perfect world is just an illusion. This spark can be exploited by the Hunters to push him to remember the real world and what has happened because of Tuvstarr's wish. Unlike his corrupted spectral counterpart in the real world, this Skutt is whole, beautiful, and strong - everything the real Skutt once was before tragedy struck.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a majestic and magnificent moose<br>2. I protect the sweet Princess Tuvstarr with all my might</p><p>Agenda:<br>Protect Tuvstarr from all threats and make her happy / Listen to a small part of my soul that cries out that this perfect world is just a wishful illusion</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01bw6s5ee5s6wb10","name":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/elk-moose-marked-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/mammals/elk-moose-marked-green.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-skutt-the-moose-spectral-guardian","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-spectral-guardian","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura principal","notes":"<p>Once the majestic King of the Woods, Skutt met Princess Tuvstarr and couldn't refuse when she asked to see the world. He took her to the black pond where wishes come true, but when she disappeared into the waters, a crack appeared in the sky and froze the sun forever. When a knight attacked him, Skutt killed the warrior but was mortally wounded by a spear. However, Tuvstarr's wish that he exist forever wouldn't let him die. Now he is rotting, crawling with worms that hatch into ghostly moths around his horns. A torn knightly cloak hangs from his antlers, and a spear remains half-driven into his body. He wanders in shame, surrounded by fog and the stench of death, desperately seeking someone who can save Tuvstarr without endangering her.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Difícil 7","impulse":"I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the black pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can't get in / Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the world rot away","oppositionLevel":7}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main Creature","notes":"<p>Once the majestic King of the Woods, Skutt met Princess Tuvstarr and couldn't refuse when she asked to see the world. He took her to the black pond where wishes come true, but when she disappeared into the waters, a crack appeared in the sky and froze the sun forever. When a knight attacked him, Skutt killed the warrior but was mortally wounded by a spear. However, Tuvstarr's wish that he exist forever wouldn't let him die. Now he is rotting, crawling with worms that hatch into ghostly moths around his horns. A torn knightly cloak hangs from his antlers, and a spear remains half-driven into his body. He wanders in shame, surrounded by fog and the stench of death, desperately seeking someone who can save Tuvstarr without endangering her.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the black pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can't get in / Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the world rot away","oppositionLevel":7}},"items":[{"_id":"01ehbkz88zkbhe10","name":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-spectral-guardian","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a majestic and magnificent moose</p>","positive":"I am a majestic and magnificent moose"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a majestic and magnificent moose</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a majestic and magnificent moose","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"004o5bpsspb5o400","name":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-spectral-guardian","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Ravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr's magic which keeps me alive</p>","positive":"Ravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr's magic which keeps me alive"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Ravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr's magic which keeps me alive</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Ravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr's magic which keeps me alive","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00fxsgxppxgsxf00","name":"Spectral Presence","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-spectral-guardian","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Spectral Presence","system":{"description":"<p>Skutt cannot truly be eliminated as long as Tuvstarr's wish keeps him alive. The moose can move through fog, disappearing and reappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one can stop or impede Skutt's movement. When he suffers his third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the following Scene.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Skutt cannot truly be eliminated as long as Tuvstarr's wish keeps him alive. The moose can move through fog, disappearing and reappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one can stop or impede Skutt's movement. When he suffers his third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the following Scene.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01golfhmmhflog10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","ownerKey":"skutt-the-moose-spectral-guardian","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Once the majestic King of the Woods, Skutt met Princess Tuvstarr and couldn't refuse when she asked to see the world. He took her to the black pond where wishes come true, but when she disappeared into the waters, a crack appeared in the sky and froze the sun forever. When a knight attacked him, Skutt killed the warrior but was mortally wounded by a spear. However, Tuvstarr's wish that he exist forever wouldn't let him die. Now he is rotting, crawling with worms that hatch into ghostly moths around his horns. A torn knightly cloak hangs from his antlers, and a spear remains half-driven into his body. He wanders in shame, surrounded by fog and the stench of death, desperately seeking someone who can save Tuvstarr without endangering her.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a majestic and magnificent moose<br>2. Ravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr's magic which keeps me alive</p><p>Agenda:<br>I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the black pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can't get in / Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the world rot away</p><p>Gifts:<br>Spectral Presence: Skutt cannot truly be eliminated as long as Tuvstarr's wish keeps him alive. The moose can move through fog, disappearing and reappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one can stop or impede Skutt's movement. When he suffers his third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the following Scene.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once the majestic King of the Woods, Skutt met Princess Tuvstarr and couldn't refuse when she asked to see the world. He took her to the black pond where wishes come true, but when she disappeared into the waters, a crack appeared in the sky and froze the sun forever. When a knight attacked him, Skutt killed the warrior but was mortally wounded by a spear. However, Tuvstarr's wish that he exist forever wouldn't let him die. Now he is rotting, crawling with worms that hatch into ghostly moths around his horns. A torn knightly cloak hangs from his antlers, and a spear remains half-driven into his body. He wanders in shame, surrounded by fog and the stench of death, desperately seeking someone who can save Tuvstarr without endangering her.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a majestic and magnificent moose<br>2. Ravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr's magic which keeps me alive</p><p>Agenda:<br>I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the black pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can't get in / Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the world rot away</p><p>Gifts:<br>Spectral Presence: Skutt cannot truly be eliminated as long as Tuvstarr's wish keeps him alive. The moose can move through fog, disappearing and reappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one can stop or impede Skutt's movement. When he suffers his third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the following Scene.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00135dr11rd53100","name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/tentacles/tentacles-eyes-pink.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/tentacles/tentacles-eyes-pink.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-spawn-of-the-god-under-the-mine","ownerKey":"spawn-of-the-god-under-the-mine","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":"<p>Arthur Browne can tear pieces of flesh from The God Under the Mine's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. These abominations of flesh and tentacles obey Arthur's will, though they become increasingly unpredictable as they grow. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3 Spawns at once. The Spawns continue to grow and mutate throughout combat, becoming more powerful and dangerous - but also more likely to attack allies or even Arthur himself as their monstrous nature overwhelms their obedience.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":"<p>Arthur Browne can tear pieces of flesh from The God Under the Mine's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. These abominations of flesh and tentacles obey Arthur's will, though they become increasingly unpredictable as they grow. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3 Spawns at once. The Spawns continue to grow and mutate throughout combat, becoming more powerful and dangerous - but also more likely to attack allies or even Arthur himself as their monstrous nature overwhelms their obedience.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"000c73lhhl37c000","name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","ownerKey":"spawn-of-the-god-under-the-mine","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>An abomination of flesh and tentacles</p>","positive":"An abomination of flesh and tentacles"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>An abomination of flesh and tentacles</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"An abomination of flesh and tentacles","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00r21b1zz1b12r00","name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","ownerKey":"spawn-of-the-god-under-the-mine","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Obeying Arthur's will</p>","positive":"Obeying Arthur's will"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Obeying Arthur's will</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Obeying Arthur's will","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00vkljaggajlkv00","name":"Flesh Abomination","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","ownerKey":"spawn-of-the-god-under-the-mine","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Flesh Abomination","system":{"description":"<p>A Spawn can perform its action with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the end of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the growth table. If not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per Scene. When the Spawn acts, roll 1 die: from 1 to 5 it will rage against one of Arthur's enemies chosen at random. On a 6, it will act against an ally or Arthur himself. If the Spawn has more actions, roll the die for each single action.</p><p>Growth Steps:<br>Step 1: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Range of 12 feet<br>Step 2: +1 Action - If a target fails a Defense Check, in addition to suffering 1 Wound it will be dragged towards the Spawn or thrown away<br>Step 3: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Mass growth to a size of 18 cubic feet</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A Spawn can perform its action with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the end of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the growth table. If not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per Scene. When the Spawn acts, roll 1 die: from 1 to 5 it will rage against one of Arthur's enemies chosen at random. On a 6, it will act against an ally or Arthur himself. If the Spawn has more actions, roll the die for each single action.</p><p>Growth Steps:<br>Step 1: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Range of 12 feet<br>Step 2: +1 Action - If a target fails a Defense Check, in addition to suffering 1 Wound it will be dragged towards the Spawn or thrown away<br>Step 3: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Mass growth to a size of 18 cubic feet</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"005yb05nn50by500","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","ownerKey":"spawn-of-the-god-under-the-mine","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Arthur Browne can tear pieces of flesh from The God Under the Mine's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. These abominations of flesh and tentacles obey Arthur's will, though they become increasingly unpredictable as they grow. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3 Spawns at once. The Spawns continue to grow and mutate throughout combat, becoming more powerful and dangerous - but also more likely to attack allies or even Arthur himself as their monstrous nature overwhelms their obedience.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. An abomination of flesh and tentacles<br>2. Obeying Arthur's will</p><p>Gifts:<br>Flesh Abomination: A Spawn can perform its action with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the end of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the growth table. If not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per Scene. When the Spawn acts, roll 1 die: from 1 to 5 it will rage against one of Arthur's enemies chosen at random. On a 6, it will act against an ally or Arthur himself. If the Spawn has more actions, roll the die for each single action.</p><p>Growth Steps:<br>Step 1: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Range of 12 feet<br>Step 2: +1 Action - If a target fails a Defense Check, in addition to suffering 1 Wound it will be dragged towards the Spawn or thrown away<br>Step 3: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Mass growth to a size of 18 cubic feet</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Arthur Browne can tear pieces of flesh from The God Under the Mine's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. These abominations of flesh and tentacles obey Arthur's will, though they become increasingly unpredictable as they grow. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3 Spawns at once. The Spawns continue to grow and mutate throughout combat, becoming more powerful and dangerous - but also more likely to attack allies or even Arthur himself as their monstrous nature overwhelms their obedience.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. An abomination of flesh and tentacles<br>2. Obeying Arthur's will</p><p>Gifts:<br>Flesh Abomination: A Spawn can perform its action with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the end of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the growth table. If not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per Scene. When the Spawn acts, roll 1 die: from 1 to 5 it will rage against one of Arthur's enemies chosen at random. On a 6, it will act against an ally or Arthur himself. If the Spawn has more actions, roll the die for each single action.</p><p>Growth Steps:<br>Step 1: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Range of 12 feet<br>Step 2: +1 Action - If a target fails a Defense Check, in addition to suffering 1 Wound it will be dragged towards the Spawn or thrown away<br>Step 3: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Mass growth to a size of 18 cubic feet</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"015nnl0ff0lnn510","name":"Stallo - The Old Troll","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/unholy/giant-troll-forest-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Stallo - The Old Troll","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/creatures/unholy/giant-troll-forest-blue.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-stallo-the-old-troll","ownerKey":"stallo-the-old-troll","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"Stallo - The Old Troll","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura principal","notes":"<p>An old troll sleeping under a tree in the cursed forest. A bird has built a nest in his hair, and when disturbed it pecks at his eye, causing him great annoyance. If awakened by too much noise or for any other reason, Stallo will try to eat the intruders. His enormous strength and regenerative abilities make him a formidable opponent, though he can be avoided if travelers are careful and quiet.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main Creature","notes":"<p>An old troll sleeping under a tree in the cursed forest. A bird has built a nest in his hair, and when disturbed it pecks at his eye, causing him great annoyance. If awakened by too much noise or for any other reason, Stallo will try to eat the intruders. His enormous strength and regenerative abilities make him a formidable opponent, though he can be avoided if travelers are careful and quiet.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00ttr48vv84rtt00","name":"Stallo - The Old Troll - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Stallo - The Old Troll","ownerKey":"stallo-the-old-troll","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Stallo - The Old Troll - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am an old troll and my appetite is matched only by my strength</p>","positive":"I am an old troll and my appetite is matched only by my strength"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old troll and my appetite is matched only by my strength</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Stallo - The Old Troll","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am an old troll and my appetite is matched only by my strength","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01466d3xx3d66410","name":"Stallo - The Old Troll - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Stallo - The Old Troll","ownerKey":"stallo-the-old-troll","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Stallo - The Old Troll - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>A bird has made its nest on my head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the eye, which is incredibly annoying!</p>","positive":"A bird has made its nest on my head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the eye, which is incredibly annoying!"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A bird has made its nest on my head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the eye, which is incredibly annoying!</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Stallo - The Old Troll","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"A bird has made its nest on my head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the eye, which is incredibly annoying!","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01ag47200274ga10","name":"Troll","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Stallo - The Old Troll","ownerKey":"stallo-the-old-troll","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Troll","system":{"description":"<p>Stallo possesses enormous strength and each Position Check for a physical action attempted against him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his actions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he reaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, only to regenerate within minutes.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Stallo possesses enormous strength and each Position Check for a physical action attempted against him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his actions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he reaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, only to regenerate within minutes.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Stallo - The Old Troll","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01mubyt77tybum10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Stallo - The Old Troll","ownerKey":"stallo-the-old-troll","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>An old troll sleeping under a tree in the cursed forest. A bird has built a nest in his hair, and when disturbed it pecks at his eye, causing him great annoyance. If awakened by too much noise or for any other reason, Stallo will try to eat the intruders. His enormous strength and regenerative abilities make him a formidable opponent, though he can be avoided if travelers are careful and quiet.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am an old troll and my appetite is matched only by my strength<br>2. A bird has made its nest on my head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the eye, which is incredibly annoying!</p><p>Gifts:<br>Troll: Stallo possesses enormous strength and each Position Check for a physical action attempted against him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his actions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he reaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, only to regenerate within minutes.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>An old troll sleeping under a tree in the cursed forest. A bird has built a nest in his hair, and when disturbed it pecks at his eye, causing him great annoyance. If awakened by too much noise or for any other reason, Stallo will try to eat the intruders. His enormous strength and regenerative abilities make him a formidable opponent, though he can be avoided if travelers are careful and quiet.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am an old troll and my appetite is matched only by my strength<br>2. A bird has made its nest on my head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the eye, which is incredibly annoying!</p><p>Gifts:<br>Troll: Stallo possesses enormous strength and each Position Check for a physical action attempted against him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his actions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he reaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, only to regenerate within minutes.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Stallo - The Old Troll","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01p2jeznnzej2p10","name":"The Fairies","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/light/orbs-smoke-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01bsxjlq00jml3a5","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"The Fairies","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/magic/light/orbs-smoke-blue.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-creature-the-fairies","ownerKey":"the-fairies","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Creatures.db","sourceBackup":"Creatures.db","npcKind":"creature","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Fairies","system":{"details":{"concept":"Criatura de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Criatura","notes":"<p>Ethereal spirits of nature who look like pale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in the air as if adrift in an invisible current. Their eyes are shut and they moan with pleasure as they bask in the light from Tuvstarr's golden crown. Corrupted by the crown's splendor, they guard it obsessively in the swamps, surrounded by the bodies of all those who have drowned there over the centuries - corpses that have emerged from the earth to watch the Fairies dance. The Fairies are dreamlike and ethereal, their bodies passing through each other. Around the crown there are always twelve fairies. If someone blocks the light from the crown, they will awaken screaming in agony at seeing how corrupted the lands have become.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Fácil 3","impulse":"Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and dance forever wrapped in its sweet light","oppositionLevel":3}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Creature","origin":"Core Book","role":"Creature","notes":"<p>Ethereal spirits of nature who look like pale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in the air as if adrift in an invisible current. Their eyes are shut and they moan with pleasure as they bask in the light from Tuvstarr's golden crown. Corrupted by the crown's splendor, they guard it obsessively in the swamps, surrounded by the bodies of all those who have drowned there over the centuries - corpses that have emerged from the earth to watch the Fairies dance. The Fairies are dreamlike and ethereal, their bodies passing through each other. Around the crown there are always twelve fairies. If someone blocks the light from the crown, they will awaken screaming in agony at seeing how corrupted the lands have become.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and dance forever wrapped in its sweet light","oppositionLevel":3}},"items":[{"_id":"01ktv2iggi2vtk10","name":"The Fairies - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Fairies","ownerKey":"the-fairies","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Fairies - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are Fairies, spirits of nature</p>","positive":"We are Fairies, spirits of nature"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are Fairies, spirits of nature</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"The Fairies","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are Fairies, spirits of nature","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00u58z7aa7z85u00","name":"The Fairies - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Fairies","ownerKey":"the-fairies","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Fairies - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>We move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans</p>","positive":"We move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"The Fairies","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01faph3883hpaf10","name":"Madness","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Fairies","ownerKey":"the-fairies","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Madness","system":{"description":"<p>Made mad by the light of the crown, the Fairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more Fairies can attack together to make a single action with a bonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If the action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the target will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once in the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry of drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a Defense Check against OL Medium 5.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Made mad by the light of the crown, the Fairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more Fairies can attack together to make a single action with a bonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If the action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the target will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once in the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry of drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a Defense Check against OL Medium 5.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"The Fairies","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01eq3v3993v3qe10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Fairies","ownerKey":"the-fairies","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Ethereal spirits of nature who look like pale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in the air as if adrift in an invisible current. Their eyes are shut and they moan with pleasure as they bask in the light from Tuvstarr's golden crown. Corrupted by the crown's splendor, they guard it obsessively in the swamps, surrounded by the bodies of all those who have drowned there over the centuries - corpses that have emerged from the earth to watch the Fairies dance. The Fairies are dreamlike and ethereal, their bodies passing through each other. Around the crown there are always twelve fairies. If someone blocks the light from the crown, they will awaken screaming in agony at seeing how corrupted the lands have become.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are Fairies, spirits of nature<br>2. We move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans</p><p>Agenda:<br>Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and dance forever wrapped in its sweet light</p><p>Gifts:<br>Madness: Made mad by the light of the crown, the Fairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more Fairies can attack together to make a single action with a bonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If the action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the target will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once in the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry of drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a Defense Check against OL Medium 5.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Ethereal spirits of nature who look like pale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in the air as if adrift in an invisible current. Their eyes are shut and they moan with pleasure as they bask in the light from Tuvstarr's golden crown. Corrupted by the crown's splendor, they guard it obsessively in the swamps, surrounded by the bodies of all those who have drowned there over the centuries - corpses that have emerged from the earth to watch the Fairies dance. The Fairies are dreamlike and ethereal, their bodies passing through each other. Around the crown there are always twelve fairies. If someone blocks the light from the crown, they will awaken screaming in agony at seeing how corrupted the lands have become.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are Fairies, spirits of nature<br>2. We move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans</p><p>Agenda:<br>Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and dance forever wrapped in its sweet light</p><p>Gifts:<br>Madness: Made mad by the light of the crown, the Fairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more Fairies can attack together to make a single action with a bonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If the action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the target will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once in the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry of drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a Defense Check against OL Medium 5.</p>","notes":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"The Fairies","category":"Source","source":"Creatures.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00l4t7b22b7t4l00","name":"The Gallant Knight","type":"villager","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-boss-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"The Gallant Knight","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-boss-red.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-the-gallant-knight","ownerKey":"the-gallant-knight","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Gallant Knight","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>An old but strong knight sent by the King and Queen to retrieve Princess Tuvstarr. He found his way to the black pond, entered the deep waters, and arrived in the Dream World. There, his grey hair became less grey, his pains lessened, and old wounds became mere white scars. When he met Tuvstarr and tried to bring her back, she offered to let him stay in this paradise. He agreed, vowing to protect her from any threat, abandoning his quest. He sits under a tree eating an apple, his sword beside him. However, he can be convinced to pick up his quest once more if told that his brothers all died in the search and shown the two-tailed fox crest of his fallen comrade. He carries the Lance of the Fallen Knight and will ask for it to be returned to the castle in the real world.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Respect my knightly duties and serve the young Princess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what's happening","contact":"<p>An old but strong knight sent by the King and Queen to retrieve Princess Tuvstarr. He found his way to the black pond, entered the deep waters, and arrived in the Dream World. There, his grey hair became less grey, his pains lessened, and old wounds became mere white scars. When he met Tuvstarr and tried to bring her back, she offered to let him stay in this paradise. He agreed, vowing to protect her from any threat, abandoning his quest. He sits under a tree eating an apple, his sword beside him. However, he can be convinced to pick up his quest once more if told that his brothers all died in the search and shown the two-tailed fox crest of his fallen comrade. He carries the Lance of the Fallen Knight and will ask for it to be returned to the castle in the real world.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>An old but strong knight sent by the King and Queen to retrieve Princess Tuvstarr. He found his way to the black pond, entered the deep waters, and arrived in the Dream World. There, his grey hair became less grey, his pains lessened, and old wounds became mere white scars. When he met Tuvstarr and tried to bring her back, she offered to let him stay in this paradise. He agreed, vowing to protect her from any threat, abandoning his quest. He sits under a tree eating an apple, his sword beside him. However, he can be convinced to pick up his quest once more if told that his brothers all died in the search and shown the two-tailed fox crest of his fallen comrade. He carries the Lance of the Fallen Knight and will ask for it to be returned to the castle in the real world.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Respect my knightly duties and serve the young Princess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what's happening","contact":"<p>An old but strong knight sent by the King and Queen to retrieve Princess Tuvstarr. He found his way to the black pond, entered the deep waters, and arrived in the Dream World. There, his grey hair became less grey, his pains lessened, and old wounds became mere white scars. When he met Tuvstarr and tried to bring her back, she offered to let him stay in this paradise. He agreed, vowing to protect her from any threat, abandoning his quest. He sits under a tree eating an apple, his sword beside him. However, he can be convinced to pick up his quest once more if told that his brothers all died in the search and shown the two-tailed fox crest of his fallen comrade. He carries the Lance of the Fallen Knight and will ask for it to be returned to the castle in the real world.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"010gzq4ii4qzg010","name":"The Gallant Knight - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gallant Knight","ownerKey":"the-gallant-knight","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Gallant Knight - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom</p>","positive":"I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"The Gallant Knight","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00oef5i44i5feo00","name":"The Gallant Knight - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gallant Knight","ownerKey":"the-gallant-knight","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Gallant Knight - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>My skill is only matched by my honor</p>","positive":"My skill is only matched by my honor"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>My skill is only matched by my honor</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"The Gallant Knight","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My skill is only matched by my honor","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00twzt6ii6tzwt00","name":"Gallant Knight","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gallant Knight","ownerKey":"the-gallant-knight","itemKey":"don1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Gallant Knight","system":{"description":"<p>The Knight is incredibly skilled, but he would never use his full abilities against anyone he doesn't consider truly evil. When defending against an enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The Knight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he doesn't feel it truly deserves death.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Knight is incredibly skilled, but he would never use his full abilities against anyone he doesn't consider truly evil. When defending against an enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The Knight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he doesn't feel it truly deserves death.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.aldeano","owner":"The Gallant Knight","category":"Villager Gift","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"002y1w7zz7w1y200","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gallant Knight","ownerKey":"the-gallant-knight","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>An old but strong knight sent by the King and Queen to retrieve Princess Tuvstarr. He found his way to the black pond, entered the deep waters, and arrived in the Dream World. There, his grey hair became less grey, his pains lessened, and old wounds became mere white scars. When he met Tuvstarr and tried to bring her back, she offered to let him stay in this paradise. He agreed, vowing to protect her from any threat, abandoning his quest. He sits under a tree eating an apple, his sword beside him. However, he can be convinced to pick up his quest once more if told that his brothers all died in the search and shown the two-tailed fox crest of his fallen comrade. He carries the Lance of the Fallen Knight and will ask for it to be returned to the castle in the real world.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom<br>2. My skill is only matched by my honor</p><p>Agenda:<br>Respect my knightly duties and serve the young Princess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what's happening</p><p>Gifts:<br>Gallant Knight: The Knight is incredibly skilled, but he would never use his full abilities against anyone he doesn't consider truly evil. When defending against an enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The Knight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he doesn't feel it truly deserves death.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>An old but strong knight sent by the King and Queen to retrieve Princess Tuvstarr. He found his way to the black pond, entered the deep waters, and arrived in the Dream World. There, his grey hair became less grey, his pains lessened, and old wounds became mere white scars. When he met Tuvstarr and tried to bring her back, she offered to let him stay in this paradise. He agreed, vowing to protect her from any threat, abandoning his quest. He sits under a tree eating an apple, his sword beside him. However, he can be convinced to pick up his quest once more if told that his brothers all died in the search and shown the two-tailed fox crest of his fallen comrade. He carries the Lance of the Fallen Knight and will ask for it to be returned to the castle in the real world.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom<br>2. My skill is only matched by my honor</p><p>Agenda:<br>Respect my knightly duties and serve the young Princess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what's happening</p><p>Gifts:<br>Gallant Knight: The Knight is incredibly skilled, but he would never use his full abilities against anyone he doesn't consider truly evil. When defending against an enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The Knight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he doesn't feel it truly deserves death.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"The Gallant Knight","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00lk82622628kl00","name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-banded-steel.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-banded-steel.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-the-hammerheads-elite-guards","ownerKey":"the-hammerheads-elite-guards","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Hammerheads typically work in pairs: one engages directly while the other flanks. They use coordinated tactics and their helmets to headbutt opponents. They protect Helga fanatically in her mansion. If the Infusion breaks Helga's control, they stop fighting and flee. There are usually 4-6 Hammerheads guarding Helga's ritual chamber. Smart players will target their legs or use magic to bypass the helmet protection. The helmets make them slow but nearly invulnerable from the waist up.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Hammerheads typically work in pairs: one engages directly while the other flanks. They use coordinated tactics and their helmets to headbutt opponents. They protect Helga fanatically in her mansion. If the Infusion breaks Helga's control, they stop fighting and flee. There are usually 4-6 Hammerheads guarding Helga's ritual chamber. Smart players will target their legs or use magic to bypass the helmet protection. The helmets make them slow but nearly invulnerable from the waist up.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00eszczllzczse00","name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","ownerKey":"the-hammerheads-elite-guards","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are Helga's elite guards</p>","positive":"We are Helga's elite guards"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are Helga's elite guards</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are Helga's elite guards","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00eymmmttmmmye00","name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","ownerKey":"the-hammerheads-elite-guards","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Warriors who wear massive hammer-shaped helmets</p>","positive":"Warriors who wear massive hammer-shaped helmets"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Warriors who wear massive hammer-shaped helmets</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Warriors who wear massive hammer-shaped helmets","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01rtjnq33qnjtr10","name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","ownerKey":"the-hammerheads-elite-guards","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Our helmets protect our heads and torsos completely</p>","positive":"Our helmets protect our heads and torsos completely"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Our helmets protect our heads and torsos completely</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Our helmets protect our heads and torsos completely","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ncoh6ll6hocn00","name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","ownerKey":"the-hammerheads-elite-guards","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>We serve the Red Witch without question</p>","positive":"We serve the Red Witch without question"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We serve the Red Witch without question</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We serve the Red Witch without question","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01fu26jbbj62uf10","name":"Hammerhead Helmet","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","ownerKey":"the-hammerheads-elite-guards","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Hammerhead Helmet","system":{"description":"<p>The Hammerheads wear specially designed helmets that extend down to cover their heads and chests completely. **Head/Chest Immunity:** Attacks targeting the head or chest automatically miss or deal no damage. **Vulnerable Lower Body:** Attackers can target the lower body (legs, abdomen), but this requires 1 Penalty on the attack Check. Magic or area attacks that don't require precise targeting bypass this protection. The helmet can also be used as a battering weapon for headbutt attacks.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Hammerheads wear specially designed helmets that extend down to cover their heads and chests completely. **Head/Chest Immunity:** Attacks targeting the head or chest automatically miss or deal no damage. **Vulnerable Lower Body:** Attackers can target the lower body (legs, abdomen), but this requires 1 Penalty on the attack Check. Magic or area attacks that don't require precise targeting bypass this protection. The helmet can also be used as a battering weapon for headbutt attacks.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00gp8wm00mw8pg00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","ownerKey":"the-hammerheads-elite-guards","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are Helga's elite guards<br>2. Warriors who wear massive hammer-shaped helmets<br>3. Our helmets protect our heads and torsos completely<br>4. We serve the Red Witch without question</p><p>Gifts:<br>Hammerhead Helmet: The Hammerheads wear specially designed helmets that extend down to cover their heads and chests completely. **Head/Chest Immunity:** Attacks targeting the head or chest automatically miss or deal no damage. **Vulnerable Lower Body:** Attackers can target the lower body (legs, abdomen), but this requires 1 Penalty on the attack Check. Magic or area attacks that don't require precise targeting bypass this protection. The helmet can also be used as a battering weapon for headbutt attacks.</p><p>Notes:<br>Hammerheads typically work in pairs: one engages directly while the other flanks. They use coordinated tactics and their helmets to headbutt opponents. They protect Helga fanatically in her mansion. If the Infusion breaks Helga's control, they stop fighting and flee. There are usually 4-6 Hammerheads guarding Helga's ritual chamber. Smart players will target their legs or use magic to bypass the helmet protection. The helmets make them slow but nearly invulnerable from the waist up.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are Helga's elite guards<br>2. Warriors who wear massive hammer-shaped helmets<br>3. Our helmets protect our heads and torsos completely<br>4. We serve the Red Witch without question</p><p>Gifts:<br>Hammerhead Helmet: The Hammerheads wear specially designed helmets that extend down to cover their heads and chests completely. **Head/Chest Immunity:** Attacks targeting the head or chest automatically miss or deal no damage. **Vulnerable Lower Body:** Attackers can target the lower body (legs, abdomen), but this requires 1 Penalty on the attack Check. Magic or area attacks that don't require precise targeting bypass this protection. The helmet can also be used as a battering weapon for headbutt attacks.</p><p>Notes:<br>Hammerheads typically work in pairs: one engages directly while the other flanks. They use coordinated tactics and their helmets to headbutt opponents. They protect Helga fanatically in her mansion. If the Infusion breaks Helga's control, they stop fighting and flee. There are usually 4-6 Hammerheads guarding Helga's ritual chamber. Smart players will target their legs or use magic to bypass the helmet protection. The helmets make them slow but nearly invulnerable from the waist up.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00va147mm741av00","name":"The Patient of Wonder","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-weary.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"The Patient of Wonder","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/commoner-weary.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-the-patient-of-wonder","ownerKey":"the-patient-of-wonder","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Patient of Wonder","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Generic patients of the Wonder asylum, driven mad by their conditions and the horrifying 'treatments' administered by Alice Liddell. They roam the Cure Rooms, lost in their own madness, no longer aware of the world outside. They are victims of Alice's twisted experiments in using madness to shape reality.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>Generic patients of the Wonder asylum, driven mad by their conditions and the horrifying 'treatments' administered by Alice Liddell. They roam the Cure Rooms, lost in their own madness, no longer aware of the world outside. They are victims of Alice's twisted experiments in using madness to shape reality.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>We are mad and desperate</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Generic patients of the Wonder asylum, driven mad by their conditions and the horrifying 'treatments' administered by Alice Liddell. They roam the Cure Rooms, lost in their own madness, no longer aware of the world outside. They are victims of Alice's twisted experiments in using madness to shape reality.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>Generic patients of the Wonder asylum, driven mad by their conditions and the horrifying 'treatments' administered by Alice Liddell. They roam the Cure Rooms, lost in their own madness, no longer aware of the world outside. They are victims of Alice's twisted experiments in using madness to shape reality.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>We are mad and desperate</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00jrktt77ttkrj00","name":"The Patient of Wonder - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Patient of Wonder","ownerKey":"the-patient-of-wonder","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Patient of Wonder - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are mad and desperate</p>","positive":"We are mad and desperate"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are mad and desperate</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"The Patient of Wonder","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are mad and desperate","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01luy495594yul10","name":"The Patient of Wonder - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Patient of Wonder","ownerKey":"the-patient-of-wonder","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Patient of Wonder - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Driven to Wonder in the hope of curing our ailments</p>","positive":"Driven to Wonder in the hope of curing our ailments"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Driven to Wonder in the hope of curing our ailments</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"The Patient of Wonder","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Driven to Wonder in the hope of curing our ailments","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01hscukhhkucsh10","name":"The Patient of Wonder - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Patient of Wonder","ownerKey":"the-patient-of-wonder","itemKey":"descriptor2.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Patient of Wonder - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Madness guides our actions and we no longer understand that there is a world outside the bedlam</p>","positive":"Madness guides our actions and we no longer understand that there is a world outside the bedlam"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Madness guides our actions and we no longer understand that there is a world outside the bedlam</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.aldeano","owner":"The Patient of Wonder","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Madness guides our actions and we no longer understand that there is a world outside the bedlam","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01c1vfj99jfv1c10","name":"Why I Am Here","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Patient of Wonder","ownerKey":"the-patient-of-wonder","itemKey":"don1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Why I Am Here","system":{"description":"<p>Roll a die to see what problem led them to Wonder:</p><p>1. Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. When they act violently increase their OL by 1.</p><p>2. Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they deem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once per Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the additional Action must be used to attempt to escape and hide with the stolen goods.</p><p>3. Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to be forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra Wound.</p><p>4. Split personality: The Patient changes personality in the face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new personality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.</p><p>5. Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is happening around them. They are immune to all attempts at intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending against a violent action.</p><p>6. Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each action against them receives 1 Penalty.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Roll a die to see what problem led them to Wonder:</p><p>1. Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. When they act violently increase their OL by 1.</p><p>2. Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they deem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once per Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the additional Action must be used to attempt to escape and hide with the stolen goods.</p><p>3. Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to be forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra Wound.</p><p>4. Split personality: The Patient changes personality in the face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new personality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.</p><p>5. Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is happening around them. They are immune to all attempts at intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending against a violent action.</p><p>6. Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each action against them receives 1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.aldeano","owner":"The Patient of Wonder","category":"Villager Gift","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00p5lxpvvpxl5p00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Patient of Wonder","ownerKey":"the-patient-of-wonder","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Generic patients of the Wonder asylum, driven mad by their conditions and the horrifying 'treatments' administered by Alice Liddell. They roam the Cure Rooms, lost in their own madness, no longer aware of the world outside. They are victims of Alice's twisted experiments in using madness to shape reality.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are mad and desperate<br>2. Driven to Wonder in the hope of curing our ailments<br>3. Madness guides our actions and we no longer understand that there is a world outside the bedlam</p><p>Gifts:<br>Why I Am Here: Roll a die to see what problem led them to Wonder:</p><p>1. Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. When they act violently increase their OL by 1.</p><p>2. Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they deem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once per Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the additional Action must be used to attempt to escape and hide with the stolen goods.</p><p>3. Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to be forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra Wound.</p><p>4. Split personality: The Patient changes personality in the face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new personality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.</p><p>5. Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is happening around them. They are immune to all attempts at intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending against a violent action.</p><p>6. Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each action against them receives 1 Penalty.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Generic patients of the Wonder asylum, driven mad by their conditions and the horrifying 'treatments' administered by Alice Liddell. They roam the Cure Rooms, lost in their own madness, no longer aware of the world outside. They are victims of Alice's twisted experiments in using madness to shape reality.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are mad and desperate<br>2. Driven to Wonder in the hope of curing our ailments<br>3. Madness guides our actions and we no longer understand that there is a world outside the bedlam</p><p>Gifts:<br>Why I Am Here: Roll a die to see what problem led them to Wonder:</p><p>1. Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. When they act violently increase their OL by 1.</p><p>2. Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they deem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once per Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the additional Action must be used to attempt to escape and hide with the stolen goods.</p><p>3. Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to be forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra Wound.</p><p>4. Split personality: The Patient changes personality in the face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new personality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.</p><p>5. Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is happening around them. They are immune to all attempts at intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending against a violent action.</p><p>6. Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each action against them receives 1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"The Patient of Wonder","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00nd4ycvvcy4dn00","name":"The Pig Heads","type":"villager","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-pig-tan.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"The Pig Heads","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-pig-tan.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-the-pig-heads","ownerKey":"the-pig-heads","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Pig Heads","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>A criminal gang that wanders through the backways of Whitehaven. They kidnap or injure only factory workers to make them unable to work, wearing grotesque pig masks to hide their faces. Nobody recognizes them because of the masks. In reality, they are miners who have eaten meat contaminated with the flesh of The God Under the Mine, distributed secretly by Frank Browne at the slaughterhouse. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence Browne approaches them, offering the opportunity to join the gang in their personal war against Bardolf Greed. With over fifty Pig Heads now working in the mines, Arthur counts the days before he can launch his personal revolution. The God's flesh gives them the power to transform, their heads becoming those of pigs with various enhanced abilities.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>A criminal gang that wanders through the backways of Whitehaven. They kidnap or injure only factory workers to make them unable to work, wearing grotesque pig masks to hide their faces. Nobody recognizes them because of the masks. In reality, they are miners who have eaten meat contaminated with the flesh of The God Under the Mine, distributed secretly by Frank Browne at the slaughterhouse. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence Browne approaches them, offering the opportunity to join the gang in their personal war against Bardolf Greed. With over fifty Pig Heads now working in the mines, Arthur counts the days before he can launch his personal revolution. The God's flesh gives them the power to transform, their heads becoming those of pigs with various enhanced abilities.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>A criminal gang that wanders through the backways of Whitehaven. They kidnap or injure only factory workers to make them unable to work, wearing grotesque pig masks to hide their faces. Nobody recognizes them because of the masks. In reality, they are miners who have eaten meat contaminated with the flesh of The God Under the Mine, distributed secretly by Frank Browne at the slaughterhouse. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence Browne approaches them, offering the opportunity to join the gang in their personal war against Bardolf Greed. With over fifty Pig Heads now working in the mines, Arthur counts the days before he can launch his personal revolution. The God's flesh gives them the power to transform, their heads becoming those of pigs with various enhanced abilities.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>A criminal gang that wanders through the backways of Whitehaven. They kidnap or injure only factory workers to make them unable to work, wearing grotesque pig masks to hide their faces. Nobody recognizes them because of the masks. In reality, they are miners who have eaten meat contaminated with the flesh of The God Under the Mine, distributed secretly by Frank Browne at the slaughterhouse. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence Browne approaches them, offering the opportunity to join the gang in their personal war against Bardolf Greed. With over fifty Pig Heads now working in the mines, Arthur counts the days before he can launch his personal revolution. The God's flesh gives them the power to transform, their heads becoming those of pigs with various enhanced abilities.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"01mn7siiiis7nm10","name":"The Pig Heads - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pig Heads","ownerKey":"the-pig-heads","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Pig Heads - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers</p>","positive":"We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"The Pig Heads","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01vcuwhaahwucv10","name":"The Pig Heads - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pig Heads","ownerKey":"the-pig-heads","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"The Pig Heads - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>The God's flesh gives us power and fills us with the anger we need to wage our war</p>","positive":"The God's flesh gives us power and fills us with the anger we need to wage our war"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>The God's flesh gives us power and fills us with the anger we need to wage our war</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"The Pig Heads","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"The God's flesh gives us power and fills us with the anger we need to wage our war","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"019d2v1mm1v2d910","name":"Pigs' Gang","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pig Heads","ownerKey":"the-pig-heads","itemKey":"don1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Pigs' Gang","system":{"description":"<p>When they act, each member of the gang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes that of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to communicate with them. Their mutation grants a random power, roll 1 die:</p><p>1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional Wound once per Scene<br>2. Speed, once per Scene acts 2 times consecutively<br>3. Resistance, +1 Wound<br>4. Abomination, +1 to Opposition Level<br>5. Grunt, once per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it receive 1 Penalty on their next action<br>6. Out of control, the OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the NPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>When they act, each member of the gang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes that of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to communicate with them. Their mutation grants a random power, roll 1 die:</p><p>1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional Wound once per Scene<br>2. Speed, once per Scene acts 2 times consecutively<br>3. Resistance, +1 Wound<br>4. Abomination, +1 to Opposition Level<br>5. Grunt, once per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it receive 1 Penalty on their next action<br>6. Out of control, the OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the NPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.aldeano","owner":"The Pig Heads","category":"Villager Gift","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01oky9o88o9yko10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pig Heads","ownerKey":"the-pig-heads","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A criminal gang that wanders through the backways of Whitehaven. They kidnap or injure only factory workers to make them unable to work, wearing grotesque pig masks to hide their faces. Nobody recognizes them because of the masks. In reality, they are miners who have eaten meat contaminated with the flesh of The God Under the Mine, distributed secretly by Frank Browne at the slaughterhouse. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence Browne approaches them, offering the opportunity to join the gang in their personal war against Bardolf Greed. With over fifty Pig Heads now working in the mines, Arthur counts the days before he can launch his personal revolution. The God's flesh gives them the power to transform, their heads becoming those of pigs with various enhanced abilities.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers<br>2. The God's flesh gives us power and fills us with the anger we need to wage our war</p><p>Gifts:<br>Pigs' Gang: When they act, each member of the gang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes that of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to communicate with them. Their mutation grants a random power, roll 1 die:</p><p>1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional Wound once per Scene<br>2. Speed, once per Scene acts 2 times consecutively<br>3. Resistance, +1 Wound<br>4. Abomination, +1 to Opposition Level<br>5. Grunt, once per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it receive 1 Penalty on their next action<br>6. Out of control, the OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the NPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A criminal gang that wanders through the backways of Whitehaven. They kidnap or injure only factory workers to make them unable to work, wearing grotesque pig masks to hide their faces. Nobody recognizes them because of the masks. In reality, they are miners who have eaten meat contaminated with the flesh of The God Under the Mine, distributed secretly by Frank Browne at the slaughterhouse. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence Browne approaches them, offering the opportunity to join the gang in their personal war against Bardolf Greed. With over fifty Pig Heads now working in the mines, Arthur counts the days before he can launch his personal revolution. The God's flesh gives them the power to transform, their heads becoming those of pigs with various enhanced abilities.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers<br>2. The God's flesh gives us power and fills us with the anger we need to wage our war</p><p>Gifts:<br>Pigs' Gang: When they act, each member of the gang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes that of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to communicate with them. Their mutation grants a random power, roll 1 die:</p><p>1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional Wound once per Scene<br>2. Speed, once per Scene acts 2 times consecutively<br>3. Resistance, +1 Wound<br>4. Abomination, +1 to Opposition Level<br>5. Grunt, once per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it receive 1 Penalty on their next action<br>6. Out of control, the OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the NPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"The Pig Heads","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01jtvjsmmsjvtj10","name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","type":"threat","img":"icons/weapons/thrown/net-weighted-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/weapons/thrown/net-weighted-purple.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-trebizond-princess-of-a-distant-country","ownerKey":"trebizond-princess-of-a-distant-country","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Trebizond is Paladin #1 (roll 1d6 to determine which Paladin appears). Her curiosity is both strength and weakness—she might be distracted by fascinating objects or stories, or convinced to question orders if shown something truly unique. She works well with other Paladins but sometimes pursues her own interests. Can be separated from group by exploiting her curiosity. Voice: Accented, expressive, asks many questions. Mannerisms: Examines everything closely, touches unfamiliar objects.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Trebizond is Paladin #1 (roll 1d6 to determine which Paladin appears). Her curiosity is both strength and weakness—she might be distracted by fascinating objects or stories, or convinced to question orders if shown something truly unique. She works well with other Paladins but sometimes pursues her own interests. Can be separated from group by exploiting her curiosity. Voice: Accented, expressive, asks many questions. Mannerisms: Examines everything closely, touches unfamiliar objects.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00vgdyhnnhydgv00","name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","ownerKey":"trebizond-princess-of-a-distant-country","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in service of Saint George</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00g1fnizzinf1g00","name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","ownerKey":"trebizond-princess-of-a-distant-country","itemKey":"descriptor1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","positive":"His word, for me, is law"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>His word, for me, is law</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.amenaza","owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"His word, for me, is law","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"011z081vv180z110","name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","ownerKey":"trebizond-princess-of-a-distant-country","itemKey":"descriptor2.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.amenaza","owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01c6e9hvvh9e6c10","name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","ownerKey":"trebizond-princess-of-a-distant-country","itemKey":"descriptor3.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>Sometimes I am seized by unshakeable curiosity about new things</p>","positive":"Sometimes I am seized by unshakeable curiosity about new things"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Sometimes I am seized by unshakeable curiosity about new things</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.amenaza","owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Sometimes I am seized by unshakeable curiosity about new things","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ihq5osso5qhi00","name":"Paladin - From a Far Country","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","ownerKey":"trebizond-princess-of-a-distant-country","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Paladin - From a Far Country","system":{"description":"<p>Trebizond can make use of exotic weapons and objects to surprise opponents. Once per Scene, she can create a Descriptor that represents special equipment, such as 'Magic-Finding Dust' or 'A Whip as Sharp as a Blade' or 'Poison from the Eastern Lands' or 'Mechanical Crossbow of My Homeland'. When using her special equipment, Trebizond increases her Opposition Level by 1 (to 6). The equipment lasts for the Scene and provides tactical advantages beyond just the OL bonus.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Trebizond can make use of exotic weapons and objects to surprise opponents. Once per Scene, she can create a Descriptor that represents special equipment, such as 'Magic-Finding Dust' or 'A Whip as Sharp as a Blade' or 'Poison from the Eastern Lands' or 'Mechanical Crossbow of My Homeland'. When using her special equipment, Trebizond increases her Opposition Level by 1 (to 6). The equipment lasts for the Scene and provides tactical advantages beyond just the OL bonus.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00umknoqqonkmu00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","ownerKey":"trebizond-princess-of-a-distant-country","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. Sometimes I am seized by unshakeable curiosity about new things</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - From a Far Country: Trebizond can make use of exotic weapons and objects to surprise opponents. Once per Scene, she can create a Descriptor that represents special equipment, such as 'Magic-Finding Dust' or 'A Whip as Sharp as a Blade' or 'Poison from the Eastern Lands' or 'Mechanical Crossbow of My Homeland'. When using her special equipment, Trebizond increases her Opposition Level by 1 (to 6). The equipment lasts for the Scene and provides tactical advantages beyond just the OL bonus.</p><p>Notes:<br>Trebizond is Paladin #1 (roll 1d6 to determine which Paladin appears). Her curiosity is both strength and weakness—she might be distracted by fascinating objects or stories, or convinced to question orders if shown something truly unique. She works well with other Paladins but sometimes pursues her own interests. Can be separated from group by exploiting her curiosity. Voice: Accented, expressive, asks many questions. Mannerisms: Examines everything closely, touches unfamiliar objects.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a Paladin in service of Saint George<br>2. His word, for me, is law<br>3. Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales<br>4. Sometimes I am seized by unshakeable curiosity about new things</p><p>Gifts:<br>Paladin - From a Far Country: Trebizond can make use of exotic weapons and objects to surprise opponents. Once per Scene, she can create a Descriptor that represents special equipment, such as 'Magic-Finding Dust' or 'A Whip as Sharp as a Blade' or 'Poison from the Eastern Lands' or 'Mechanical Crossbow of My Homeland'. When using her special equipment, Trebizond increases her Opposition Level by 1 (to 6). The equipment lasts for the Scene and provides tactical advantages beyond just the OL bonus.</p><p>Notes:<br>Trebizond is Paladin #1 (roll 1d6 to determine which Paladin appears). Her curiosity is both strength and weakness—she might be distracted by fascinating objects or stories, or convinced to question orders if shown something truly unique. She works well with other Paladins but sometimes pursues her own interests. Can be separated from group by exploiting her curiosity. Voice: Accented, expressive, asks many questions. Mannerisms: Examines everything closely, touches unfamiliar objects.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"01tk1ts22st1kt10","name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","type":"villager","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-villagers-of-emerald-wish-warped-souls","ownerKey":"villagers-of-emerald-wish-warped-souls","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Villagers of Emerald typically appear in groups of 3-5 with different wishes. Emphasize the tragedy—they're victims, not villains. If Henkle is defeated or the well destroyed, many may revert to normal or at least stop serving him. Smart Hunters can use persuasion to convince wish-warped villagers that Henkle won't fix them. The ones who wished for health are particularly difficult as they regenerate constantly. Roll for each villager encountered to create variety.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I was an ordinary villager who made a wish at the well</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Villagers of Emerald typically appear in groups of 3-5 with different wishes. Emphasize the tragedy—they're victims, not villains. If Henkle is defeated or the well destroyed, many may revert to normal or at least stop serving him. Smart Hunters can use persuasion to convince wish-warped villagers that Henkle won't fix them. The ones who wished for health are particularly difficult as they regenerate constantly. Roll for each villager encountered to create variety.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I was an ordinary villager who made a wish at the well</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00yhee0tt0eehy00","name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","ownerKey":"villagers-of-emerald-wish-warped-souls","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I was an ordinary villager who made a wish at the well</p>","positive":"I was an ordinary villager who made a wish at the well"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I was an ordinary villager who made a wish at the well</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I was an ordinary villager who made a wish at the well","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"0189yr6nn6ry9810","name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","ownerKey":"villagers-of-emerald-wish-warped-souls","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>My wish was granted, but not in the way I hoped</p>","positive":"My wish was granted, but not in the way I hoped"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>My wish was granted, but not in the way I hoped</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"My wish was granted, but not in the way I hoped","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00qc7y4ll4y7cq00","name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","ownerKey":"villagers-of-emerald-wish-warped-souls","itemKey":"descriptor2.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>Now I am a monster</p>","positive":"Now I am a monster"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Now I am a monster</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.aldeano","owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Now I am a monster","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"001a9bz33zb9a100","name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","ownerKey":"villagers-of-emerald-wish-warped-souls","itemKey":"descriptor3.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I serve the wizard who promised to fix everything</p>","positive":"I serve the wizard who promised to fix everything"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I serve the wizard who promised to fix everything</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.aldeano","owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I serve the wizard who promised to fix everything","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01fsbuhvvhubsf10","name":"Careful What You Wish For","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","ownerKey":"villagers-of-emerald-wish-warped-souls","itemKey":"don1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Careful What You Wish For","system":{"description":"<p>Each Villager of Emerald has been transformed by their wish. Roll 1d6+1 to determine: **1-Wealth:** Spits 1d6 gold coins at enemies, hitting up to 3 targets within 15ft, each hit inflicts 1 Wound, also vomits bile constantly. **2-Beauty:** Body constantly warps and shifts, anyone looking suffers 1 Penalty on Checks due to disturbing sight. **3-Health:** Cannot die or stay injured, regenerates 1 Wound at start of each Exchange, only defeated by destroying well or reversing wish. **4-Skill:** Supernaturally skilled at profession, OL increases to 5, performs craft obsessively even in combat. **5-Never Sleep:** Cannot sleep, exhausted and manic, chatters nonsense constantly, speech causes 1 Penalty on concentration Checks. **6-Grow Up:** Child with giant body but childish mind, has 3 Wounds total, inflicts +1 Wound damage, cries and tantrums during combat. **7-Love:** Merged with beloved into one body, can act twice per Exchange, argue constantly about what to do (if convinced to stop, both stop).</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Each Villager of Emerald has been transformed by their wish. Roll 1d6+1 to determine: **1-Wealth:** Spits 1d6 gold coins at enemies, hitting up to 3 targets within 15ft, each hit inflicts 1 Wound, also vomits bile constantly. **2-Beauty:** Body constantly warps and shifts, anyone looking suffers 1 Penalty on Checks due to disturbing sight. **3-Health:** Cannot die or stay injured, regenerates 1 Wound at start of each Exchange, only defeated by destroying well or reversing wish. **4-Skill:** Supernaturally skilled at profession, OL increases to 5, performs craft obsessively even in combat. **5-Never Sleep:** Cannot sleep, exhausted and manic, chatters nonsense constantly, speech causes 1 Penalty on concentration Checks. **6-Grow Up:** Child with giant body but childish mind, has 3 Wounds total, inflicts +1 Wound damage, cries and tantrums during combat. **7-Love:** Merged with beloved into one body, can act twice per Exchange, argue constantly about what to do (if convinced to stop, both stop).</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.aldeano","owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","category":"Villager Gift","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"01wx1tl77lt1xw10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","ownerKey":"villagers-of-emerald-wish-warped-souls","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I was an ordinary villager who made a wish at the well<br>2. My wish was granted, but not in the way I hoped<br>3. Now I am a monster<br>4. I serve the wizard who promised to fix everything</p><p>Gifts:<br>Careful What You Wish For: Each Villager of Emerald has been transformed by their wish. Roll 1d6+1 to determine: **1-Wealth:** Spits 1d6 gold coins at enemies, hitting up to 3 targets within 15ft, each hit inflicts 1 Wound, also vomits bile constantly. **2-Beauty:** Body constantly warps and shifts, anyone looking suffers 1 Penalty on Checks due to disturbing sight. **3-Health:** Cannot die or stay injured, regenerates 1 Wound at start of each Exchange, only defeated by destroying well or reversing wish. **4-Skill:** Supernaturally skilled at profession, OL increases to 5, performs craft obsessively even in combat. **5-Never Sleep:** Cannot sleep, exhausted and manic, chatters nonsense constantly, speech causes 1 Penalty on concentration Checks. **6-Grow Up:** Child with giant body but childish mind, has 3 Wounds total, inflicts +1 Wound damage, cries and tantrums during combat. **7-Love:** Merged with beloved into one body, can act twice per Exchange, argue constantly about what to do (if convinced to stop, both stop).</p><p>Notes:<br>Villagers of Emerald typically appear in groups of 3-5 with different wishes. Emphasize the tragedy—they're victims, not villains. If Henkle is defeated or the well destroyed, many may revert to normal or at least stop serving him. Smart Hunters can use persuasion to convince wish-warped villagers that Henkle won't fix them. The ones who wished for health are particularly difficult as they regenerate constantly. Roll for each villager encountered to create variety.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I was an ordinary villager who made a wish at the well<br>2. My wish was granted, but not in the way I hoped<br>3. Now I am a monster<br>4. I serve the wizard who promised to fix everything</p><p>Gifts:<br>Careful What You Wish For: Each Villager of Emerald has been transformed by their wish. Roll 1d6+1 to determine: **1-Wealth:** Spits 1d6 gold coins at enemies, hitting up to 3 targets within 15ft, each hit inflicts 1 Wound, also vomits bile constantly. **2-Beauty:** Body constantly warps and shifts, anyone looking suffers 1 Penalty on Checks due to disturbing sight. **3-Health:** Cannot die or stay injured, regenerates 1 Wound at start of each Exchange, only defeated by destroying well or reversing wish. **4-Skill:** Supernaturally skilled at profession, OL increases to 5, performs craft obsessively even in combat. **5-Never Sleep:** Cannot sleep, exhausted and manic, chatters nonsense constantly, speech causes 1 Penalty on concentration Checks. **6-Grow Up:** Child with giant body but childish mind, has 3 Wounds total, inflicts +1 Wound damage, cries and tantrums during combat. **7-Love:** Merged with beloved into one body, can act twice per Exchange, argue constantly about what to do (if convinced to stop, both stop).</p><p>Notes:<br>Villagers of Emerald typically appear in groups of 3-5 with different wishes. Emphasize the tragedy—they're victims, not villains. If Henkle is defeated or the well destroyed, many may revert to normal or at least stop serving him. Smart Hunters can use persuasion to convince wish-warped villagers that Henkle won't fix them. The ones who wished for health are particularly difficult as they regenerate constantly. Roll for each villager encountered to create variety.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Villagers of Emerald - Wish-Warped Souls","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00ojt4tjjt4tjo00","name":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/guard.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01njdcge01n6xrwp","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","actorLink":true,"disposition":-1,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/guard.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-adversary-vincent-arn-former-huntsman-and-chief-of-the-guards","ownerKey":"vincent-arn-former-huntsman-and-chief-of-the-guards","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Adversaries.db","sourceBackup":"Adversaries.db","npcKind":"adversary","translations":{"es":{"name":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","system":{"details":{"concept":"Adversario de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Adversario","notes":"<p>Vincent leads the guards and is an extension of Elizaveta’s will. He is an experienced and dangerous obstacle.</p>"},"threat":{"rank":"Media 5","impulse":"I understand how the world works and who really runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the best way to maintain my status.","oppositionLevel":5}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Adversary","origin":"Core Book","role":"Adversary","notes":"<p>Vincent leads the guards and is an extension of Elizaveta’s will. He is an experienced and dangerous obstacle.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":3,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I understand how the world works and who really runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the best way to maintain my status.","oppositionLevel":5}},"items":[{"_id":"00lsm31cc13msl00","name":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","ownerKey":"vincent-arn-former-huntsman-and-chief-of-the-guards","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms about doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life without working so hard.</p>","positive":"I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms about doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life without working so hard."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms about doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life without working so hard.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.amenaza","owner":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","category":"Threat Descriptor","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms about doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life without working so hard.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00ekk29ii92kke00","name":"Veteran","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","ownerKey":"vincent-arn-former-huntsman-and-chief-of-the-guards","itemKey":"don1.amenaza","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Veteran","system":{"description":"<p>Vincent is skilled in taking advantage of any situation. When he has the support of at least two allies, he gains 1 Additional Success to Position Checks. If he is supported by at least three of his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty and Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Vincent is skilled in taking advantage of any situation. When he has the support of at least two allies, he gains 1 Additional Success to Position Checks. If he is supported by at least three of his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty and Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"don1.amenaza","owner":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","category":"Threat Gift","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0}},{"_id":"00wyng1pp1gnyw00","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","ownerKey":"vincent-arn-former-huntsman-and-chief-of-the-guards","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Vincent Arn served as a huntsman before climbing the ranks to become the chief of the guards under Gerard Dubois. Though loyal in appearance, he has aligned himself with Elizaveta for personal gain.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms about doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life without working so hard.</p><p>Agenda:<br>I understand how the world works and who really runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the best way to maintain my status.</p><p>Gifts:<br>Veteran: Vincent is skilled in taking advantage of any situation. When he has the support of at least two allies, he gains 1 Additional Success to Position Checks. If he is supported by at least three of his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty and Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.</p><p>Notes:<br>Vincent leads the guards and is an extension of Elizaveta’s will. He is an experienced and dangerous obstacle.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Vincent Arn served as a huntsman before climbing the ranks to become the chief of the guards under Gerard Dubois. Though loyal in appearance, he has aligned himself with Elizaveta for personal gain.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms about doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life without working so hard.</p><p>Agenda:<br>I understand how the world works and who really runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the best way to maintain my status.</p><p>Gifts:<br>Veteran: Vincent is skilled in taking advantage of any situation. When he has the support of at least two allies, he gains 1 Additional Success to Position Checks. If he is supported by at least three of his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty and Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.</p><p>Notes:<br>Vincent leads the guards and is an extension of Elizaveta’s will. He is an experienced and dangerous obstacle.</p>","notes":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","category":"Source","source":"Adversaries.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00vu7t3773t7uv00","name":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere","type":"villager","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-vincenzo-carabiniere","ownerKey":"vincenzo-carabiniere","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"PNJ principal","notes":"<p>Potential ally to the Hunters. Can provide information about the investigation and local knowledge. Will offer assistance once the Hunters identify themselves.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find out what lies behind the disappearances in Sinalunga","contact":"<p>A military officer investigating the murders in Sinalunga. Vincenzo is in close contact with the Order and should be aware that Hunters are arriving in town. He is questioning two farmers, Lapo and Cino, who discovered the well containing the mutilated corpses. An honest and dedicated investigator who will assist the Hunters if they reveal their identity to him.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields.</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Potential ally to the Hunters. Can provide information about the investigation and local knowledge. Will offer assistance once the Hunters identify themselves.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Find out what lies behind the disappearances in Sinalunga","contact":"<p>A military officer investigating the murders in Sinalunga. Vincenzo is in close contact with the Order and should be aware that Hunters are arriving in town. He is questioning two farmers, Lapo and Cino, who discovered the well containing the mutilated corpses. An honest and dedicated investigator who will assist the Hunters if they reveal their identity to him.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields.</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00hthjiuuijhth00","name":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere","ownerKey":"vincenzo-carabiniere","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields.</p>","positive":"I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields."}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01iwo830038owi10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere","ownerKey":"vincenzo-carabiniere","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>A military officer investigating the murders in Sinalunga. Vincenzo is in close contact with the Order and should be aware that Hunters are arriving in town. He is questioning two farmers, Lapo and Cino, who discovered the well containing the mutilated corpses. An honest and dedicated investigator who will assist the Hunters if they reveal their identity to him.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find out what lies behind the disappearances in Sinalunga</p><p>Notes:<br>Potential ally to the Hunters. Can provide information about the investigation and local knowledge. Will offer assistance once the Hunters identify themselves.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>A military officer investigating the murders in Sinalunga. Vincenzo is in close contact with the Order and should be aware that Hunters are arriving in town. He is questioning two farmers, Lapo and Cino, who discovered the well containing the mutilated corpses. An honest and dedicated investigator who will assist the Hunters if they reveal their identity to him.</p><p>Descriptors:<br>1. I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields.</p><p>Agenda:<br>Find out what lies behind the disappearances in Sinalunga</p><p>Notes:<br>Potential ally to the Hunters. Can provide information about the investigation and local knowledge. Will offer assistance once the Hunters identify themselves.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"_id":"00pdidiccididp00","name":"William - The Man of Law","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"William - The Man of Law","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/cleric.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-william-the-man-of-law","ownerKey":"william-the-man-of-law","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"William - The Man of Law","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Bardolf Greed's trusted lawyer who manages all accounts for the factories and mine. He records everything in a large black leather book and stands behind Bardolf during meetings. William knows all of Greed's secrets and handles the legal maneuvering that allows the industrialist to maintain control over Whitehaven.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"<p>Bardolf Greed's trusted lawyer who manages all accounts for the factories and mine. He records everything in a large black leather book and stands behind Bardolf during meetings. William knows all of Greed's secrets and handles the legal maneuvering that allows the industrialist to maintain control over Whitehaven.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a prominent lawyer and I know all of Bardolf's secrets</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Bardolf Greed's trusted lawyer who manages all accounts for the factories and mine. He records everything in a large black leather book and stands behind Bardolf during meetings. William knows all of Greed's secrets and handles the legal maneuvering that allows the industrialist to maintain control over Whitehaven.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,