{"_id":"00e3xm5qq5mx3e00","name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","type":"villager","img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-entangled-humanoid.webp","effects":[],"folder":"01s3j0z5002t5810","ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-entangled-humanoid.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-villager-wolfgang-the-enslaved-pharmacist","ownerKey":"wolfgang-the-enslaved-pharmacist","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"Villager.db","sourceBackup":"Villager.db","npcKind":"villager","translations":{"es":{"name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","system":{"details":{"concept":"Aldeano de escenario","origin":"Libro básico","role":"Aldeano","notes":"<p>Wolfgang can be a valuable ally if the Hunters gain his trust. He knows: the recipe for Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop, elderberry), safe paths through the animated forest, the layout of Helga's mansion, and that elderberry is the key ingredient Helga forbids. If freed from blood magic control, he'll help the Hunters escape and provide medical assistance.</p>"},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I'm a simple pharmacist forced to pretend to be a druid</p>"}}}}}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Core Book","role":"Villager","notes":"<p>Wolfgang can be a valuable ally if the Hunters gain his trust. He knows: the recipe for Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop, elderberry), safe paths through the animated forest, the layout of Helga's mansion, and that elderberry is the key ingredient Helga forbids. If freed from blood magic control, he'll help the Hunters escape and provide medical assistance.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"","contact":"","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I'm a simple pharmacist forced to pretend to be a druid</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"00o2sk0aa0ks2o00","name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","ownerKey":"wolfgang-the-enslaved-pharmacist","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist - Descriptor","system":{"description":"<p>I'm a simple pharmacist forced to pretend to be a druid</p>","positive":"I'm a simple pharmacist forced to pretend to be a druid"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I'm a simple pharmacist forced to pretend to be a druid</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.aldeano","owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I'm a simple pharmacist forced to pretend to be a druid","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"019bkuecceukb910","name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","ownerKey":"wolfgang-the-enslaved-pharmacist","itemKey":"descriptor1.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist - Descriptor 2","system":{"description":"<p>Helga threatens my family if I don't obey</p>","positive":"Helga threatens my family if I don't obey"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Helga threatens my family if I don't obey</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor1.aldeano","owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"Helga threatens my family if I don't obey","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01n5vueiieuv5n10","name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","ownerKey":"wolfgang-the-enslaved-pharmacist","itemKey":"descriptor2.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist - Descriptor 3","system":{"description":"<p>I hate what I've become, but I don't know how to escape</p>","positive":"I hate what I've become, but I don't know how to escape"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I hate what I've become, but I don't know how to escape</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.aldeano","owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I hate what I've become, but I don't know how to escape","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"00v7zwykkywz7v00","name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","ownerKey":"wolfgang-the-enslaved-pharmacist","itemKey":"descriptor3.aldeano","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist - Descriptor 4","system":{"description":"<p>I know herbs and medicines, not magic</p>","positive":"I know herbs and medicines, not magic"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>I know herbs and medicines, not magic</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.aldeano","owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","category":"Villager Descriptor","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I know herbs and medicines, not magic","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"01to30cvvc03ot10","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","ownerKey":"wolfgang-the-enslaved-pharmacist","sourcePack":"broken-tales.scenario-actors","translations":{"es":{"name":"Texto fuente","system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I'm a simple pharmacist forced to pretend to be a druid<br>2. Helga threatens my family if I don't obey<br>3. I hate what I've become, but I don't know how to escape<br>4. I know herbs and medicines, not magic</p><p>Notes:<br>Wolfgang can be a valuable ally if the Hunters gain his trust. He knows: the recipe for Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop, elderberry), safe paths through the animated forest, the layout of Helga's mansion, and that elderberry is the key ingredient Helga forbids. If freed from blood magic control, he'll help the Hunters escape and provide medical assistance.</p>"}}}}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptors:<br>1. I'm a simple pharmacist forced to pretend to be a druid<br>2. Helga threatens my family if I don't obey<br>3. I hate what I've become, but I don't know how to escape<br>4. I know herbs and medicines, not magic</p><p>Notes:<br>Wolfgang can be a valuable ally if the Hunters gain his trust. He knows: the recipe for Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop, elderberry), safe paths through the animated forest, the layout of Helga's mansion, and that elderberry is the key ingredient Helga forbids. If freed from blood magic control, he'll help the Hunters escape and provide medical assistance.</p>","notes":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"hoja-fuente","owner":"Wolfgang - The Enslaved Pharmacist","category":"Source","source":"Villager.db (legacy structured backup)"}}]}
{"name":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","type":"villager","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-cat.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0},"prototypeToken":{"name":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"texture":{"src":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-cat.webp"}},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyNames":["Adam - The Chatty Servant"],"ownerKey":"adam-the-chatty-servant","collection":"Legacy Structured Backup","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db","npcKind":"villager"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Scenario Villager","origin":"Legacy Structured Backup","role":"NPC","notes":"<p>Adam is a young man in his twenties who works on Andersen's estate to pay off a debt he owes to the former commander. Unlike the twenty-plus other servants who can come and go freely, Adam cannot escape to the nearby city—he is bound by his obligation until the debt is cleared. Despite his circumstances, Adam is remarkably talkative and sociable, perhaps because he craves connection and conversation to break up the monotony of estate work. He observes everything that happens in the household and has no qualms about sharing gossip with visitors, including the Hunters. Adam knows there is a complex and troubled relationship between Andersen and Satu, and he's observed that the woman comes from the Captain's past, though he doesn't know the sordid details. He's also noticed that Andersen is very considerate of young Erik and clearly regards the boy as a son, though again Adam doesn't know why. Adam provides the Hunters with useful social intelligence about the estate's inhabitants and dynamics. He can be encountered wandering the estate grounds and will eagerly approach visitors to chat.</p>"},"background":"<p>Adam is a young man in his twenties who works on Andersen's estate to pay off a debt he owes to the former commander. Unlike the twenty-plus other servants who can come and go freely, Adam cannot escape to the nearby city—he is bound by his obligation until the debt is cleared. Despite his circumstances, Adam is remarkably talkative and sociable, perhaps because he craves connection and conversation to break up the monotony of estate work. He observes everything that happens in the household and has no qualms about sharing gossip with visitors, including the Hunters. Adam knows there is a complex and troubled relationship between Andersen and Satu, and he's observed that the woman comes from the Captain's past, though he doesn't know the sordid details. He's also noticed that Andersen is very considerate of young Erik and clearly regards the boy as a son, though again Adam doesn't know why. Adam provides the Hunters with useful social intelligence about the estate's inhabitants and dynamics. He can be encountered wandering the estate grounds and will eagerly approach visitors to chat.</p>","resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"threat":{"rank":"easy","impulse":"Pass the time by talking with interesting visitors","oppositionLevel":3},"villager":{"age":"","bond":"Pass the time by talking with interesting visitors\nEventually pay off my debt and return to the city\nUnderstand the strange dynamics between Andersen, Satu, and Erik","contact":"<p>Adam is a young man in his twenties who works on Andersen's estate to pay off a debt he owes to the former commander. Unlike the twenty-plus other servants who can come and go freely, Adam cannot escape to the nearby city—he is bound by his obligation until the debt is cleared. Despite his circumstances, Adam is remarkably talkative and sociable, perhaps because he craves connection and conversation to break up the monotony of estate work. He observes everything that happens in the household and has no qualms about sharing gossip with visitors, including the Hunters. Adam knows there is a complex and troubled relationship between Andersen and Satu, and he's observed that the woman comes from the Captain's past, though he doesn't know the sordid details. He's also noticed that Andersen is very considerate of young Erik and clearly regards the boy as a son, though again Adam doesn't know why. Adam provides the Hunters with useful social intelligence about the estate's inhabitants and dynamics. He can be encountered wandering the estate grounds and will eagerly approach visitors to chat.</p>","distinguishingFeatures":"<p>I am a talkative young servant bound by debt to Andersen</p>"}},"items":[{"_id":"cWKJirJMp4s8rjDl","name":"Adam - The Chatty Servant - Principal Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","ownerKey":"adam-the-chatty-servant","itemKey":"descriptor-principal.adam-the-chatty-servant","contentKey":"descriptor-principal.adam-the-chatty-servant","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db","role":"principal-descriptor","descriptorRole":"principal-descriptor","key":"descriptor-principal.cazador"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a talkative young servant bound by debt to Andersen</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor-principal.adam-the-chatty-servant","owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","category":"Principal Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I am a talkative young servant bound by debt to Andersen","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"yL6xMlCbDtit1Htb","name":"Adam - The Chatty Servant - Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","ownerKey":"adam-the-chatty-servant","itemKey":"descriptor2.adam-the-chatty-servant","contentKey":"descriptor2.adam-the-chatty-servant","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I observe everything that happens on this estate</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor2.adam-the-chatty-servant","owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I observe everything that happens on this estate","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"RocAKgeWLFC51FXd","name":"Adam - The Chatty Servant - Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","ownerKey":"adam-the-chatty-servant","itemKey":"descriptor3.adam-the-chatty-servant","contentKey":"descriptor3.adam-the-chatty-servant","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I enjoy conversation and sharing what I know</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor3.adam-the-chatty-servant","owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I enjoy conversation and sharing what I know","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"ZUPS2ncr5YXCLJBy","name":"Adam - The Chatty Servant - Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","ownerKey":"adam-the-chatty-servant","itemKey":"descriptor4.adam-the-chatty-servant","contentKey":"descriptor4.adam-the-chatty-servant","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I cannot leave the estate until my debt is paid</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"descriptor4.adam-the-chatty-servant","owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","category":"Scenario Descriptor","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","positive":"I cannot leave the estate until my debt is paid","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false}},{"_id":"NlTGNiezcQaT33Rw","name":"Agenda","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","ownerKey":"adam-the-chatty-servant","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Pass the time by talking with interesting visitors</p><p>Eventually pay off my debt and return to the city</p><p>Understand the strange dynamics between Andersen, Satu, and Erik</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.agenda","owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}},{"_id":"WllsdmrJV6pqDifT","name":"Notes","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","ownerKey":"adam-the-chatty-servant","sourceBackup":"Villager 1.db"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Adam serves as an information source for Hunters exploring the estate. Voice: Fast-talking, gossipy, friendly. Encountered on a roll of 5-6 when exploring estate. Provides social context: complex relationship between Andersen and Satu, they have a shared past, Andersen treats Erik like a son. Doesn't know about the rape, murder, or Enar's return—just observes surface behavior. Over 20 servants work on the estate but most are inexperienced fighters and would flee if Enar attacks. Only Andersen and Christian are skilled combatants. Adam himself is not a fighter. Willing to help Hunters in non-combat ways (showing them around, delivering messages, providing supplies). Represents the ordinary people caught up in extraordinary circumstances.</p>","notes":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)","key":"story.notes","owner":"Adam - The Chatty Servant","category":"Legacy Notes","source":"Villager 1.db (legacy structured backup)"}}],"_id":"smn6WTloIyZpJNhL"}
